56 class JSCallReducerAssembler : public JSGraphAssembler {
57  static constexpr bool kMarkLoopExits = true;
58 
59  public:
60  JSCallReducerAssembler(JSCallReducer* reducer, Node* node,
61  Node* effect = nullptr, Node* control = nullptr)
62  : JSGraphAssembler(
63  reducer->broker(), reducer->JSGraphForGraphAssembler(),
64  reducer->ZoneForGraphAssembler(), BranchSemantics::kJS,
65  [reducer](Node* n) { reducer->RevisitForGraphAssembler(n); },
66  kMarkLoopExits),
67  dependencies_(reducer->dependencies()),
68  node_(node) {
69  InitializeEffectControl(
70  effect ? effect : NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node),
71  control ? control : NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node));
72 
73  // Finish initializing the outermost catch scope.
74  bool has_handler =
75  NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &outermost_handler_);
76  outermost_catch_scope_.set_has_handler(has_handler);
77  }

164  void MaybeInsertMapChecks(MapInference* inference,
165  bool has_stability_dependency) {
166  // TODO(jgruber): Implement MapInference::InsertMapChecks in graph
167  // assembler.
168  if (!has_stability_dependency) {
169  Effect e = effect();
170  inference->InsertMapChecks(jsgraph(), &e, Control{control()}, feedback());

175  TNode<Object> ConvertHoleToUndefined(TNode<Object> value, ElementsKind kind) {
176  DCHECK(IsHoleyElementsKind(kind));
177  if (kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
178 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
179  return AddNode<Number>(graph()->NewNode(
180  simplified()->ChangeFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleToTagged(), value));
181 #else
182  return AddNode<Number>(
183  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeFloat64HoleToTagged(), value));
184 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
185  }
186  return ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(value);
187  }

189  class TryCatchBuilder0 {
190  public:
191  using TryFunction = VoidGenerator0;
192  using CatchFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Object>)>;
193 
194  TryCatchBuilder0(JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm, const TryFunction& try_body)
195  : gasm_(gasm), try_body_(try_body) {}
196 
197  void Catch(const CatchFunction& catch_body) {
198  TNode<Object> handler_exception;
199  Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
200  Control handler_control{nullptr};
201 
202  auto continuation = gasm_->MakeLabel();
203 
204  // Try.
205  {
206  CatchScope catch_scope = CatchScope::Inner(gasm_->temp_zone(), gasm_);
207  try_body_();
208  gasm_->Goto(&continuation);
209 
210  catch_scope.MergeExceptionalPaths(&handler_exception, &handler_effect,
211  &handler_control);
212  }
213 
214  // Catch.
215  {
216  gasm_->InitializeEffectControl(handler_effect, handler_control);
217  catch_body(handler_exception);
218  gasm_->Goto(&continuation);
219  }
220 
221  gasm_->Bind(&continuation);
222  }
223 
224  private:
225  JSCallReducerAssembler* const gasm_;
226  const VoidGenerator0 try_body_;
227  };
228 
229  TryCatchBuilder0 Try(const VoidGenerator0& try_body) {
230  return {this, try_body};
231  }

233  using ConditionFunction1 = std::function<TNode<Boolean>(TNode<Number>)>;
234  using StepFunction1 = std::function<TNode<Number>(TNode<Number>)>;
235  class ForBuilder0 {
236  using For0BodyFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Number>)>;
237 
238  public:
239  ForBuilder0(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Number> initial_value,
240  const ConditionFunction1& cond, const StepFunction1& step)
241  : gasm_(gasm),
242  initial_value_(initial_value),
243  cond_(cond),
244  step_(step) {}
245 
246  void Do(const For0BodyFunction& body) {
247  auto loop_exit = gasm_->MakeLabel();
248 
249  {
250  GraphAssembler::LoopScope<kPhiRepresentation> loop_scope(gasm_);
251 
252  auto loop_header = loop_scope.loop_header_label();
253  auto loop_body = gasm_->MakeLabel();
254 
255  gasm_->Goto(loop_header, initial_value_);
256 
257  gasm_->Bind(loop_header);
258  TNode<Number> i = loop_header->PhiAt<Number>(0);
259 
260  gasm_->BranchWithHint(cond_(i), &loop_body, &loop_exit,
261  BranchHint::kTrue);
262 
263  gasm_->Bind(&loop_body);
264  body(i);
265  gasm_->Goto(loop_header, step_(i));
266  }
267 
268  gasm_->Bind(&loop_exit);
269  }
270 
271  private:
272  static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
273  MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
274 
275  JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
276  const TNode<Number> initial_value_;
277  const ConditionFunction1 cond_;
278  const StepFunction1 step_;
279  };
280 
281  ForBuilder0 ForZeroUntil(TNode<Number> excluded_limit) {
282  TNode<Number> initial_value = ZeroConstant();
283  auto cond = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
284  return NumberLessThan(i, excluded_limit);
285  };
286  auto step = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
287  return NumberAdd(i, OneConstant());
288  };
289  return {this, initial_value, cond, step};
290  }
291 
292  ForBuilder0 Forever(TNode<Number> initial_value, const StepFunction1& step) {
293  return {this, initial_value,
294  [=, this](TNode<Number>) { return TrueConstant(); }, step};
295  }

297  using For1BodyFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Number>, TNode<Object>*)>;
298  class ForBuilder1 {
299  public:
300  ForBuilder1(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Number> initial_value,
301  const ConditionFunction1& cond, const StepFunction1& step,
302  TNode<Object> initial_arg0)
303  : gasm_(gasm),
304  initial_value_(initial_value),
305  cond_(cond),
306  step_(step),
307  initial_arg0_(initial_arg0) {}
308 
309  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT ForBuilder1& Do(const For1BodyFunction& body) {
310  body_ = body;
311  return *this;
312  }
313 
314  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT TNode<Object> Value() {
315  DCHECK(body_);
316  TNode<Object> arg0 = initial_arg0_;
317 
318  auto loop_exit = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel(kPhiRepresentation);
319 
320  {
321  GraphAssembler::LoopScope<kPhiRepresentation, kPhiRepresentation>
322  loop_scope(gasm_);
323 
324  auto loop_header = loop_scope.loop_header_label();
325  auto loop_body = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel(kPhiRepresentation);
326 
327  gasm_->Goto(loop_header, initial_value_, initial_arg0_);
328 
329  gasm_->Bind(loop_header);
330  TNode<Number> i = loop_header->PhiAt<Number>(0);
331  arg0 = loop_header->PhiAt<Object>(1);
332 
333  gasm_->BranchWithHint(cond_(i), &loop_body, &loop_exit,
334  BranchHint::kTrue, arg0);
335 
336  gasm_->Bind(&loop_body);
337  body_(i, &arg0);
338  gasm_->Goto(loop_header, step_(i), arg0);
339  }
340 
341  gasm_->Bind(&loop_exit);
342  return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(loop_exit.PhiAt<Object>(0));
343  }
344 
345  void ValueIsUnused() { USE(Value()); }
346 
347  private:
348  static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
349  MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
350 
351  JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
352  const TNode<Number> initial_value_;
353  const ConditionFunction1 cond_;
354  const StepFunction1 step_;
355  For1BodyFunction body_;
356  const TNode<Object> initial_arg0_;
357  };
358 
359  ForBuilder1 For1(TNode<Number> initial_value, const ConditionFunction1& cond,
360  const StepFunction1& step, TNode<Object> initial_arg0) {
361  return {this, initial_value, cond, step, initial_arg0};
362  }
363 
364  ForBuilder1 For1ZeroUntil(TNode<Number> excluded_limit,
365  TNode<Object> initial_arg0) {
366  TNode<Number> initial_value = ZeroConstant();
367  auto cond = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
368  return NumberLessThan(i, excluded_limit);
369  };
370  auto step = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
371  return NumberAdd(i, OneConstant());
372  };
373  return {this, initial_value, cond, step, initial_arg0};
374  }

376  void ThrowIfNotCallable(TNode<Object> maybe_callable,
377  FrameState frame_state) {
378  IfNot(ObjectIsCallable(maybe_callable))
379  .Then(_ {
380  JSCallRuntime1(Runtime::kThrowCalledNonCallable, maybe_callable,
381  ContextInput(), frame_state);
382  Unreachable(); // The runtime call throws unconditionally.
383  })
384  .ExpectTrue();
385  }

449  const bool has_stability_dependency,
450  ElementsKind kind,
451  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared);
452  TNode<Object> ReduceArrayPrototypeReduce(MapInference* inference,
453  const bool has_stability_dependency,
454  ElementsKind kind,
455  ArrayReduceDirection direction,
456  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared);

458  const bool has_stability_dependency,
459  ElementsKind kind,
460  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
461  NativeContextRef native_context);

463  const bool has_stability_dependency,
464  ElementsKind kind,
465  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
466  NativeContextRef native_context);

468  const bool has_stability_dependency,
469  ElementsKind kind,
470  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
471  NativeContextRef native_context,
472  ArrayFindVariant variant);
473  TNode<Boolean> ReduceArrayPrototypeEverySome(
474  MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
475  ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
476  NativeContextRef native_context, ArrayEverySomeVariant variant);
477  TNode<Object> ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(ZoneVector<MapRef> kinds,
478  bool needs_fallback_builtin_call);
479  TNode<Object> ReduceArrayPrototypeIndexOfIncludes(
480  ElementsKind kind, ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant variant);
481  TNode<Number> ReduceArrayPrototypePush(MapInference* inference);
482 
483  private:
484  // Returns {index,value}. Assumes that the map has not changed, but possibly
485  // the length and backing store.
486  std::pair<TNode<Number>, TNode<Object>> SafeLoadElement(ElementsKind kind,
487  TNode<JSArray> o,
488  TNode<Number> index) {
489  // Make sure that the access is still in bounds, since the callback could
490  // have changed the array's size.
491  TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(o, kind);
492  index = CheckBounds(index, length);
493 
494  // Reload the elements pointer before calling the callback, since the
495  // previous callback might have resized the array causing the elements
496  // buffer to be re-allocated.
497  TNode<HeapObject> elements =
498  LoadField<HeapObject>(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), o);
499  TNode<Object> value = LoadElement<Object>(
500  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind), elements, index);
501  return std::make_pair(index, value);
502  }
503 
504  template <typename... Vars>
505  TNode<Object> MaybeSkipHole(
506  TNode<Object> o, ElementsKind kind,
507  GraphAssemblerLabel<sizeof...(Vars)>* continue_label,
508  TNode<Vars>... vars) {
509  if (!IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) return o;
510 
511  auto if_not_hole = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentationOf<Vars>::value...);
512  BranchWithHint(HoleCheck(kind, o), continue_label, &if_not_hole,
513  BranchHint::kFalse, vars...);
514 
515  // The contract is that we don't leak "the hole" into "user JavaScript",
516  // so we must rename the {element} here to explicitly exclude "the hole"
517  // from the type of {element}.
518  Bind(&if_not_hole);
519  return TypeGuardNonInternal(o);
520  }
521 
522  TNode<Smi> LoadJSArrayLength(TNode<JSArray> array, ElementsKind kind) {
523  return LoadField<Smi>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), array);
524  }
525  void StoreJSArrayLength(TNode<JSArray> array, TNode<Number> value,
526  ElementsKind kind) {
527  StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), array, value);
528  }
529  void StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(TNode<FixedArrayBase> o, TNode<Number> index,
530  TNode<Object> v, ElementsKind kind) {
531  StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind), o, index, v);
532  }
533 
534  TNode<FixedArrayBase> LoadElements(TNode<JSObject> o) {
535  return LoadField<FixedArrayBase>(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), o);
536  }
537  TNode<Smi> LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(TNode<FixedArrayBase> o) {
538  return LoadField<Smi>(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength(), o);
539  }
540 
541  TNode<Boolean> HoleCheck(ElementsKind kind, TNode<Object> v) {
542  return IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)
543  ? NumberIsFloat64Hole(TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(v))
544  : IsTheHole(v);
545  }
546 };

590  TNode<JSFunction> CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
591  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, TNode<Context> context) {
592  DCHECK(shared.HasBuiltinId());
593  Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell =
594  isolate()->factory()->many_closures_cell();
595  Callable const callable =
596  Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), shared.builtin_id());
597  CodeRef code = MakeRef(broker(), *callable.code());
598  return AddNode<JSFunction>(graph()->NewNode(
599  javascript()->CreateClosure(shared, code), HeapConstant(feedback_cell),
600  context, effect(), control()));
601  }

603  void CallPromiseExecutor(TNode<Object> executor, TNode<JSFunction> resolve,
604  TNode<JSFunction> reject, FrameState frame_state) {
605  JSConstructNode n(node_ptr());
606  const ConstructParameters& p = n.Parameters();
607  FeedbackSource no_feedback_source{};
608  Node* no_feedback = UndefinedConstant();
609  MayThrow(_ {
610  return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
611  javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(2), p.frequency(),
612  no_feedback_source,
613  ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined),
614  executor, UndefinedConstant(), resolve, reject, no_feedback,
615  n.context(), frame_state, effect(), control()));
616  });
617  }
618 
619  void CallPromiseReject(TNode<JSFunction> reject, TNode<Object> exception,
620  FrameState frame_state) {
621  JSConstructNode n(node_ptr());
622  const ConstructParameters& p = n.Parameters();
623  FeedbackSource no_feedback_source{};
624  Node* no_feedback = UndefinedConstant();
625  MayThrow(_ {
626  return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
627  javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1), p.frequency(),
628  no_feedback_source,
629  ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined),
630  reject, UndefinedConstant(), exception, no_feedback, n.context(),
631  frame_state, effect(), control()));
632  });
633  }
634 };
635 
636 class FastApiCallReducerAssembler : public JSCallReducerAssembler {
637  public:
638  FastApiCallReducerAssembler(
639  JSCallReducer* reducer, Node* node,
640  const FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info,
641  FastApiCallFunction c_function, Node* receiver,
642  const SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* target, const int arity,
643  Node* effect)
644  : JSCallReducerAssembler(reducer, node),
645  c_function_(c_function),
646  function_template_info_(function_template_info),
647  receiver_(receiver),
648  shared_(shared),
649  target_(target),
650  arity_(arity) {
651  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode());
652  InitializeEffectControl(effect, NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node));
653  }
654 
655  TNode<Object> ReduceFastApiCall() {
656  JSCallNode n(node_ptr());
657 
658  // C arguments include the receiver at index 0. Thus C index 1 corresponds
659  // to the JS argument 0, etc.
660  // All functions in c_candidate_functions_ have the same number of
661  // arguments, so extract c_argument_count from the first function.
662  const int c_argument_count =
663  static_cast<int>(c_function_.signature->ArgumentCount());
664  CHECK_GE(c_argument_count, kReceiver);
665 
666  const int slow_arg_count =
667  // Arguments for CallApiCallbackOptimizedXXX builtin including
668  // context, see CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor.
669  kSlowBuiltinParams +
670  // JS arguments.
671  kReceiver + arity_;
672 
673  const int value_input_count =
674  FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_argument_count, slow_arg_count);
675 
676  base::SmallVector<Node*, kInlineSize> inputs(value_input_count +
677  kEffectAndControl);
678  int cursor = 0;
679  inputs[cursor++] = n.receiver();
680 
681  // TODO(turbofan): Consider refactoring CFunctionInfo to distinguish
682  // between receiver and arguments, simplifying this (and related) spots.
683  int js_args_count = c_argument_count - kReceiver;
684  for (int i = 0; i < js_args_count; ++i) {
685  if (i < n.ArgumentCount()) {
686  inputs[cursor++] = n.Argument(i);
687  } else {
688  inputs[cursor++] = UndefinedConstant();
689  }
690  }
691 
692  // Here we add the arguments for the slow call, which will be
693  // reconstructed at a later phase. Those are effectively the same
694  // arguments as for the fast call, but we want to have them as
695  // separate inputs, so that SimplifiedLowering can provide the best
696  // possible UseInfos for each of them. The inputs to FastApiCall
697  // look like:
698  // [receiver, ... C arguments, callback data,
699  // slow call code, external constant for function, argc,
700  // FunctionTemplateInfo, holder, receiver, ... JS arguments,
701  // context, new frame state].
702  bool no_profiling =
703  broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoProfilingProtector();
704  Callable call_api_callback = Builtins::CallableFor(
705  isolate(), no_profiling ? Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling
706  : Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized);
707  CallInterfaceDescriptor cid = call_api_callback.descriptor();
708  DCHECK_EQ(cid.GetParameterCount() + (cid.HasContextParameter() ? 1 : 0),
709  kSlowBuiltinParams);
710 
711  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
712  Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(graph()->zone(), cid, arity_ + kReceiver,
713  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
714  ApiFunction api_function(function_template_info_.callback(broker()));
715  ExternalReference function_reference = ExternalReference::Create(
716  isolate(), &api_function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL,
717  function_template_info_.c_functions(broker()).data(),
718  function_template_info_.c_signatures(broker()).data(),
719  static_cast<unsigned>(
720  function_template_info_.c_functions(broker()).size()));
721 
722  // LINT.IfChange
723  // TODO(crbug.com/418936518): Support deopt for functions with return value.
724  Node* error_message = jsgraph()->SmiConstant(
725  static_cast<int>(AbortReason::kUnsupportedDeopt));
726  Node* continuation_frame_state =
727  c_function_.signature->ReturnInfo().GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid
728  ? CreateInlinedApiFunctionFrameState(jsgraph(), shared_, target_,
729  ContextInput(), receiver_,
730  FrameStateInput())
731  : CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
732  jsgraph(), Builtin::kAbort, ContextInput(), &error_message, 1,
733  FrameStateInput(), ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
734  // The `DeoptimizationEntry_LazyAfterFastCall` builtin currently sets the
735  // return value unconditionally to `undefined`. If a continuation builtin is
736  // set up here, then the entry builtin should not overwrite the return
737  // value.
738  // LINT.ThenChange(/src/builtins/x64/builtins-x64.cc:DeoptAfterFastCallSetReturnValue)
739 
740  // Callback data value for fast Api calls. Unlike slow Api calls, the fast
741  // variant passes callback data directly.
742  inputs[cursor++] =
743  Constant(function_template_info_.callback_data(broker()).value());
744 
745  inputs[cursor++] = HeapConstant(call_api_callback.code());
746  inputs[cursor++] = ExternalConstant(function_reference);
747  inputs[cursor++] = NumberConstant(arity_);
748  inputs[cursor++] = HeapConstant(function_template_info_.object());
749  inputs[cursor++] = receiver_;
750  for (int i = 0; i < arity_; ++i) {
751  inputs[cursor++] = Argument(i);
752  }
753  inputs[cursor++] = ContextInput();
754  inputs[cursor++] = continuation_frame_state;
755 
756  inputs[cursor++] = effect();
757  inputs[cursor++] = control();
758 
759  DCHECK_EQ(cursor, value_input_count + kEffectAndControl);
760 
761  return FastApiCall(call_descriptor, inputs.begin(), inputs.size());
762  }
763 
764  private:
765  static constexpr int kEffectAndControl = 2;
766 
767  // Api function address, argc, FunctionTemplateInfo, context.
768  // See CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor.
769  static constexpr int kSlowBuiltinParams = 4;
770  static constexpr int kReceiver = 1;
771 
772  // Enough for creating FastApiCall node with two JS arguments.
773  static constexpr int kInlineSize = 16;
774 
775  TNode<Object> FastApiCall(CallDescriptor* descriptor, Node** inputs,
776  size_t inputs_size) {
777  return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
778  simplified()->FastApiCall(c_function_, feedback(), descriptor),
779  static_cast<int>(inputs_size), inputs));
780  }
781 
782  FastApiCallFunction c_function_;
783  const FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info_;
784  Node* const receiver_;
785  const SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_;
786  Node* const target_;
787  const int arity_;
788 };

900 TNode<JSArray> JSCallReducerAssembler::AllocateEmptyJSArray(
901  ElementsKind kind, NativeContextRef native_context) {
902  // TODO(jgruber): Port AllocationBuilder to JSGraphAssembler.
903  MapRef map = native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), kind);
904 
905  AllocationBuilder ab(jsgraph(), broker(), effect(), control());
906  ab.Allocate(map.instance_size(), AllocationType::kYoung, Type::Array());
907  ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), map);
908  Node* empty_fixed_array = jsgraph()->EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
909  ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer(),
910  empty_fixed_array);
911  ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), empty_fixed_array);
912  ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
913  for (int i = 0; i < map.GetInObjectProperties(); ++i) {
914  ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectInObjectProperty(map, i),
915  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
916  }
917  Node* result = ab.Finish();
918  InitializeEffectControl(result, control());
919  return TNode<JSArray>::UncheckedCast(result);
920 }

922 TNode<Number> JSCallReducerAssembler::LoadMapElementsKind(TNode<Map> map) {
923  TNode<Number> bit_field2 =
924  LoadField<Number>(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2(), map);
925  return NumberShiftRightLogical(
926  NumberBitwiseAnd(bit_field2,
927  NumberConstant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
928  NumberConstant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
929 }

931 TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceMathUnary(const Operator* op) {
932  TNode<Object> input = Argument(0);
933  TNode<Number> input_as_number = SpeculativeToNumber(input);
934  return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(graph()->NewNode(op, input_as_number));
935 }

937 TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceMathBinary(const Operator* op) {
938  TNode<Object> left = Argument(0);
939  TNode<Object> right = ArgumentOrNaN(1);
940  TNode<Number> left_number = SpeculativeToNumber(left);
941  TNode<Number> right_number = SpeculativeToNumber(right);
942  return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(
943  graph()->NewNode(op, left_number, right_number));
944 }

946 TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstring() {
947  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
948  TNode<Object> start = Argument(0);
949  TNode<Object> end = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
950 
951  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
952  TNode<Number> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
953 
954  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
955 
956  TNode<Number> end_smi = SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end))
957  .Then(_ { return length; })
958  .Else(_ { return CheckSmi(end); })
959  .ExpectFalse()
960  .Value();
961 
962  TNode<Number> zero = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(ZeroConstant());
963  TNode<Number> finalStart = NumberMin(NumberMax(start_smi, zero), length);
964  TNode<Number> finalEnd = NumberMin(NumberMax(end_smi, zero), length);
965  TNode<Number> from = NumberMin(finalStart, finalEnd);
966  TNode<Number> to = NumberMax(finalStart, finalEnd);
967 
968  return StringSubstring(receiver_string, from, to);
969 }
970 
971 TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith(
972  StringRef search_element_string) {
973  DCHECK(search_element_string.IsContentAccessible());
974  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
975  TNode<Object> start = ArgumentOrZero(1);
976 
977  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
978  TNode<Smi> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
979  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
980 
981  TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
982  TNode<Number> clamped_start = NumberMin(NumberMax(start_smi, zero), length);
983 
984  int search_string_length = search_element_string.length();
985  DCHECK(search_string_length <= JSCallReducer::kMaxInlineMatchSequence);
986 
987  auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
988 
989  auto search_string_too_long =
990  NumberLessThan(NumberSubtract(length, clamped_start),
991  NumberConstant(search_string_length));
992 
993  GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
994 
995  static_assert(String::kMaxLength <= kSmiMaxValue);
996 
997  for (int i = 0; i < search_string_length; i++) {
998  TNode<Number> k = NumberConstant(i);
999  TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1000  TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, clamped_start)));
1001  Node* receiver_string_char =
1002  StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
1003  Node* search_string_char = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
1004  search_element_string.GetChar(broker(), i).value());
1005  auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
1006  search_string_char, receiver_string_char);
1007  GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
1008  }
1009 
1010  Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
1011 
1012  Bind(&out);
1013  return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1014 }
1015 
1016 TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith() {
1017  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1018  TNode<Object> search_element = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1019  TNode<Object> start = ArgumentOrZero(1);
1020 
1021  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1022  TNode<String> search_string = CheckString(search_element);
1023  TNode<Smi> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
1024  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1025 
1026  TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1027  TNode<Number> clamped_start = NumberMin(NumberMax(start_smi, zero), length);
1028 
1029  TNode<Number> search_string_length = StringLength(search_string);
1030 
1031  auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1032 
1033  auto search_string_too_long = NumberLessThan(
1034  NumberSubtract(length, clamped_start), search_string_length);
1035 
1036  GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
1037 
1038  static_assert(String::kMaxLength <= kSmiMaxValue);
1039 
1040  ForZeroUntil(search_string_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1041  TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1042  TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, clamped_start)));
1043  Node* receiver_string_char =
1044  StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
1045  if (!v8_flags.turbo_loop_variable) {
1046  // Without loop variable analysis, Turbofan's typer is unable to derive a
1047  // sufficiently precise type here. This is not a soundness problem, but
1048  // triggers graph verification errors. So we only insert the TypeGuard if
1049  // necessary.
1050  k = TypeGuard(Type::Unsigned32(), k);
1051  }
1052  Node* search_string_char = StringCharCodeAt(search_string, k);
1053  auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
1054  receiver_string_char, search_string_char);
1055  GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
1056  });
1057 
1058  Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
1059 
1060  Bind(&out);
1061  return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1062 }
1063 
1064 TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeEndsWith(
1065  StringRef search_element_string) {
1066  DCHECK(search_element_string.IsContentAccessible());
1067  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1068  TNode<Object> end_position = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1069  TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1070 
1071  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1072  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1073  int search_string_length = search_element_string.length();
1074  DCHECK_LE(search_string_length, JSCallReducer::kMaxInlineMatchSequence);
1075 
1076  TNode<Number> clamped_end =
1077  SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end_position))
1078  .Then(_ { return length; })
1079  .Else(_ {
1080  return NumberMin(NumberMax(CheckSmi(end_position), zero), length);
1081  })
1082  .ExpectTrue()
1083  .Value();
1084 
1085  TNode<Number> start =
1086  NumberSubtract(clamped_end, NumberConstant(search_string_length));
1087 
1088  auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1089 
1090  TNode<Boolean> search_string_too_long = NumberLessThan(start, zero);
1091  GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
1092 
1093  for (int i = 0; i < search_string_length; i++) {
1094  TNode<Number> k = NumberConstant(i);
1095  TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1096  TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, start)));
1097  Node* receiver_string_char =
1098  StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
1099  Node* search_string_char = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
1100  search_element_string.GetChar(broker(), i).value());
1101  auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
1102  receiver_string_char, search_string_char);
1103  GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
1104  }
1105 
1106  Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
1107 
1108  Bind(&out);
1109  return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1110 }
1111 
1112 TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeEndsWith() {
1113  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1114  TNode<Object> search_string = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1115  TNode<Object> end_position = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1116  TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1117 
1118  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1119  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1120  TNode<String> search_element_string = CheckString(search_string);
1121  TNode<Number> search_string_length = StringLength(search_element_string);
1122 
1123  TNode<Number> clamped_end =
1124  SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end_position))
1125  .Then(_ { return length; })
1126  .Else(_ {
1127  return NumberMin(NumberMax(CheckSmi(end_position), zero), length);
1128  })
1129  .ExpectTrue()
1130  .Value();
1131 
1132  TNode<Number> start = NumberSubtract(clamped_end, search_string_length);
1133 
1134  auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1135 
1136  TNode<Boolean> search_string_too_long = NumberLessThan(start, zero);
1137  GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
1138 
1139  ForZeroUntil(search_string_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1140  TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1141  TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, start)));
1142  Node* receiver_string_char =
1143  StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
1144  if (!v8_flags.turbo_loop_variable) {
1145  // Without loop variable analysis, Turbofan's typer is unable to derive a
1146  // sufficiently precise type here. This is not a soundness problem, but
1147  // triggers graph verification errors. So we only insert the TypeGuard if
1148  // necessary.
1149  k = TypeGuard(Type::Unsigned32(), k);
1150  }
1151  Node* search_string_char = StringCharCodeAt(search_element_string, k);
1152  auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
1153  receiver_string_char, search_string_char);
1154  GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
1155  });
1156 
1157  Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
1158 
1159  Bind(&out);
1160  return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1161 }
1162 
1163 TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(
1164  StringRef s, uint32_t index) {
1165  DCHECK(s.IsContentAccessible());
1166  if (s.IsOneByteRepresentation()) {
1167  OptionalObjectRef elem = s.GetCharAsStringOrUndefined(broker(), index);
1168  TNode<String> elem_string =
1169  elem.has_value()
1170  ? TNode<String>::UncheckedCast(
1171  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(elem.value(), broker()))
1172  : EmptyStringConstant();
1173  return elem_string;
1174  } else {
1175  const uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(s.length());
1176  if (index >= length) return EmptyStringConstant();
1177  Handle<SeqTwoByteString> flat = broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
1178  broker()
1179  ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
1180  ->factory()
1181  ->NewRawTwoByteString(1, AllocationType::kOld)
1182  .ToHandleChecked());
1183  flat->SeqTwoByteStringSet(0, s.GetChar(broker(), index).value());
1184  TNode<String> two_byte_elem =
1185  TNode<String>::UncheckedCast(jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(flat));
1186  return two_byte_elem;
1187  }
1188 }
1189 
1190 TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(
1191  SpeculationMode speculation_mode) {
1192  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1193  TNode<Object> index = ArgumentOrZero(0);
1194 
1195  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1196  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1197 
1198  if (speculation_mode == SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation) {
1199  TNode<Number> index_smi = CheckSmi(index);
1200  return SelectIf<String>(NumberLessThan(index_smi, ZeroConstant()))
1201  .Then(_ { return EmptyStringConstant(); })
1202  .Else(_ {
1203  return SelectIf<String>(NumberLessThan(index_smi, length))
1204  .Then(_ {
1205  return StringFromSingleCharCode(
1206  TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(StringCharCodeAt(
1207  receiver_string,
1208  TypeGuard(Type::Unsigned32(), index_smi))));
1209  })
1210  .Else(_ { return EmptyStringConstant(); })
1211  .ExpectTrue()
1212  .Value();
1213  })
1214  .ExpectFalse()
1215  .Value();
1216  }
1217 
1218  DCHECK_EQ(speculation_mode, SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation);
1219  TNode<Number> bounded_index = CheckBounds(index, length);
1220  return StringFromSingleCharCode(TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1221  StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, bounded_index)));
1222 }

1224 TNode<Number> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeCharCodeAt(
1225  SpeculationMode speculation_mode) {
1226  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1227  TNode<Object> index = ArgumentOrZero(0);
1228 
1229  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1230  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1231 
1232  if (speculation_mode == SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation) {
1233  TNode<Number> index_smi = CheckSmi(index);
1234  return SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(index_smi, ZeroConstant()))
1235  .Then(_ { return NaNConstant(); })
1236  .Else(_ {
1237  return SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(index_smi, length))
1238  .Then(_ {
1239  return TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(StringCharCodeAt(
1240  receiver_string, TypeGuard(Type::Unsigned32(), index_smi)));
1241  })
1242  .Else(_ { return NaNConstant(); })
1243  .ExpectTrue()
1244  .Value();
1245  })
1246  .ExpectFalse()
1247  .Value();
1248  }
1249  DCHECK_EQ(speculation_mode, SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation);
1250 
1251  TNode<Number> bounded_index = CheckBounds(index, length);
1252  return TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1253  (StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, bounded_index)));
1254 }
1255 
1256 TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeSlice() {
1257  TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1258  TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1259 
1260  TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1261 
1262  TNode<Object> start = Argument(0);
1263  TNode<Object> end = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1264 
1265  // Special case str.slice(-1) to str.charAt(str.length - 1).
1266  // This will not hit if the start offset is not known to be the -1 constant
1267  // during this reduction, nor if the end argument is explicitly rather than
1268  // implicitly undefined; hopefully in common cases the code will explicitly
1269  // use the -1 literal.
1270  if (ArgumentCount() == 1) {
1271  NumberMatcher m(start);
1272  if (m.Is(-1)) {
1273  return SelectIf<String>(
1274  ReferenceEqual(receiver_string, EmptyStringConstant()))
1275  .Then(_ { return EmptyStringConstant(); })
1276  .Else(_ {
1277  return StringFromSingleCharCode(
1278  TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(StringCharCodeAt(
1279  receiver_string,
1280  TypeGuard(Type::Unsigned32(),
1281  NumberAdd(length, TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1282  m.node()))))));
1283  })
1284  .Value();
1285  }
1286  }
1287 
1288  TNode<Number> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
1289  TNode<Number> end_smi = SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end))
1290  .Then(_ { return length; })
1291  .Else(_ { return CheckSmi(end); })
1292  .ExpectFalse()
1293  .Value();
1294 
1295  TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1296  TNode<Number> from_untyped =
1297  SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(start_smi, zero))
1298  .Then(_ { return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, start_smi), zero); })
1299  .Else(_ { return NumberMin(start_smi, length); })
1300  .ExpectFalse()
1301  .Value();
1302  // {from} is always in non-negative Smi range, but our typer cannot figure
1303  // that out yet.
1304  TNode<Smi> from = TypeGuardUnsignedSmall(from_untyped);
1305 
1306  TNode<Number> to_untyped =
1307  SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(end_smi, zero))
1308  .Then(_ { return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, end_smi), zero); })
1309  .Else(_ { return NumberMin(end_smi, length); })
1310  .ExpectFalse()
1311  .Value();
1312  // {to} is always in non-negative Smi range, but our typer cannot figure that
1313  // out yet.
1314  TNode<Smi> to = TypeGuardUnsignedSmall(to_untyped);
1315 
1316  return SelectIf<String>(NumberLessThan(from, to))
1317  .Then(_ { return StringSubstring(receiver_string, from, to); })
1318  .Else(_ { return EmptyStringConstant(); })
1319  .ExpectTrue()
1320  .Value();
1321 }
1322 
1323 TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(
1324  Builtin builtin) {
1325  JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node_ptr());
1326  TNode<Object> arguments_list = n.Argument(0);
1327 
1328  auto call_builtin = MakeLabel();
1329  auto done = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1330 
1331  // Check if {arguments_list} is a JSArray.
1332  GotoIf(ObjectIsSmi(arguments_list), &call_builtin);
1333  TNode<Map> arguments_list_map =
1334  LoadField<Map>(AccessBuilder::ForMap(),
1335  TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(arguments_list));
1336  TNode<Number> arguments_list_instance_type = LoadField<Number>(
1337  AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), arguments_list_map);
1338  auto check_instance_type =
1339  NumberEqual(arguments_list_instance_type, NumberConstant(JS_ARRAY_TYPE));
1340  GotoIfNot(check_instance_type, &call_builtin);
1341 
1342  // Check if {arguments_list} has PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
1343  TNode<Number> arguments_list_elements_kind =
1344  LoadMapElementsKind(arguments_list_map);
1345 
1346  auto check_element_kind = NumberEqual(arguments_list_elements_kind,
1347  NumberConstant(PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS));
1348  GotoIfNot(check_element_kind, &call_builtin);
1349 
1350  // If {arguments_list} is a JSArray with PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, calculate the
1351  // result with inlined loop.
1352  TNode<JSArray> array_arguments_list =
1353  TNode<JSArray>::UncheckedCast(arguments_list);
1354  Goto(&done, builtin == Builtin::kMathMax
1355  ? DoubleArrayMax(array_arguments_list)
1356  : DoubleArrayMin(array_arguments_list));
1357 
1358  // Otherwise, call BuiltinMathMin/Max as usual.
1359  Bind(&call_builtin);
1360  TNode<Object> call = CopyNode();
1361  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1362 
1363  // Set SpeculationMode to kDisallowSpeculation to avoid infinite
1364  // recursion.
1365  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
1366  call, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(
1367  p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
1368  SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, p.feedback_relation()));
1369  Goto(&done, call);
1370 
1371  Bind(&done);
1372  return done.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1373 }
1374 
1375 TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(
1376  ZoneVector<MapRef> maps, bool needs_fallback_builtin_call) {
1377  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1378  TNode<Object> index = ArgumentOrZero(0);
1379 
1380  TNode<Number> index_num = CheckSmi(index);
1381  TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(receiver);
1382 
1383  TNode<Map> receiver_map =
1384  TNode<Map>::UncheckedCast(LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), receiver));
1385 
1386  auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1387 
1388  for (MapRef map : maps) {
1389  DCHECK(map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker()));
1390  auto correct_map_label = MakeLabel(), wrong_map_label = MakeLabel();
1391  TNode<Boolean> is_map_equal = ReferenceEqual(receiver_map, Constant(map));
1392  Branch(is_map_equal, &correct_map_label, &wrong_map_label);
1393  Bind(&correct_map_label);
1394 
1395  TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, map.elements_kind());
1396 
1397  // If index is less than 0, then subtract from length.
1398  TNode<Boolean> cond = NumberLessThan(index_num, ZeroConstant());
1399  TNode<Number> real_index_num =
1400  SelectIf<Number>(cond)
1401  .Then(_ { return NumberAdd(length, index_num); })
1402  .Else(_ { return index_num; })
1403  .ExpectTrue() // Most common usage should be .at(-1)
1404  .Value();
1405 
1406  // Bound checking.
1407  GotoIf(NumberLessThan(real_index_num, ZeroConstant()), &out,
1408  UndefinedConstant());
1409  GotoIfNot(NumberLessThan(real_index_num, length), &out,
1410  UndefinedConstant());
1411  if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
1412  real_index_num = CheckBounds(real_index_num, length,
1413  CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds);
1414  }
1415 
1416  // Retrieving element at index.
1417  TNode<Object> element = LoadElement<Object>(
1418  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(map.elements_kind()), elements,
1419  real_index_num);
1420  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(map.elements_kind())) {
1421  // This case is needed in particular for HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: raw
1422  // doubles are stored in the FixedDoubleArray, and need to be converted to
1423  // HeapNumber or to Smi so that this function can return an Object. The
1424  // automatic converstion performed by
1425  // RepresentationChanger::GetTaggedRepresentationFor does not handle
1426  // holes, so we convert manually a potential hole here.
1427  element = ConvertHoleToUndefined(element, map.elements_kind());
1428  }
1429  Goto(&out, element);
1430 
1431  Bind(&wrong_map_label);
1432  }
1433 
1434  if (needs_fallback_builtin_call) {
1435  JSCallNode n(node_ptr());
1436  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1437 
1438  // We set SpeculationMode to kDisallowSpeculation to avoid infinite
1439  // recursion on the node we're creating (since, after all, it's calling
1440  // Array.Prototype.at).
1441  const Operator* op = javascript()->Call(
1442  JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
1443  ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined,
1444  SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget);
1445  Node* fallback_builtin = node_ptr()->InputAt(0);
1446 
1447  TNode<Object> res = MayThrow(_ {
1448  return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
1449  op, fallback_builtin, receiver, index, n.feedback_vector(),
1450  ContextInput(), n.frame_state(), effect(), control()));
1451  });
1452  Goto(&out, res);
1453  } else {
1454  Goto(&out, UndefinedConstant());
1455  }
1456 
1457  Bind(&out);
1458  return out.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1459 }
1460 
1461 TNode<Number> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypePush(
1462  MapInference* inference) {
1463  int const num_push_arguments = ArgumentCount();
1464  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference->GetMaps();
1465 
1466  base::SmallVector<MachineRepresentation, 4> argument_reps;
1467  base::SmallVector<Node*, 4> argument_nodes;
1468 
1469  for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1470  argument_reps.push_back(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1471  argument_nodes.push_back(Argument(i));
1472  }
1473 
1474  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1475  TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadMap(receiver);
1476 
1477  auto double_label = MakeLabel(argument_reps);
1478  auto smi_label = MakeLabel(argument_reps);
1479  auto object_label = MakeLabel(argument_reps);
1480 
1481  for (size_t i = 0; i < receiver_maps.size(); i++) {
1482  MapRef map = receiver_maps[i];
1483  ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
1484 
1485  if (i < receiver_maps.size() - 1) {
1486  TNode<Boolean> is_map_equal = ReferenceEqual(receiver_map, Constant(map));
1487  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
1488  GotoIf(is_map_equal, &double_label, argument_nodes);
1489  } else if (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) {
1490  GotoIf(is_map_equal, &smi_label, argument_nodes);
1491  } else {
1492  GotoIf(is_map_equal, &object_label, argument_nodes);
1493  }
1494  } else {
1495  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
1496  Goto(&double_label, argument_nodes);
1497  } else if (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) {
1498  Goto(&smi_label, argument_nodes);
1499  } else {
1500  Goto(&object_label, argument_nodes);
1501  }
1502  }
1503  }
1504 
1505  auto return_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1506 
1507  auto build_array_push = [&](ElementsKind kind,
1508  base::SmallVector<Node*, 1>& push_arguments) {
1509  // Only support PACKED_ELEMENTS and PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, as "markers" of
1510  // what the elements array is (a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray).
1511  DCHECK(kind == PACKED_ELEMENTS || kind == PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
1512 
1513  // Load the "length" property of the {receiver}.
1514  TNode<Smi> length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1515  TNode<Number> return_value = length;
1516 
1517  // Check if we have any {values} to push.
1518  if (num_push_arguments > 0) {
1519  // Compute the resulting "length" of the {receiver}.
1520  TNode<Number> new_length = return_value =
1521  NumberAdd(length, NumberConstant(num_push_arguments));
1522 
1523  // Load the elements backing store of the {receiver}.
1524  TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(receiver);
1525  TNode<Smi> elements_length = LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(elements);
1526 
1527  elements = MaybeGrowFastElements(
1528  kind, feedback(), receiver, elements,
1529  NumberAdd(length, NumberConstant(num_push_arguments - 1)),
1530  elements_length);
1531 
1532  // Update the JSArray::length field. Since this is observable,
1533  // there must be no other check after this.
1534  StoreJSArrayLength(receiver, new_length, kind);
1535 
1536  // Append the {values} to the {elements}.
1537  for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1538  StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(
1539  elements, NumberAdd(length, NumberConstant(i)),
1540  TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(push_arguments[i]), kind);
1541  }
1542  }
1543 
1544  Goto(&return_label, return_value);
1545  };
1546 
1547  if (double_label.IsUsed()) {
1548  Bind(&double_label);
1549  base::SmallVector<Node*, 1> push_arguments(num_push_arguments);
1550  for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1551  Node* value =
1552  CheckNumber(TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(double_label.PhiAt(i)));
1553  // Make sure we do not store signaling NaNs into double arrays.
1554  value = AddNode<Number>(
1555  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSilenceNaN(), value));
1556  push_arguments[i] = value;
1557  }
1558  build_array_push(PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, push_arguments);
1559  }
1560 
1561  if (smi_label.IsUsed()) {
1562  Bind(&smi_label);
1563  base::SmallVector<Node*, 4> push_arguments(num_push_arguments);
1564  for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1565  Node* value = CheckSmi(TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(smi_label.PhiAt(i)));
1566  push_arguments[i] = value;
1567  }
1568  Goto(&object_label, push_arguments);
1569  }
1570 
1571  if (object_label.IsUsed()) {
1572  Bind(&object_label);
1573  base::SmallVector<Node*, 1> push_arguments(num_push_arguments);
1574  for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1575  push_arguments[i] = object_label.PhiAt(i);
1576  }
1577  build_array_push(PACKED_ELEMENTS, push_arguments);
1578  }
1579 
1580  Bind(&return_label);
1581  return TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(return_label.PhiAt(0));
1582 }

1598 FrameState ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(const ForEachFrameStateParams& params,
1599  TNode<Object> k) {
1600  Builtin builtin = Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation;
1601  Node* checkpoint_params[] = {params.receiver, params.callback,
1602  params.this_arg, k, params.original_length};
1603  return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1604  params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,
1605  checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params), params.outer_frame_state,
1606  ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
1607 }

1612  Node* checkpoint_params[] = {params.receiver, params.callback,
1613  params.this_arg, k, params.original_length};
1614  return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1615  params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,

1621 
1622 TNode<Object>
1623 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeForEach(
1624  MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1625  ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
1626  FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1627  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1628  TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1629  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1630  TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1631  TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1632 
1633  TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1634 
1635  ForEachFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1636  jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1637  receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
1638 
1639  ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback, ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
1640  ZeroConstant()));
1641 
1642  ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1643  Checkpoint(ForEachLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1644 
1645  // Deopt if the map has changed during the iteration.
1646  MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1647 
1648  TNode<Object> element;
1649  std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1650 
1651  auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1652  element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
1653 
1654  TNode<Number> next_k = NumberAdd(k, OneConstant());
1655  JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1656  ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, next_k));
1657 
1658  Goto(&continue_label);
1659  Bind(&continue_label);
1660  });
1661 
1662  return UndefinedConstant();
1663 }

1719 FrameState ReduceLoopEagerFrameState(const ReduceFrameStateParams& params,
1720  TNode<Object> receiver,
1721  TNode<Object> callback, TNode<Object> k,
1722  TNode<Number> original_length,
1723  TNode<Object> accumulator) {

1727  Node* checkpoint_params[] = {receiver, callback, k, original_length,
1728  accumulator};
1729  return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1730  params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,
1731  checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params), params.outer_frame_state,
1732  ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER);
1733 }
1734 
1735 } // namespace
1736 
1737 TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeReduce(
1738  MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1739  ElementsKind kind, ArrayReduceDirection direction,
1740  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
1741  FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1742  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1743  TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1744  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1745  TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1746 
1747  ReduceFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1748  jsgraph(), shared, direction, context, target, outer_frame_state};
1749 
1750  TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1751 
1752  // Set up variable behavior depending on the reduction kind (left/right).
1753  TNode<Number> k;
1754  StepFunction1 step;
1755  ConditionFunction1 cond;
1756  TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1757  TNode<Number> one = OneConstant();
1758  if (direction == ArrayReduceDirection::kLeft) {
1759  k = zero;
1760  step = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberAdd(i, one); };
1761  cond = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberLessThan(i, original_length); };
1762  } else {
1763  k = NumberSubtract(original_length, one);
1764  step = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberSubtract(i, one); };
1765  cond = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberLessThanOrEqual(zero, i); };
1766  }
1767 
1768  ThrowIfNotCallable(
1769  fncallback, ReducePreLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1770  fncallback, k, original_length));
1771 
1772  // Set initial accumulator value.
1773  TNode<Object> accumulator;
1774  if (ArgumentCount() > 1) {
1775  accumulator = Argument(1); // Initial value specified by the user.
1776  } else {
1777  // The initial value was not specified by the user. In this case, the first
1778  // (or last in the case of reduceRight) non-holey value of the array is
1779  // used. Loop until we find it. If not found, trigger a deopt.
1780  // TODO(jgruber): The deopt does not seem necessary. Instead we could simply
1781  // throw the TypeError here from optimized code.
1782  auto found_initial_element = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
1783  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1784  Forever(k, step).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1785  Checkpoint(ReducePreLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1786  fncallback, original_length));
1787  CheckIf(cond(k), DeoptimizeReason::kNoInitialElement);
1788 
1789  TNode<Object> element;
1790  std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1791 
1792  auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1793  GotoIf(HoleCheck(kind, element), &continue_label);
1794  Goto(&found_initial_element, k, TypeGuardNonInternal(element));
1795 
1796  Bind(&continue_label);
1797  });
1798  Unreachable(); // The loop is exited either by deopt or a jump to below.
1799 
1800  // TODO(jgruber): This manual fiddling with blocks could be avoided by
1801  // implementing a `break` mechanic for loop builders.
1802  Bind(&found_initial_element);
1803  k = step(found_initial_element.PhiAt<Number>(0));
1804  accumulator = found_initial_element.PhiAt<Object>(1);
1805  }
1806 
1807  TNode<Object> result =
1808  For1(k, cond, step, accumulator)
1809  .Do([&](TNode<Number> k, TNode<Object>* accumulator) {
1810  Checkpoint(ReduceLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1811  fncallback, k, original_length,
1812  *accumulator));
1813 
1814  // Deopt if the map has changed during the iteration.
1815  MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1816 
1817  TNode<Object> element;
1818  std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1819 
1820  auto continue_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1821  element =
1822  MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label, *accumulator);
1823 
1824  TNode<Number> next_k = step(k);
1825  TNode<Object> next_accumulator = JSCall4(
1826  fncallback, UndefinedConstant(), *accumulator, element, k,
1827  receiver,
1828  ReduceLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1829  fncallback, next_k, original_length));
1830  Goto(&continue_label, next_accumulator);
1831 
1832  Bind(&continue_label);
1833  *accumulator = continue_label.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1834  })
1835  .Value();
1836 
1837  return result;
1838 }

1891 
1892 TNode<JSArray> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeMap(
1893  MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1894  ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
1895  NativeContextRef native_context) {
1896  FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1897  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1898  TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1899  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1900  TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1901  TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1902 
1903  TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1904 
1905  // If the array length >= kMaxFastArrayLength, then CreateArray
1906  // will create a dictionary. We should deopt in this case, and make sure
1907  // not to attempt inlining again.
1908  original_length = CheckBounds(original_length,
1909  NumberConstant(JSArray::kMaxFastArrayLength));
1910 
1911  // Even though {JSCreateArray} is not marked as {kNoThrow}, we can elide the
1912  // exceptional projections because it cannot throw with the given
1913  // parameters.
1914  TNode<Object> array_ctor =
1915  Constant(native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), kind)
1916  .GetConstructor(broker()));
1917 
1918  MapFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1919  jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1920  receiver, fncallback, this_arg, {} /* TBD */, original_length};
1921 
1922  TNode<JSArray> a =
1923  CreateArrayNoThrow(array_ctor, original_length,
1924  MapPreLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params));
1925  frame_state_params.a = a;
1926 
1927  ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback,
1928  MapLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant()));
1929 
1930  ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1931  Checkpoint(MapLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1932  MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1933 
1934  TNode<Object> element;
1935  std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1936 
1937  auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1938  element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
1939 
1940  TNode<Object> v = JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1941  MapLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1942 
1943  // The array {a} should be HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS because we'd only come into
1944  // this loop if the input array length is non-zero, and "new Array({x > 0})"
1945  // always produces a HOLEY array.
1946  MapRef holey_double_map =
1947  native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
1948  MapRef holey_map =
1949  native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
1950  TransitionAndStoreElement(holey_double_map, holey_map, a, k, v);
1951 
1952  Goto(&continue_label);
1953  Bind(&continue_label);
1954  });
1955 
1956  return a;
1957 }

2032 
2033 TNode<JSArray>
2034 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeFilter(
2035  MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
2036  ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
2037  NativeContextRef native_context) {
2038  FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2039  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2040  TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2041  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2042  TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2043  TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
2044 
2045  // The output array is packed (filter doesn't visit holes).
2046  ElementsKind filtered_kind = GetPackedElementsKind(kind);
2047 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2048  if (kind == ElementsKind::HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
2049  // Array may contain double-encoded undefineds that may be preserved by
2050  // the filter operation, so the output has to be holey, too.
2051  // TODO(nicohartmann, 385155404): We can consider starting with a
2052  // PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS and only transition to holey, when we actually
2053  // encounter an undefined.
2054  filtered_kind = ElementsKind::HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS;
2055  }
2056 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2057  TNode<JSArray> a = AllocateEmptyJSArray(filtered_kind, native_context);
2058 
2059  TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2060 
2061  FilterFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
2062  jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
2063  receiver, fncallback, this_arg, a, original_length};
2064 
2065  // This frame state doesn't ever call the deopt continuation, it's only
2066  // necessary to specify a continuation in order to handle the exceptional
2067  // case. We don't have all the values available to completely fill out
2068  // the checkpoint parameters yet, but that's okay because it'll never be
2069  // called.
2070  TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
2071  ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback, FilterLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
2072  zero, zero, zero));
2073 
2074  TNode<Number> initial_a_length = zero;
2075  For1ZeroUntil(original_length, initial_a_length)
2076  .Do([&](TNode<Number> k, TNode<Object>* a_length_object) {
2077  TNode<Number> a_length = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(*a_length_object);
2078  Checkpoint(FilterLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, a_length));
2079  MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
2080 
2081  TNode<Object> element;
2082  std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
2083 
2084  auto continue_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
2085  element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label, a_length);
2086 
2087  TNode<Object> v = JSCall3(
2088  fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
2089  FilterLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k, a_length, element));
2090 
2091  // We need an eager frame state for right after the callback function
2092  // returned, just in case an attempt to grow the output array fails.
2093  Checkpoint(FilterLoopEagerPostCallbackFrameState(frame_state_params, k,
2094  a_length, element, v));
2095 
2096  GotoIfNot(ToBoolean(v), &continue_label, a_length);
2097 
2098  // Since the callback returned a trueish value, store the element in a.
2099  {
2100  TNode<Number> a_length1 = TypeGuardFixedArrayLength(a_length);
2101  TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(a);
2102  elements = MaybeGrowFastElements(kind, FeedbackSource{}, a, elements,
2103  a_length1,
2104  LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(elements));
2105 
2106  TNode<Number> new_a_length = NumberInc(a_length1);
2107  StoreJSArrayLength(a, new_a_length, kind);
2108  StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(elements, a_length1, element, kind);
2109 
2110  Goto(&continue_label, new_a_length);
2111  }
2112 
2113  Bind(&continue_label);
2114  *a_length_object =
2115  TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(continue_label.PhiAt(0));
2116  })
2117  .ValueIsUnused();
2118 
2119  return a;
2120 }

2179 
2180 TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeFind(
2181  MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
2182  ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
2183  NativeContextRef native_context, ArrayFindVariant variant) {
2184  FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2185  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2186  TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2187  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2188  TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2189  TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
2190 
2191  TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2192 
2193  FindFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
2194  jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
2195  receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
2196 
2197  ThrowIfNotCallable(
2198  fncallback,
2199  FindLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant(), variant));
2200 
2201  const bool is_find_variant = (variant == ArrayFindVariant::kFind);
2202  auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2203 
2204  ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
2205  Checkpoint(FindLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
2206  MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
2207 
2208  TNode<Object> element;
2209  std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
2210 
2211  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
2212  element = ConvertHoleToUndefined(element, kind);
2213  }
2214 
2215  TNode<Object> if_found_value = is_find_variant ? element : k;
2216  TNode<Number> next_k = NumberInc(k);
2217 
2218  // The callback result states whether the desired element was found.
2219  TNode<Object> v =
2220  JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
2221  FindLoopAfterCallbackLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, next_k,
2222  if_found_value, variant));
2223 
2224  GotoIf(ToBoolean(v), &out, if_found_value);
2225  });
2226 
2227  // If the loop completed, the element was not found.
2228  TNode<Object> if_not_found_value =
2229  is_find_variant ? TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(UndefinedConstant())
2230  : TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(MinusOneConstant());
2231  Goto(&out, if_not_found_value);
2232 
2233  Bind(&out);
2234  return out.PhiAt<Object>(0);
2235 }

2281 TNode<Boolean>
2282 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeEverySome(
2283  MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
2284  ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
2285  NativeContextRef native_context, ArrayEverySomeVariant variant) {
2286  FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2287  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2288  TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2289  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2290  TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2291  TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
2292 
2293  TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2294 
2295  EverySomeFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
2296  jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
2297  receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
2298 
2299  ThrowIfNotCallable(
2300  fncallback,
2301  EverySomeLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant(), variant));
2302 
2303  auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2304 
2305  ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
2306  Checkpoint(EverySomeLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
2307  MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
2308 
2309  TNode<Object> element;
2310  std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
2311 
2312  auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
2313  element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
2314 
2315  TNode<Object> v =
2316  JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
2317  EverySomeLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
2318 
2319  if (variant == ArrayEverySomeVariant::kEvery) {
2320  GotoIfNot(ToBoolean(v), &out, FalseConstant());
2321  } else {
2322  DCHECK_EQ(variant, ArrayEverySomeVariant::kSome);
2323  GotoIf(ToBoolean(v), &out, TrueConstant());
2324  }
2325  Goto(&continue_label);
2326  Bind(&continue_label);
2327  });
2328 
2329  Goto(&out, (variant == ArrayEverySomeVariant::kEvery) ? TrueConstant()
2330  : FalseConstant());
2331 
2332  Bind(&out);
2333  return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
2334 }
2335 
2336 namespace {
2337 
2338 Callable GetCallableForArrayIndexOfIncludes(ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant variant,
2339  ElementsKind elements_kind,
2340  Isolate* isolate) {
2341  if (variant == ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIndexOf) {
2342  switch (elements_kind) {
2343  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2344  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2345  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate, Builtin::kArrayIndexOfSmi);
2346  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
2347  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
2348  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2349  Builtin::kArrayIndexOfSmiOrObject);
2350  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
2351  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2352  Builtin::kArrayIndexOfPackedDoubles);
2353  default:
2354  DCHECK_EQ(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, elements_kind);
2355  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2356  Builtin::kArrayIndexOfHoleyDoubles);
2357  }
2358  } else {
2359  DCHECK_EQ(variant, ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIncludes);
2360  switch (elements_kind) {
2361  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2362  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2363  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate, Builtin::kArrayIncludesSmi);
2364  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
2365  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
2366  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2367  Builtin::kArrayIncludesSmiOrObject);
2368  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
2369  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2370  Builtin::kArrayIncludesPackedDoubles);
2371  default:
2372  DCHECK_EQ(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, elements_kind);
2373  return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2374  Builtin::kArrayIncludesHoleyDoubles);
2375  }
2376  }
2377  UNREACHABLE();
2378 }
2379 
2380 } // namespace
2381 TNode<Object>
2382 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeIndexOfIncludes(
2383  ElementsKind kind, ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant variant) {
2384  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2385  TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2386  TNode<Object> search_element = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2387  TNode<Object> from_index = ArgumentOrZero(1);
2388 
2389  // TODO(jgruber): This currently only reduces to a stub call. Create a full
2390  // reduction (similar to other higher-order array builtins) instead of
2391  // lowering to a builtin call. E.g. Array.p.every and Array.p.some have almost
2392  // identical functionality.
2393 
2394  TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2395  TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(receiver);
2396 
2397  const bool have_from_index = ArgumentCount() > 1;
2398  if (have_from_index) {
2399  TNode<Smi> from_index_smi = CheckSmi(from_index);
2400 
2401  // If the index is negative, it means the offset from the end and
2402  // therefore needs to be added to the length. If the result is still
2403  // negative, it needs to be clamped to 0.
2404  TNode<Boolean> cond = NumberLessThan(from_index_smi, ZeroConstant());
2405  from_index = SelectIf<Number>(cond)
2406  .Then(_ {
2407  return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, from_index_smi),
2408  ZeroConstant());
2409  })
2410  .Else(_ { return from_index_smi; })
2411  .ExpectFalse()
2412  .Value();
2413  }
2414 
2415  return Call4(GetCallableForArrayIndexOfIncludes(variant, kind, isolate()),
2416  context, elements, search_element, length, from_index);
2417 }

2420 struct PromiseCtorFrameStateParams {
2421  JSGraph* jsgraph;
2422  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared;
2423  Node* node_ptr;
2424  TNode<Context> context;
2425  TNode<Object> target;
2426  FrameState outer_frame_state;
2427 };

2429 // Remnant of old-style JSCallReducer code. Could be ported to graph assembler,
2430 // but probably not worth the effort.
2431 FrameState CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(
2432  Node* node, Node* outer_frame_state, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
2433  Node* context, CommonOperatorBuilder* common, TFGraph* graph) {
2434  const FrameStateFunctionInfo* state_info =
2435  common->CreateFrameStateFunctionInfo(FrameStateType::kConstructInvokeStub,
2436  1, 0, 0, shared.object(), {});
2437 
2438  const Operator* op = common->FrameState(
2439  BytecodeOffset::None(), OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), state_info);
2440  const Operator* op0 = common->StateValues(0, SparseInputMask::Dense());
2441  Node* node0 = graph->NewNode(op0);
2442 
2443  static constexpr int kTargetInputIndex = 0;
2444  static constexpr int kReceiverInputIndex = 1;
2445  std::vector<Node*> params;
2446  params.push_back(node->InputAt(kReceiverInputIndex));
2447  const Operator* op_param = common->StateValues(
2448  static_cast<int>(params.size()), SparseInputMask::Dense());
2449  Node* params_node = graph->NewNode(op_param, static_cast<int>(params.size()),
2450  &params.front());
2451  DCHECK(context);
2452  return FrameState(graph->NewNode(op, params_node, node0, node0, context,
2453  node->InputAt(kTargetInputIndex),
2454  outer_frame_state));
2455 }
2456 
2457 FrameState PromiseConstructorFrameState(
2458  const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params, CommonOperatorBuilder* common,
2459  TFGraph* graph) {
2460  DCHECK_EQ(1,
2461  params.shared
2462  .internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver_deprecated());
2463  return CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(
2464  params.node_ptr, params.outer_frame_state, params.shared, params.context,
2465  common, graph);
2466 }
2467 
2468 FrameState PromiseConstructorLazyFrameState(
2469  const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params,
2470  FrameState constructor_frame_state) {
2471  // The deopt continuation of this frame state is never called; the frame state
2472  // is only necessary to obtain the right stack trace.
2473  JSGraph* jsgraph = params.jsgraph;
2474  Node* checkpoint_params[] = {
2475  jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* receiver */
2476  jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* promise */
2477  jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* reject function */
2478  jsgraph->TheHoleConstant() /* exception */
2479  };
2480  return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2481  jsgraph, params.shared, Builtin::kPromiseConstructorLazyDeoptContinuation,
2482  params.target, params.context, checkpoint_params,
2483  arraysize(checkpoint_params), constructor_frame_state,
2484  ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
2485 }
2486 
2487 FrameState PromiseConstructorLazyWithCatchFrameState(
2488  const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params,
2489  FrameState constructor_frame_state, TNode<JSPromise> promise,
2490  TNode<JSFunction> reject) {
2491  // This continuation just returns the created promise and takes care of
2492  // exceptions thrown by the executor.
2493  Node* checkpoint_params[] = {
2494  params.jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* receiver */
2495  promise, reject};
2496  return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2497  params.jsgraph, params.shared,
2498  Builtin::kPromiseConstructorLazyDeoptContinuation, params.target,
2499  params.context, checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params),
2500  constructor_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY_WITH_CATCH);
2501 }

2504 
2505 TNode<Object> PromiseBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReducePromiseConstructor(
2506  NativeContextRef native_context) {
2507  DCHECK_GE(ConstructArity(), 1);
2508 
2509  JSConstructNode n(node_ptr());
2510  FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2511  TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2512  TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2513  TNode<Object> executor = n.Argument(0);
2514  DCHECK_EQ(target, NewTargetInput());
2515 
2516  SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_shared =
2517  native_context.promise_function(broker()).shared(broker());
2518 
2519  PromiseCtorFrameStateParams frame_state_params{jsgraph(), promise_shared,
2520  node_ptr(), context,
2521  target, outer_frame_state};
2522 
2523  // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
2524  // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
2525  // For the frame state, we only provide the executor parameter, even if more
2526  // arguments were passed. This is not observable from JS.
2527  FrameState constructor_frame_state =
2528  PromiseConstructorFrameState(frame_state_params, common(), graph());
2529 
2530  IfNot(ObjectIsCallable(executor))
2531  .Then((_ {
2532  JSCallRuntime2(
2533  Runtime::kThrowTypeError,
2534  SmiConstant(
2535  Smi::FromEnum(MessageTemplate::kResolverNotAFunction).value()),
2536  executor, context,
2537  PromiseConstructorLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
2538  constructor_frame_state));
2539  }))
2540  .ExpectTrue();
2541 
2542  TNode<JSPromise> promise = CreatePromise(context);
2543 
2544  // 8. CreatePromiseResolvingFunctions
2545  // Allocate a promise context for the closures below.
2546  TNode<Context> promise_context = CreateFunctionContext(
2547  native_context, context, PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseContextLength);
2548  StoreContextNoCellSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseSlot,
2549  promise);
2550  StoreContextNoCellSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kAlreadyResolvedSlot,
2551  FalseConstant());
2552  StoreContextNoCellSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kDebugEventSlot,
2553  TrueConstant());
2554 
2555  // Allocate closures for the resolve and reject cases.
2556  SharedFunctionInfoRef resolve_sfi =
2557  MakeRef(broker(), broker()
2558  ->isolate()
2559  ->factory()
2560  ->promise_capability_default_resolve_shared_fun());
2561  TNode<JSFunction> resolve =
2562  CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(resolve_sfi, promise_context);
2563 
2564  SharedFunctionInfoRef reject_sfi =
2565  MakeRef(broker(), broker()
2566  ->isolate()
2567  ->factory()
2568  ->promise_capability_default_reject_shared_fun());
2569  TNode<JSFunction> reject =
2570  CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(reject_sfi, promise_context);
2571 
2572  FrameState lazy_with_catch_frame_state =
2573  PromiseConstructorLazyWithCatchFrameState(
2574  frame_state_params, constructor_frame_state, promise, reject);
2575 
2576  // 9. Call executor with both resolving functions.
2577  // 10a. Call reject if the call to executor threw.
2578  Try(_ {
2579  CallPromiseExecutor(executor, resolve, reject, lazy_with_catch_frame_state);
2580  }).Catch([&](TNode<Object> exception) {
2581  // Clear pending message since the exception is not going to be rethrown.
2582  ClearPendingMessage();
2583  CallPromiseReject(reject, exception, lazy_with_catch_frame_state);
2584  });
2585 
2586  return promise;
2587 }

2591 std::pair<Node*, Node*> JSCallReducer::ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(
2592  JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm) {
2593  auto catch_scope = gasm->catch_scope();
2594  DCHECK(catch_scope->is_outermost());
2595 
2596  if (catch_scope->has_handler() &&
2597  catch_scope->has_exceptional_control_flow()) {
2598  TNode<Object> handler_exception;
2599  Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
2600  Control handler_control{nullptr};
2601  gasm->catch_scope()->MergeExceptionalPaths(
2602  &handler_exception, &handler_effect, &handler_control);
2603 
2604  ReplaceWithValue(gasm->outermost_handler(), handler_exception,
2605  handler_effect, handler_control);
2606  }
2607 
2608  return {gasm->effect(), gasm->control()};
2609 }
2610 
2611 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReplaceWithSubgraph(JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm,
2612  Node* subgraph) {
2613  // TODO(jgruber): Consider a less fiddly way of integrating the new subgraph
2614  // into the outer graph. For instance, the subgraph could be created in
2615  // complete isolation, and then plugged into the outer graph in one go.
2616  // Instead of manually tracking IfException nodes, we could iterate the
2617  // subgraph.
2618 
2619  // Replace the Call node with the newly-produced subgraph.
2620  ReplaceWithValue(gasm->node_ptr(), subgraph, gasm->effect(), gasm->control());
2621 
2622  // Wire exception edges contained in the newly-produced subgraph into the
2623  // outer graph.
2624  auto catch_scope = gasm->catch_scope();
2625  DCHECK(catch_scope->is_outermost());
2626 
2627  if (catch_scope->has_handler() &&
2628  catch_scope->has_exceptional_control_flow()) {
2629  TNode<Object> handler_exception;
2630  Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
2631  Control handler_control{nullptr};
2632  gasm->catch_scope()->MergeExceptionalPaths(
2633  &handler_exception, &handler_effect, &handler_control);
2634 
2635  ReplaceWithValue(gasm->outermost_handler(), handler_exception,
2636  handler_effect, handler_control);
2637  }
2638 
2639  return Replace(subgraph);
2640 }

2642 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathUnary(Node* node, const Operator* op) {
2643  JSCallNode n(node);
2644  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2645  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
2646  return NoChange();
2647  }
2648  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2649  Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
2650  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2651  return Replace(value);
2652  }
2653 
2654  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
2655  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceMathUnary(op);
2656  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
2657 }

2660  JSCallNode n(node);
2661  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2662  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
2663  return NoChange();
2664  }
2665  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2666  Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
2667  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2668  return Replace(value);
2669  }
2670 
2671  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
2672  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceMathBinary(op);
2673  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
2674 }
