2676 // ES6 section 20.2.2.19 Math.imul ( x, y )
2677 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathImul(Node* node) {
2678  JSCallNode n(node);
2679  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2680  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
2681  return NoChange();
2682  }
2683  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2684  Node* value = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
2685  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2686  return Replace(value);
2687  }
2688  Node* left = n.Argument(0);
2689  Node* right = n.ArgumentOr(1, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
2690  Effect effect = n.effect();
2691  Control control = n.control();
2692 
2693  left = effect =
2694  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2695  NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2696  left, effect, control);
2697  right = effect =
2698  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2699  NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2700  right, effect, control);
2701  left = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), left);
2702  right = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), right);
2703  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberImul(), left, right);
2704  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2705  return Replace(value);
2706 }

2708 // ES6 section 20.2.2.11 Math.clz32 ( x )
2709 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathClz32(Node* node) {
2710  JSCallNode n(node);
2711  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2712  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
2713  return NoChange();
2714  }
2715  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2716  Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(32);
2717  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2718  return Replace(value);
2719  }
2720  Node* input = n.Argument(0);
2721  Effect effect = n.effect();
2722  Control control = n.control();
2723 
2724  input = effect =
2725  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2726  NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2727  input, effect, control);
2728  input = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), input);
2729  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberClz32(), input);
2730  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2731  return Replace(value);
2732 }

2734 // ES6 section 20.2.2.24 Math.max ( value1, value2, ...values )
2735 // ES6 section 20.2.2.25 Math.min ( value1, value2, ...values )
2736 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathMinMax(Node* node, const Operator* op,
2737  Node* empty_value) {
2738  JSCallNode n(node);
2739  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2740  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
2741  return NoChange();
2742  }
2743  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2744  ReplaceWithValue(node, empty_value);
2745  return Replace(empty_value);
2746  }
2747  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2748  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2749 
2750  Node* value = effect =
2751  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2752  NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2753  n.Argument(0), effect, control);
2754  for (int i = 1; i < n.ArgumentCount(); i++) {
2755  Node* input = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2756  simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball,
2757  p.feedback()),
2758  n.Argument(i), effect, control);
2759  value = graph()->NewNode(op, value, input);
2760  }
2761 
2762  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2763  return Replace(value);
2764 }
2765 
2766 Reduction JSCallReducer::Reduce(Node* node) {
2767  switch (node->opcode()) {
2768  case IrOpcode::kJSConstruct:
2769  return ReduceJSConstruct(node);
2770  case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike:
2771  return ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(node);
2772  case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread:
2773  return ReduceJSConstructWithSpread(node);
2774  case IrOpcode::kJSConstructForwardAllArgs:
2775  return ReduceJSConstructForwardAllArgs(node);
2776  case IrOpcode::kJSCall:
2777  return ReduceJSCall(node);
2778  case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike:
2779  return ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node);
2780  case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread:
2781  return ReduceJSCallWithSpread(node);
2782  default:
2783  break;
2784  }
2785  return NoChange();
2786 }
2787 
2788 void JSCallReducer::Finalize() {
2789  // TODO(turbofan): This is not the best solution; ideally we would be able
2790  // to teach the GraphReducer about arbitrary dependencies between different
2791  // nodes, even if they don't show up in the use list of the other node.
2792  std::set<Node*> const waitlist = std::move(waitlist_);
2793  for (Node* node : waitlist) {
2794  if (!node->IsDead()) {
2795  // Remember the max node id before reduction.
2796  NodeId const max_id = static_cast<NodeId>(graph()->NodeCount() - 1);
2797  Reduction const reduction = Reduce(node);
2798  if (reduction.Changed()) {
2799  Node* replacement = reduction.replacement();
2800  if (replacement != node) {
2801  Replace(node, replacement, max_id);
2802  }
2803  }
2804  }
2805  }
2806 }
2807 
2808 // ES6 section 22.1.1 The Array Constructor
2809 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayConstructor(Node* node) {
2810  JSCallNode n(node);
2811  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2812  if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2813  return NoChange();
2814  }
2815 
2816  // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
2817  Node* target = n.target();
2818  size_t const arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2819  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
2820  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 0);
2821  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 1);
2822  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2823  node, javascript()->CreateArray(arity, std::nullopt,
2824  n.Parameters().feedback()));
2825  return Changed(node);
2826 }
2827 
2828 // ES6 section 19.3.1.1 Boolean ( value )
2829 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBooleanConstructor(Node* node) {
2830  // Replace the {node} with a proper {ToBoolean} operator.
2831  JSCallNode n(node);
2832  Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
2833  value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), value);
2834  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2835  return Replace(value);
2836 }

2838 // ES section #sec-object-constructor
2839 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectConstructor(Node* node) {
2840  JSCallNode n(node);
2841  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
2842  Node* value = n.Argument(0);
2843  Effect effect = n.effect();
2844 
2845  // We can fold away the Tagged<Object>(x) call if |x| is definitely not a
2846  // primitive.
2847  if (NodeProperties::CanBePrimitive(broker(), value, effect)) {
2848  if (!NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), value, effect)) {
2849  // Turn the {node} into a {JSToObject} call if we know that
2850  // the {value} cannot be null or undefined.
2851  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
2852  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToObject());
2853  return Changed(node);
2854  }
2855  } else {
2856  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2857  return Replace(value);
2858  }
2859  return NoChange();
2860 }
2861 
2862 // ES6 section 19.2.3.1 Function.prototype.apply ( thisArg, argArray )
2863 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeApply(Node* node) {
2864  JSCallNode n(node);
2865  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2866  CallFeedbackRelation new_feedback_relation =
2867  p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kReceiver
2868  ? CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget
2869  : CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated;
2870  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2871 
2872  if (arity < 2) {
2873  // Degenerate cases.
2874  ConvertReceiverMode convert_mode;
2875  if (arity == 0) {
2876  // Neither thisArg nor argArray was provided.
2877  convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined;
2878  node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), n.receiver());
2879  node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2880  } else {
2881  DCHECK_EQ(arity, 1);
2882  // The argArray was not provided, just remove the {target}.
2883  convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
2884  node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
2885  --arity;
2886  }
2887  // Change {node} to a {JSCall} and try to reduce further.
2888  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2889  node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
2890  p.feedback(), convert_mode,
2891  p.speculation_mode(), new_feedback_relation));
2892  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
2893  }
2894 
2895  // Turn the JSCall into a JSCallWithArrayLike.
2896  // If {argArray} can be null or undefined, we have to generate branches since
2897  // JSCallWithArrayLike would throw for null or undefined.
2898 
2899  Node* target = n.receiver();
2900  Node* this_argument = n.Argument(0);
2901  Node* arguments_list = n.Argument(1);
2902  Node* context = n.context();
2903  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
2904  Effect effect = n.effect();
2905  Control control = n.control();
2906 
2907  // If {arguments_list} cannot be null or undefined, we don't need
2908  // to expand this {node} to control-flow.
2909  if (!NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), arguments_list, effect)) {
2910  // Massage the value inputs appropriately.
2911  node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), target);
2912  node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), this_argument);
2913  node->ReplaceInput(n.ArgumentIndex(0), arguments_list);
2914  while (arity-- > 1) node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(1));
2915 
2916  // Morph the {node} to a {JSCallWithArrayLike}.
2917  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2918  node, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
2919  p.speculation_mode(),
2920  new_feedback_relation));
2921  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node));
2922  }
2923 
2924  // Check whether {arguments_list} is null.
2925  Node* check_null =
2926  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), arguments_list,
2927  jsgraph()->NullConstant());
2928  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check_null,
2929  control);
2930  Node* if_null = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2931  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2932 
2933  // Check whether {arguments_list} is undefined.
2934  Node* check_undefined =
2935  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), arguments_list,
2936  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2937  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
2938  check_undefined, control);
2939  Node* if_undefined = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2940  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2941 
2942  // Lower to {JSCallWithArrayLike} if {arguments_list} is neither null
2943  // nor undefined.
2944  Node* effect0 = effect;
2945  Node* control0 = control;
2946  Node* value0 = effect0 = control0 = graph()->NewNode(
2947  javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
2948  p.speculation_mode(),
2949  new_feedback_relation),
2950  target, this_argument, arguments_list, n.feedback_vector(), context,
2951  frame_state, effect0, control0);
2952 
2953  // Lower to {JSCall} if {arguments_list} is either null or undefined.
2954  Node* effect1 = effect;
2955  Node* control1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_null, if_undefined);
2956  Node* value1 = effect1 = control1 = graph()->NewNode(
2957  javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(0)), target, this_argument,
2958  n.feedback_vector(), context, frame_state, effect1, control1);
2959 
2960  // Rewire potential exception edges.
2961  Node* if_exception = nullptr;
2962  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &if_exception)) {
2963  // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
2964  Node* if_exception0 =
2965  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), control0, effect0);
2966  control0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control0);
2967  Node* if_exception1 =
2968  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), control1, effect1);
2969  control1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control1);
2970 
2971  // Join the exception edges.
2972  Node* merge =
2973  graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception0, if_exception1);
2974  Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception0,
2975  if_exception1, merge);
2976  Node* phi =
2977  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
2978  if_exception0, if_exception1, merge);
2979  ReplaceWithValue(if_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
2980  }
2981 
2982  // Join control paths.
2983  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), control0, control1);
2984  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect0, effect1, control);
2985  Node* value =
2986  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), value0,
2987  value1, control);
2988  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2989  return Replace(value);
2990 }
2991 
2992 // ES section #sec-function.prototype.bind
2993 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeBind(Node* node) {
2994  JSCallNode n(node);
2995  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2996  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
2997  return NoChange();
2998  }
2999 
3000  // Value inputs to the {node} are as follows:
3001  //
3002  // - target, which is Function.prototype.bind JSFunction
3003  // - receiver, which is the [[BoundTargetFunction]]
3004  // - bound_this (optional), which is the [[BoundThis]]
3005  // - and all the remaining value inputs are [[BoundArguments]]
3006  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
3007  Node* context = n.context();
3008  Effect effect = n.effect();
3009  Control control = n.control();
3010 
3011  // Ensure that the {receiver} is known to be a JSBoundFunction or
3012  // a JSFunction with the same [[Prototype]], and all maps we've
3013  // seen for the {receiver} so far indicate that {receiver} is
3014  // definitely a constructor or not a constructor.
3015  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
3016  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
3017  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
3018 
3019  MapRef first_receiver_map = receiver_maps[0];
3020  bool const is_constructor = first_receiver_map.is_constructor();
3021 
3022  HeapObjectRef prototype = first_receiver_map.prototype(broker());
3023 
3024  for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
3025  HeapObjectRef map_prototype = receiver_map.prototype(broker());
3026 
3027  // Check for consistency among the {receiver_maps}.
3028  if (!map_prototype.equals(prototype) ||
3029  receiver_map.is_constructor() != is_constructor ||
3030  !InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(
3031  receiver_map.instance_type())) {
3032  return inference.NoChange();
3033  }
3034 
3035  // Disallow binding of slow-mode functions. We need to figure out
3036  // whether the length and name property are in the original state.
3037  if (receiver_map.is_dictionary_map()) return inference.NoChange();
3038 
3039  // Check whether the length and name properties are still present
3040  // as AccessorInfo objects. In that case, their values can be
3041  // recomputed even if the actual value of the object changes.
3042  // This mirrors the checks done in builtins-function-gen.cc at
3043  // runtime otherwise.
3044  int minimum_nof_descriptors =
3045  std::max(
3046  {JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex,
3047  JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::
3048  kNameDescriptorIndex}) +
3049  1;
3050  if (receiver_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors() < minimum_nof_descriptors) {
3051  return inference.NoChange();
3052  }
3053  const InternalIndex kLengthIndex(
3054  JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex);
3055  const InternalIndex kNameIndex(
3056  JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex);
3057  StringRef length_string = broker()->length_string();
3058  StringRef name_string = broker()->name_string();
3059 
3060  OptionalObjectRef length_value(
3061  receiver_map.GetStrongValue(broker(), kLengthIndex));
3062  OptionalObjectRef name_value(
3063  receiver_map.GetStrongValue(broker(), kNameIndex));
3064  if (!length_value || !name_value) {
3065  TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(
3066  broker(), "name or length descriptors on map " << receiver_map);
3067  return inference.NoChange();
3068  }
3069  if (!receiver_map.GetPropertyKey(broker(), kLengthIndex)
3070  .equals(length_string) ||
3071  !length_value->IsAccessorInfo() ||
3072  !receiver_map.GetPropertyKey(broker(), kNameIndex)
3073  .equals(name_string) ||
3074  !name_value->IsAccessorInfo()) {
3075  return inference.NoChange();
3076  }
3077  }
3078 
3079  // Choose the map for the resulting JSBoundFunction (but bail out in case of a
3080  // custom prototype).
3081  MapRef map =
3082  is_constructor
3083  ? native_context().bound_function_with_constructor_map(broker())
3084  : native_context().bound_function_without_constructor_map(broker());
3085  if (!map.prototype(broker()).equals(prototype)) return inference.NoChange();
3086 
3087  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
3088  control, p.feedback());
3089 
3090  // Replace the {node} with a JSCreateBoundFunction.
3091  static constexpr int kBoundThis = 1;
3092  static constexpr int kReceiverContextEffectAndControl = 4;
3093  int const arity = n.ArgumentCount();
3094 
3095  if (arity > 0) {
3096  MapRef fixed_array_map = broker()->fixed_array_map();
3097  AllocationBuilder ab(jsgraph(), broker(), effect, control);
3098  if (!ab.CanAllocateArray(arity, fixed_array_map)) {
3099  return NoChange();
3100  }
3101  }
3102 
3103  int const arity_with_bound_this = std::max(arity, kBoundThis);
3104  int const input_count =
3105  arity_with_bound_this + kReceiverContextEffectAndControl;
3106  Node** inputs = graph()->zone()->AllocateArray<Node*>(input_count);
3107  int cursor = 0;
3108  inputs[cursor++] = receiver;
3109  inputs[cursor++] = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph()); // bound_this.
3110  for (int i = 1; i < arity; ++i) {
3111  inputs[cursor++] = n.Argument(i);
3112  }
3113  inputs[cursor++] = context;
3114  inputs[cursor++] = effect;
3115  inputs[cursor++] = control;
3116  DCHECK_EQ(cursor, input_count);
3117  Node* value = effect =
3118  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateBoundFunction(
3119  arity_with_bound_this - kBoundThis, map),
3120  input_count, inputs);
3121  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
3122  return Replace(value);
3123 }

3125 // ES6 section 19.2.3.3 Function.prototype.call (thisArg, ...args)
3126 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeCall(Node* node) {
3127  JSCallNode n(node);
3128  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3129  Node* target = n.target();
3130  Effect effect = n.effect();
3131  Control control = n.control();
3132 
3133  // Change context of {node} to the Function.prototype.call context,
3134  // to ensure any exception is thrown in the correct context.
3135  Node* context;
3136  HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
3137  if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
3138  JSFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
3139  context = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function.context(broker()), broker());
3140  } else {
3141  context = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3142  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext()), target,
3143  effect, control);
3144  }
3145  NodeProperties::ReplaceContextInput(node, context);
3146  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
3147 
3148  // Remove the target from {node} and use the receiver as target instead, and
3149  // the thisArg becomes the new target. If thisArg was not provided, insert
3150  // undefined instead.
3151  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3152  ConvertReceiverMode convert_mode;
3153  if (arity == 0) {
3154  // The thisArg was not provided, use undefined as receiver.
3155  convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined;
3156  node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), n.receiver());
3157  node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3158  } else {
3159  // Just remove the target, which is the first value input.
3160  convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
3161  node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
3162  --arity;
3163  }
3164  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3165  node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
3166  p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
3167  CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
3168  // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
3169  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
3170 }

3172 // ES6 section 19.2.3.6 Function.prototype [ @@hasInstance ] (V)
3173 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeHasInstance(Node* node) {
3174  JSCallNode n(node);
3175  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
3176  Node* object = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3177  Node* context = n.context();
3178  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3179  Effect effect = n.effect();
3180  Control control = n.control();
3181 
3182  // TODO(turbofan): If JSOrdinaryToInstance raises an exception, the
3183  // stack trace doesn't contain the @@hasInstance call; we have the
3184  // corresponding bug in the baseline case. Some massaging of the frame
3185  // state would be necessary here.
3186 
3187  // Morph this {node} into a JSOrdinaryHasInstance node.
3188  node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
3189  node->ReplaceInput(1, object);
3190  node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
3191  node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
3192  node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
3193  node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
3194  node->TrimInputCount(6);
3195  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->OrdinaryHasInstance());
3196  return Changed(node);
3197 }

3199 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectGetPrototype(Node* node, Node* object) {
3200  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
3201 
3202  // Try to determine the {object} map.
3203  MapInference inference(broker(), object, effect);
3204  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
3205  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& object_maps = inference.GetMaps();
3206 
3207  MapRef candidate_map = object_maps[0];
3208  HeapObjectRef candidate_prototype = candidate_map.prototype(broker());
3209 
3210  // Check if we can constant-fold the {candidate_prototype}.
3211  for (size_t i = 0; i < object_maps.size(); ++i) {
3212  MapRef object_map = object_maps[i];
3213  HeapObjectRef map_prototype = object_map.prototype(broker());
3214  if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(object_map.instance_type()) ||
3215  !map_prototype.equals(candidate_prototype)) {
3216  // We exclude special receivers, like JSProxy or API objects that
3217  // might require access checks here; we also don't want to deal
3218  // with hidden prototypes at this point.
3219  return inference.NoChange();
3220  }
3221  // The above check also excludes maps for primitive values, which is
3222  // important because we are not applying [[ToObject]] here as expected.
3223  DCHECK(!object_map.IsPrimitiveMap() && object_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
3224  }
3225  if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
3226  return inference.NoChange();
3227  }
3228  Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(candidate_prototype, broker());
3229  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
3230  return Replace(value);
3231 }

3256 // ES #sec-object.prototype.hasownproperty
3257 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty(Node* node) {
3258  JSCallNode call_node(node);
3259  Node* receiver = call_node.receiver();
3260  Node* name = call_node.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3261  Effect effect = call_node.effect();
3262  Control control = call_node.control();
3263 
3264  // We can optimize a call to Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty if it's being
3265  // used inside a fast-mode for..in, so for code like this:
3266  //
3267  // for (name in receiver) {
3268  // if (receiver.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
3269  // ...
3270  // }
3271  // }
3272  //
3273  // If the for..in is in fast-mode, we know that the {receiver} has {name}
3274  // as own property, otherwise the enumeration wouldn't include it. The graph
3275  // constructed by the BytecodeGraphBuilder in this case looks like this:
3276 
3277  // receiver
3278  // ^ ^
3279  // | |
3280  // | +-+
3281  // | |
3282  // | JSToObject
3283  // | ^
3284  // | |
3285  // | JSForInNext
3286  // | ^
3287  // +----+ |
3288  // | |
3289  // JSCall[hasOwnProperty]
3290 
3291  // We can constant-fold the {node} to True in this case, and insert
3292  // a (potentially redundant) map check to guard the fact that the
3293  // {receiver} map didn't change since the dominating JSForInNext. This
3294  // map check is only necessary when TurboFan cannot prove that there
3295  // is no observable side effect between the {JSForInNext} and the
3296  // {JSCall} to Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.
3297  //
3298  // Also note that it's safe to look through the {JSToObject}, since the
3299  // Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty does an implicit ToObject anyway, and
3300  // these operations are not observable.
3301  if (name->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSForInNext) {
3302  JSForInNextNode n(name);
3303  if (n.Parameters().mode() != ForInMode::kGeneric) {
3304  Node* object = n.receiver();
3305  Node* cache_type = n.cache_type();
3306  if (object->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToObject) {
3307  object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(object, 0);
3308  }
3309  if (object == receiver) {
3310  // No need to repeat the map check if we can prove that there's no
3311  // observable side effect between {effect} and {name].
3312  if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect, name)) {
3313  Node* receiver_map = effect =
3314  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
3315  receiver, effect, control);
3316  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
3317  receiver_map, cache_type);
3318  effect = graph()->NewNode(
3319  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap), check, effect,
3320  control);
3321  }
3322  Node* value = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
3323  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
3324  return Replace(value);
3325  }
3326 
3327  // We can also optimize for this case below:
3328 
3329  // receiver(is a heap constant with fast map)
3330  // ^
3331  // | object(all keys are enumerable)
3332  // | ^
3333  // | |
3334  // | JSForInNext
3335  // | ^
3336  // +----+ |
3337  // | |
3338  // JSCall[hasOwnProperty]
3339 
3340  // We can replace the {JSCall} with several internalized string
3341  // comparisons.
3342 
3343  if (receiver->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant) {
3344  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
3345  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) {
3346  return inference.NoChange();
3347  }
3348  const ZoneRefSet<Map>& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
3349  if (receiver_maps.size() == 1) {
3350  const MapRef receiver_map = *receiver_maps.begin();
3351  InstanceType instance_type = receiver_map.instance_type();
3352  int const nof = receiver_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3353  // We set a heuristic value to limit the compare instructions number.
3354  if (nof > 4 || instance_type <= LAST_SPECIAL_RECEIVER_TYPE ||
3355  receiver_map.is_dictionary_map()) {
3356  return inference.NoChange();
3357  }
3358  // Replace builtin call with several internalized string comparisons.
3359  CallParameters const& p = call_node.Parameters();
3360  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(),
3361  &effect, control, p.feedback());
3362 #define __ gasm.
3363  JSGraphAssembler gasm(broker(), jsgraph(), jsgraph()->zone(),
3364  BranchSemantics::kJS);
3365  gasm.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
3366  auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3367  const DescriptorArrayRef descriptor_array =
3368  receiver_map.instance_descriptors(broker());
3369  for (InternalIndex key_index : InternalIndex::Range(nof)) {
3370  NameRef receiver_key =
3371  descriptor_array.GetPropertyKey(broker(), key_index);
3372  Node* lhs = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(receiver_key.object());
3373  __ GotoIf(__ ReferenceEqual(TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(lhs),
3374  TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(name)),
3375  &done, __ TrueConstant());
3376  }
3377  __ Goto(&done, __ FalseConstant());
3378  __ Bind(&done);
3379 
3380  Node* value = done.PhiAt(0);
3381  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, gasm.effect(), gasm.control());
3382  return Replace(value);
3383 #undef __
3384  }
3385  return inference.NoChange();
3386  }
3387  }
3388  }
3389 
3390  return NoChange();
3391 }

3393 // ES #sec-object.prototype.isprototypeof
3394 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectPrototypeIsPrototypeOf(Node* node) {
3395  JSCallNode n(node);
3396  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
3397  Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3398  Effect effect = n.effect();
3399 
3400  // Ensure that the {receiver} is known to be a JSReceiver (so that
3401  // the ToObject step of Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf is a no-op).
3402  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
3403  if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
3404  return NoChange();
3405  }
3406 
3407  // We don't check whether {value} is a proper JSReceiver here explicitly,
3408  // and don't explicitly rule out Primitive {value}s, since all of them
3409  // have null as their prototype, so the prototype chain walk inside the
3410  // JSHasInPrototypeChain operator immediately aborts and yields false.
3411  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, value, n.TargetIndex());
3412  for (int i = node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i > 2; i--) {
3413  node->RemoveInput(2);
3414  }
3415  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->HasInPrototypeChain());
3416  return Changed(node);
3417 }
3418 
3419 // ES6 section 26.1.1 Reflect.apply ( target, thisArgument, argumentsList )
3420 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectApply(Node* node) {
3421  JSCallNode n(node);
3422  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3423  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3424  // Massage value inputs appropriately.
3425  static_assert(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex());
3426  node->RemoveInput(n.ReceiverIndex());
3427  node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
3428  while (arity < 3) {
3429  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity++, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3430  }
3431  while (arity-- > 3) {
3432  node->RemoveInput(arity);
3433  }
3434  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3435  node, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
3436  p.speculation_mode(),
3437  CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
3438  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node));
3439 }
3440 
3441 // ES6 section 26.1.2 Reflect.construct ( target, argumentsList [, newTarget] )
3442 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectConstruct(Node* node) {
3443  JSCallNode n(node);
3444  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3445  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3446  // Massage value inputs appropriately.
3447  TNode<Object> arg_target = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3448  TNode<Object> arg_argument_list = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
3449  TNode<Object> arg_new_target = n.ArgumentOr(2, arg_target);
3450 
3451  static_assert(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex());
3452  node->RemoveInput(n.ReceiverIndex());
3453  node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
3454 
3455  // TODO(jgruber): This pattern essentially ensures that we have the correct
3456  // number of inputs for a given argument count. Wrap it in a helper function.
3457  static_assert(JSConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex() == 2);
3458  while (arity < 3) {
3459  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity++, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3460  }
3461  while (arity-- > 3) {
3462  node->RemoveInput(arity);
3463  }
3464 
3465  static_assert(JSConstructNode::TargetIndex() == 0);
3466  static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1);
3467  static_assert(JSConstructNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput);
3468  node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::TargetIndex(), arg_target);
3469  node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex(), arg_new_target);
3470  node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(0), arg_argument_list);
3471 
3472  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3473  node, javascript()->ConstructWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback()));
3474  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(node));
3475 }

3479  JSCallNode n(node);
3480  Node* target = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3481  return ReduceObjectGetPrototype(node, target);
3482 }

3484 // ES6 section #sec-object.create Object.create(proto, properties)
3485 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectCreate(Node* node) {
3486  JSCallNode n(node);
3487  Node* properties = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
3488  if (properties != jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant()) return NoChange();
3489 
3490  Node* context = n.context();
3491  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3492  Effect effect = n.effect();
3493  Control control = n.control();
3494  Node* prototype = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3495  node->ReplaceInput(0, prototype);
3496  node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
3497  node->ReplaceInput(2, frame_state);
3498  node->ReplaceInput(3, effect);
3499  node->ReplaceInput(4, control);
3500  node->TrimInputCount(5);
3501  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->CreateObject());
3502  return Changed(node);
3503 }

3505 // ES section #sec-reflect.get
3506 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectGet(Node* node) {
3507  JSCallNode n(node);
3508  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3509  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3510  if (arity != 2) return NoChange();
3511  Node* target = n.Argument(0);
3512  Node* key = n.Argument(1);
3513  Node* context = n.context();
3514  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3515  Effect effect = n.effect();
3516  Control control = n.control();
3517 
3518  // Check whether {target} is a JSReceiver.
3519  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), target);
3520  Node* branch =
3521  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3522 
3523  // Throw an appropriate TypeError if the {target} is not a JSReceiver.
3524  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3525  Node* efalse = effect;
3526  {
3527  if_false = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3528  javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
3529  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
3530  static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject)),
3531  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->ReflectGet_string()), context,
3532  frame_state, efalse, if_false);
3533  }
3534 
3535  // Otherwise just use the existing GetPropertyStub.
3536  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3537  Node* etrue = effect;
3538  Node* vtrue;
3539  {
3540  Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kGetProperty);
3541  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
3542  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
3543  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
3544  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState, Operator::kNoProperties);
3545  Node* stub_code = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code());
3546  vtrue = etrue = if_true =
3547  graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), stub_code, target,
3548  key, context, frame_state, etrue, if_true);
3549  }
3550 
3551  // Rewire potential exception edges.
3552  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
3553  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
3554  // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
3555  Node* extrue = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), etrue, if_true);
3556  if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_true);
3557  Node* exfalse = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), efalse, if_false);
3558  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_false);
3559 
3560  // Join the exception edges.
3561  Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), extrue, exfalse);
3562  Node* ephi =
3563  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), extrue, exfalse, merge);
3564  Node* phi =
3565  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3566  extrue, exfalse, merge);
3567  ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
3568  }
3569 
3570  // Connect the throwing path to end.
3571  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), efalse, if_false);
3572  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), if_false);
3573 
3574  // Continue on the regular path.
3575  ReplaceWithValue(node, vtrue, etrue, if_true);
3576  return Changed(vtrue);
3577 }
3578 
3579 // ES section #sec-reflect.has
3580 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectHas(Node* node) {
3581  JSCallNode n(node);
3582  Node* target = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3583  Node* key = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
3584  Node* context = n.context();
3585  Effect effect = n.effect();
3586  Control control = n.control();
3587  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3588 
3589  // Check whether {target} is a JSReceiver.
3590  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), target);
3591  Node* branch =
3592  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3593 
3594  // Throw an appropriate TypeError if the {target} is not a JSReceiver.
3595  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3596  Node* efalse = effect;
3597  {
3598  if_false = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3599  javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
3600  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
3601  static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject)),
3602  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->ReflectHas_string()), context,
3603  frame_state, efalse, if_false);
3604  }
3605 
3606  // Otherwise just use the existing {JSHasProperty} logic.
3607  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3608  Node* etrue = effect;
3609  Node* vtrue;
3610  {
3611  // TODO(magardn): collect feedback so this can be optimized
3612  vtrue = etrue = if_true = graph()->NewNode(
3613  javascript()->HasProperty(FeedbackSource()), target, key,
3614  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), context, frame_state, etrue, if_true);
3615  }
3616 
3617  // Rewire potential exception edges.
3618  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
3619  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
3620  // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
3621  Node* extrue = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), etrue, if_true);
3622  if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_true);
3623  Node* exfalse = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), efalse, if_false);
3624  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_false);
3625 
3626  // Join the exception edges.
3627  Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), extrue, exfalse);
3628  Node* ephi =
3629  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), extrue, exfalse, merge);
3630  Node* phi =
3631  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3632  extrue, exfalse, merge);
3633  ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
3634  }
3635 
3636  // Connect the throwing path to end.
3637  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), efalse, if_false);
3638  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), if_false);
3639 
3640  // Continue on the regular path.
3641  ReplaceWithValue(node, vtrue, etrue, if_true);
3642  return Changed(vtrue);
3643 }

3647 bool CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(JSHeapBroker* broker,
3648  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps,
3649  ElementsKind* kind_return) {
3650  DCHECK_NE(0, receiver_maps.size());
3651  *kind_return = receiver_maps[0].elements_kind();
3652  for (MapRef map : receiver_maps) {
3653  if (!map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker) ||
3654  !UnionElementsKindUptoSize(kind_return, map.elements_kind())) {
3655  return false;
3656  }
3657  }
3658  return true;
3659 }
3660 
3661 bool CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(JSHeapBroker* broker,
3662  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps,
3663  std::vector<ElementsKind>* kinds,
3664  bool builtin_is_push = false) {
3665  DCHECK_NE(0, receiver_maps.size());
3666  for (MapRef map : receiver_maps) {
3667  if (!map.supports_fast_array_resize(broker)) return false;
3668  // TODO(turbofan): We should also handle fast holey double elements once
3669  // we got the hole NaN mess sorted out in TurboFan/V8.
3670  if (map.elements_kind() == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS && !builtin_is_push) {
3671  return false;
3672  }
3673  ElementsKind current_kind = map.elements_kind();
3674  auto kind_ptr = kinds->data();
3675  size_t i;
3676  for (i = 0; i < kinds->size(); i++, kind_ptr++) {
3677  if (UnionElementsKindUptoPackedness(kind_ptr, current_kind)) {
3678  break;
3679  }
3680  }
3681  if (i == kinds->size()) kinds->push_back(current_kind);
3682  }
3683  return true;
3684 }
3685 
3686 // Wraps common setup code for iterating array builtins.
3687 class IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper {
3688  public:
3689  IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper(Node* node, JSHeapBroker* broker,
3690  JSGraph* jsgraph,
3691  CompilationDependencies* dependencies)
3692  : receiver_(NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1)),
3693  effect_(NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)),
3694  control_(NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)),
3695  inference_(broker, receiver_, effect_) {
3696  if (!v8_flags.turbo_inline_array_builtins) return;
3697 
3698  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode());
3699  const CallParameters& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
3700  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
3701  return;
3702  }
3703 
3704  // Try to determine the {receiver} map.
3705  if (!inference_.HaveMaps()) return;
3706  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference_.GetMaps();
3707 
3708  if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker, receiver_maps,
3709  &elements_kind_)) {
3710  return;
3711  }
3712 
3713  // TODO(jgruber): May only be needed for holey elements kinds.
3714  if (!dependencies->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) return;
3715 
3716  has_stability_dependency_ = inference_.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(
3717  dependencies, jsgraph, &effect_, control_, p.feedback());
3718 
3719  can_reduce_ = true;
3720  }
3721 
3722  bool can_reduce() const { return can_reduce_; }
3723  bool has_stability_dependency() const { return has_stability_dependency_; }
3724  Effect effect() const { return effect_; }
3725  Control control() const { return control_; }
3726  MapInference* inference() { return &inference_; }
3727  ElementsKind elements_kind() const { return elements_kind_; }
3728 
3729  private:
3730  bool can_reduce_ = false;
3731  bool has_stability_dependency_ = false;
3732  Node* receiver_;
3733  Effect effect_;
3734  Control control_;
3735  MapInference inference_;
3736  ElementsKind elements_kind_;
3737 };
3738 
3739 } // namespace

3741 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayForEach(Node* node,
3742  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
3743  IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper h(node, broker(), jsgraph(), dependencies());
3744  if (!h.can_reduce()) return h.inference()->NoChange();

3746  IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
3747  a.InitializeEffectControl(h.effect(), h.control());
3748  TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReduceArrayPrototypeForEach(
3749  h.inference(), h.has_stability_dependency(), h.elements_kind(), shared);
3750  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
3751 }

3903 namespace {
3904 
3905 bool CanInlineJSToWasmCall(const wasm::CanonicalSig* wasm_signature) {
3906  if (wasm_signature->return_count() > 1) {
3907  return false;
3908  }
3909 
3910  for (auto type : wasm_signature->all()) {
3911 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_32_BIT)
3912  if (type == wasm::kWasmI64) return false;
3913 #endif
3914  if (type != wasm::kWasmI32 && type != wasm::kWasmI64 &&
3915  type != wasm::kWasmF32 && type != wasm::kWasmF64 &&
3916  type != wasm::kWasmExternRef) {
3917  return false;
3918  }
3919  }
3920 
3921  return true;
3922 }
3923 
3924 } // namespace
3925 
3926 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallWasmFunction(Node* node,
3927  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
3928  DCHECK(flags() & kInlineJSToWasmCalls);
3929 
3930  JSCallNode n(node);
3931  const CallParameters& p = n.Parameters();
3932 
3933  // Avoid deoptimization loops if feedback says we should be conservative.
3934  if (p.feedback().IsValid() &&
3935  p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
3936  return NoChange();
3937  }
3938 
3939  // Read the trusted object only once to ensure a consistent view on it.
3940  Tagged<Object> trusted_data = shared.object()->GetTrustedData(isolate());
3941  if (!IsWasmExportedFunctionData(trusted_data)) return NoChange();
3942  Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> function_data =
3943  Cast<WasmExportedFunctionData>(trusted_data);
3944 
3945  if (function_data->is_promising()) return NoChange();
3946 
3947  Tagged<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance_data =
3948  function_data->instance_data();
3949  const wasm::CanonicalSig* wasm_signature = function_data->sig();
3950  if (!CanInlineJSToWasmCall(wasm_signature)) {
3951  return NoChange();
3952  }
3953 
3954  wasm::NativeModule* native_module = instance_data->native_module();
3955  const wasm::WasmModule* wasm_module = native_module->module();
3956  int wasm_function_index = function_data->function_index();
3957  bool receiver_is_first_param = function_data->receiver_is_first_param() != 0;
3958 
3959  if (wasm_module_for_inlining_ == nullptr) {
3960  wasm_module_for_inlining_ = wasm_module;
3961  }
3962 
3963  // TODO(mliedtke): We should be able to remove module, signature, native
3964  // module and function index from the SharedFunctionInfoRef. However, for some
3965  // reason I may dereference the SharedFunctionInfoRef here but not in
3966  // JSInliningHeuristic later on.
3967  const Operator* op =
3968  javascript()->CallWasm(wasm_module, wasm_signature, wasm_function_index,
3969  shared, native_module, p.feedback());
3970 
3971  size_t actual_arity = n.ArgumentCount();
3972  DCHECK(JSCallNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput);
3973  DCHECK_EQ(actual_arity + JSWasmCallNode::kExtraInputCount - 1,
3974  n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
3975  size_t expected_arity = wasm_signature->parameter_count();
3976 
3977  // Duplicate the receiver into the first argument slot if requested.
3978  if (receiver_is_first_param) {
3979  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.FirstArgumentIndex(),
3980  node->InputAt(n.ReceiverIndex()));
3981  actual_arity++;
3982  }
3983 
3984  // Remove additional inputs.
3985  while (actual_arity > expected_arity) {
3986  int removal_index =
3987  static_cast<int>(n.FirstArgumentIndex() + expected_arity);
3988  DCHECK_LT(removal_index, static_cast<int>(node->InputCount()));
3989  node->RemoveInput(removal_index);
3990  actual_arity--;
3991  }
3992 
3993  // Add missing inputs.
3994  while (actual_arity < expected_arity) {
3995  int insertion_index = n.ArgumentIndex(n.ArgumentCount());
3996  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), insertion_index,
3997  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3998  actual_arity++;
3999  }
4000 
4001  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, op);
4002  return Changed(node);
4003 }
4004 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4005 
4006 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallApiFunction(Node* node,
4007  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
4008  JSCallNode n(node);
4009  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4010  int const argc = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
4011  Node* target = n.target();
4012  Node* global_proxy = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
4013  native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()), broker());
4014  Node* receiver = (p.convert_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined)
4015  ? global_proxy
4016  : n.receiver();
4017  Node* context = n.context();
4018  Effect effect = n.effect();
4019  Control control = n.control();
4020  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
4021 
4022  if (!shared.function_template_info(broker()).has_value()) {
4023  TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(
4024  broker(), "FunctionTemplateInfo for function with SFI " << shared);
4025  return NoChange();
4026  }
4027 
4028  // See if we can optimize this API call to {shared}.
4029  FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info(
4030  shared.function_template_info(broker()).value());
4031 
4032  if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver() &&
4033  function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
4034  // We might be able to
4035  // optimize the API call depending on the {function_template_info}.
4036  // If the API function accepts any kind of {receiver}, we only need to
4037  // ensure that the {receiver} is actually a JSReceiver at this point,
4038  // and also pass that as the {holder}. There are two independent bits
4039  // here:
4040  //
4041  // a. When the "accept any receiver" bit is set, it means we don't
4042  // need to perform access checks, even if the {receiver}'s map
4043  // has the "needs access check" bit set.
4044  // b. When the {function_template_info} has no signature, we don't
4045  // need to do the compatible receiver check, since all receivers
4046  // are considered compatible at that point, and the {receiver}
4047  // will be pass as the {holder}.
4048  //
4049  receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4050  simplified()->ConvertReceiver(p.convert_mode()), receiver,
4051  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker()), global_proxy,
4052  effect, control);
4053  } else {
4054  // Try to infer the {receiver} maps from the graph.
4055  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
4056  if (inference.HaveMaps()) {
4057  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
4058  MapRef first_receiver_map = receiver_maps[0];
4059 
4060  // See if we can constant-fold the compatible receiver checks.
4061  HolderLookupResult api_holder =
4062  function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
4063  first_receiver_map);
4064  if (api_holder.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound) {
4065  return inference.NoChange();
4066  }
4067 
4068  // Check that all {receiver_maps} are actually JSReceiver maps and
4069  // that the {function_template_info} accepts them without access
4070  // checks (even if "access check needed" is set for {receiver}).
4071  //
4072  // Note that we don't need to know the concrete {receiver} maps here,
4073  // meaning it's fine if the {receiver_maps} are unreliable, and we also
4074  // don't need to install any stability dependencies, since the only
4075  // relevant information regarding the {receiver} is the Map::constructor
4076  // field on the root map (which is different from the JavaScript exposed
4077  // "constructor" property) and that field cannot change.
4078  //
4079  // So if we know that {receiver} had a certain constructor at some point
4080  // in the past (i.e. it had a certain map), then this constructor is going
4081  // to be the same later, since this information cannot change with map
4082  // transitions.
4083  //
4084  // The same is true for the instance type, e.g. we still know that the
4085  // instance type is JSObject even if that information is unreliable, and
4086  // the "access check needed" bit, which also cannot change later.
4087  CHECK(first_receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
4088  CHECK(!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
4089  function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
4090 
4091  for (size_t i = 1; i < receiver_maps.size(); ++i) {
4092  MapRef receiver_map = receiver_maps[i];
4093  HolderLookupResult holder_i =
4094  function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
4095  receiver_map);
4096 
4097  if (api_holder.lookup != holder_i.lookup) return inference.NoChange();
4098  DCHECK(holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound ||
4099  holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver);
4100  if (holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound) {
4101  DCHECK(api_holder.holder.has_value() && holder_i.holder.has_value());
4102  if (!api_holder.holder->equals(*holder_i.holder)) {
4103  return inference.NoChange();
4104  }
4105  }
4106 
4107  CHECK(receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
4108  CHECK(!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
4109  function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
4110  }
4111 
4112  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation &&
4113  !inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
4114  // We were not able to make the receiver maps reliable without map
4115  // checks but doing map checks would lead to deopt loops, so give up.
4116  return inference.NoChange();
4117  }
4118 
4119  // TODO(neis): The maps were used in a way that does not actually require
4120  // map checks or stability dependencies.
4121  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
4122  control, p.feedback());
4123  } else {
4124  // We don't have enough information to eliminate the access check
4125  // and/or the compatible receiver check, so use the generic builtin
4126  // that does those checks dynamically. This is still significantly
4127  // faster than the generic call sequence.
4128  Builtin builtin_name;
4129  if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()) {
4130  DCHECK(!function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker()));
4131  builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckCompatibleReceiver;
4132  } else if (function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
4133  builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccess;
4134  } else {
4135  builtin_name =
4136  Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccessAndCompatibleReceiver;
4137  }
4138 
4139  // The CallFunctionTemplate builtin requires the {receiver} to be
4140  // an actual JSReceiver, so make sure we do the proper conversion
4141  // first if necessary.
4142  receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4143  simplified()->ConvertReceiver(p.convert_mode()), receiver,
4144  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker()), global_proxy,
4145  effect, control);
4146 
4147  Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), builtin_name);
4148  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
4149  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
4150  argc + 1 /* implicit receiver */, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
4151  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4152  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
4153  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()));
4154  node->ReplaceInput(
4155  1, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function_template_info, broker()));
4156  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2,
4157  jsgraph()->Int32Constant(JSParameterCount(argc)));
4158  node->ReplaceInput(3, receiver); // Update receiver input.
4159  node->ReplaceInput(6 + argc, effect); // Update effect input.
4160  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
4161  return Changed(node);
4162  }
4163  }
4164 
4165  // TODO(turbofan): Consider introducing a JSCallApiCallback operator for
4166  // this and lower it during JSGenericLowering, and unify this with the
4167  // JSNativeContextSpecialization::InlineApiCall method a bit.
4168  compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_callback_data =
4169  function_template_info.callback_data(broker());
4170  // Check if the function has an associated C++ code to execute.
4171  if (!maybe_callback_data.has_value()) {
4172  // TODO(ishell): consider generating "return undefined" for empty function
4173  // instead of failing.
4174  TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "call code for function template info "
4175  << function_template_info);
4176  return NoChange();
4177  }
4178 
4179  // Handles overloaded functions.
4180  FastApiCallFunction c_function = fast_api_call::GetFastApiCallTarget(
4181  broker(), function_template_info, argc);
4182 
4183  if (c_function.address) {
4184  FastApiCallReducerAssembler a(this, node, function_template_info,
4185  c_function, receiver, shared, target, argc,
4186  effect);
4187  Node* fast_call_subgraph = a.ReduceFastApiCall();
4188 
4189  return Replace(fast_call_subgraph);
4190  }
4191 
4192  // Slow call
4193 
4194  bool no_profiling = broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoProfilingProtector();
4195  Callable call_api_callback = Builtins::CallableFor(
4196  isolate(), no_profiling ? Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling
4197  : Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized);
4198  CallInterfaceDescriptor cid = call_api_callback.descriptor();
4199  auto call_descriptor =
4200  Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(graph()->zone(), cid, argc + 1 /*
4201  implicit receiver */, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
4202  ApiFunction api_function(function_template_info.callback(broker()));
4203  ExternalReference function_reference = ExternalReference::Create(
4204  &api_function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
4205 
4206  Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateInlinedApiFunctionFrameState(
4207  jsgraph(), shared, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
4208 
4209  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4210  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
4211  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(call_api_callback.code()));
4212  node->ReplaceInput(1, jsgraph()->ExternalConstant(function_reference));
4213  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(argc));
4214  node->InsertInput(
4215  graph()->zone(), 3,
4216  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(function_template_info.object()));
4217  node->ReplaceInput(4, receiver); // Update receiver input.
4218  // 6 + argc is context input.
4219  node->ReplaceInput(5 + argc + 1, continuation_frame_state);
4220  node->ReplaceInput(5 + argc + 2, effect);
4221  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
4222  return Changed(node);
4223 }

4227 // Check whether elements aren't mutated; we play it extremely safe here by
4228 // explicitly checking that {node} is only used by {LoadField} or
4229 // {LoadElement}.
4230 bool IsSafeArgumentsElements(Node* node) {
4231  for (Edge const edge : node->use_edges()) {
4232  if (!NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge)) continue;
4233  if (edge.from()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadField &&
4234  edge.from()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadElement) {
4235  return false;
4236  }
4237  }
4238  return true;
4239 }

4260 Node* JSCallReducer::ConvertHoleToUndefined(Node* value, ElementsKind kind) {
4261  DCHECK(IsHoleyElementsKind(kind));
4262  if (kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
4263 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
4264  return graph()->NewNode(
4265  simplified()->ChangeFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleToTagged(), value);
4266 #else
4267  return graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeFloat64HoleToTagged(), value);
4268 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
4269  }
4270  return graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
4271 }
4272 
4273 void JSCallReducer::CheckIfConstructor(Node* construct) {
4274  JSConstructNode n(construct);
4275  Node* new_target = n.new_target();
4276  Control control = n.control();
4277 
4278  Node* check =
4279  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsConstructor(), new_target);
4280  Node* check_branch =
4281  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
4282  Node* check_fail = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), check_branch);
4283  Node* check_throw = check_fail = graph()->NewNode(
4284  javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
4285  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
4286  static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kNotConstructor)),
4287  new_target, n.context(), n.frame_state(), n.effect(), check_fail);
4288  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), check_branch);
4289  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(construct, control);
4290 
4291  // Rewire potential exception edges.
4292  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
4293  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(construct, &on_exception)) {
4294  // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
4295  Node* if_exception =
4296  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), check_throw, check_fail);
4297  check_fail = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), check_fail);
4298 
4299  // Join the exception edges.
4300  Node* merge =
4301  graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception, on_exception);
4302  Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception,
4303  on_exception, merge);
4304  Node* phi =
4305  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
4306  if_exception, on_exception, merge);
4307  ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
4308  merge->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
4309  ephi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
4310  phi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
4311  }
4312 
4313  // The above %ThrowTypeError runtime call is an unconditional throw,
4314  // making it impossible to return a successful completion in this case. We
4315  // simply connect the successful completion to the graph end.
4316  Node* throw_node =
4317  graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), check_throw, check_fail);
4318  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
4319 }

4321 namespace {
4322 
4323 bool ShouldUseCallICFeedback(Node* node) {
4324  HeapObjectMatcher m(node);
4325  if (m.HasResolvedValue() || m.IsCheckClosure() || m.IsJSCreateClosure()) {
4326  // Don't use CallIC feedback when we know the function
4327  // being called, i.e. either know the closure itself or
4328  // at least the SharedFunctionInfo.
4329  return false;
4330  } else if (m.IsPhi()) {
4331  // Protect against endless loops here.
4332  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
4333  if (control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kLoop ||
4334  control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kDead) {
4335  return true;
4336  }
4337  // Check if {node} is a Phi of nodes which shouldn't
4338  // use CallIC feedback (not looking through loops).
4339  int const value_input_count = m.node()->op()->ValueInputCount();
4340  for (int n = 0; n < value_input_count; ++n) {
4341  if (ShouldUseCallICFeedback(node->InputAt(n))) return true;
4342  }
4343  return false;
4344  }
4345  return true;
4346 }

4348 } // namespace
