4350 Node* JSCallReducer::CheckArrayLength(Node* array, ElementsKind elements_kind,
4351  uint32_t array_length,
4352  const FeedbackSource& feedback_source,
4353  Effect effect, Control control) {
4354  Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4355  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind)),
4356  array, effect, control);
4357  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
4358  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(array_length));
4359  return graph()->NewNode(
4360  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayLengthChanged,
4361  feedback_source),
4362  check, effect, control);
4363 }
4364 
4365 Reduction
4366 JSCallReducer::ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfCreateArguments(
4367  Node* node, Node* arguments_list, int arraylike_or_spread_index,
4368  CallFrequency const& frequency, FeedbackSource const& feedback,
4369  SpeculationMode speculation_mode, CallFeedbackRelation feedback_relation) {
4370  DCHECK_EQ(arguments_list->opcode(), IrOpcode::kJSCreateArguments);
4371 
4372  // Check if {node} is the only value user of {arguments_list} (except for
4373  // value uses in frame states). If not, we give up for now.
4374  for (Edge edge : arguments_list->use_edges()) {
4375  if (!NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge)) continue;
4376  Node* const user = edge.from();
4377  switch (user->opcode()) {
4378  case IrOpcode::kCheckMaps:
4379  case IrOpcode::kFrameState:
4380  case IrOpcode::kStateValues:
4381  case IrOpcode::kReferenceEqual:
4382  case IrOpcode::kReturn:
4383  // Ignore safe uses that definitely don't mess with the arguments.
4384  continue;
4385  case IrOpcode::kLoadField: {
4386  DCHECK_EQ(arguments_list, user->InputAt(0));
4387  FieldAccess const& access = FieldAccessOf(user->op());
4388  if (access.offset == JSArray::kLengthOffset) {
4389  // Ignore uses for arguments#length.
4390  static_assert(
4391  static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
4392  static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset));
4393  static_assert(
4394  static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
4395  static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset));
4396  continue;
4397  } else if (access.offset == JSObject::kElementsOffset) {
4398  // Ignore safe uses for arguments#elements.
4399  if (IsSafeArgumentsElements(user)) continue;
4400  }
4401  break;
4402  }
4403  case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike: {
4404  // Ignore uses as argumentsList input to calls with array like.
4405  JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(user);
4406  if (edge.index() == n.ArgumentIndex(0)) continue;
4407  break;
4408  }
4409  case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike: {
4410  // Ignore uses as argumentsList input to calls with array like.
4411  JSConstructWithArrayLikeNode n(user);
4412  if (edge.index() == n.ArgumentIndex(0)) continue;
4413  break;
4414  }
4415  case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread: {
4416  // Ignore uses as spread input to calls with spread.
4417  JSCallWithSpreadNode n(user);
4418  if (edge.index() == n.LastArgumentIndex()) continue;
4419  break;
4420  }
4421  case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread: {
4422  // Ignore uses as spread input to construct with spread.
4423  JSConstructWithSpreadNode n(user);
4424  if (edge.index() == n.LastArgumentIndex()) continue;
4425  break;
4426  }
4427  default:
4428  break;
4429  }
4430  // We cannot currently reduce the {node} to something better than what
4431  // it already is, but we might be able to do something about the {node}
4432  // later, so put it on the waitlist and try again during finalization.
4433  waitlist_.insert(node);
4434  return NoChange();
4435  }
4436 
4437  // Get to the actual frame state from which to extract the arguments;
4438  // we can only optimize this in case the {node} was already inlined into
4439  // some other function (and same for the {arguments_list}).
4440  CreateArgumentsType const type = CreateArgumentsTypeOf(arguments_list->op());
4441  FrameState frame_state =
4442  FrameState{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(arguments_list)};
4443 
4444  int formal_parameter_count;
4445  {
4446  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
4447  if (!frame_state.frame_state_info().shared_info().ToHandle(&shared)) {
4448  return NoChange();
4449  }
4450  formal_parameter_count =
4451  MakeRef(broker(), shared)
4452  .internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver_deprecated();
4453  }
4454 
4455  if (type == CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments) {
4456  // Mapped arguments (sloppy mode) that are aliased can only be handled
4457  // here if there's no side-effect between the {node} and the {arg_array}.
4458  // TODO(turbofan): Further relax this constraint.
4459  if (formal_parameter_count != 0) {
4460  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
4461  if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect,
4462  arguments_list)) {
4463  return NoChange();
4464  }
4465  }
4466  }
4467 
4468  // For call/construct with spread, we need to also install a code
4469  // dependency on the array iterator lookup protector cell to ensure
4470  // that no one messed with the %ArrayIteratorPrototype%.next method.
4471  if (IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node)) {
4472  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) return NoChange();
4473  }
4474 
4475  // Remove the {arguments_list} input from the {node}.
4476  node->RemoveInput(arraylike_or_spread_index);
4477 
4478  // The index of the first relevant parameter. Only non-zero when looking at
4479  // rest parameters, in which case it is set to the index of the first rest
4480  // parameter.
4481  const int start_index = (type == CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter)
4482  ? formal_parameter_count
4483  : 0;
4484 
4485  // After removing the arraylike or spread object, the argument count is:
4486  int argc =
4487  arraylike_or_spread_index - JSCallOrConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex();
4488  // Check if are spreading to inlined arguments or to the arguments of
4489  // the outermost function.
4490  if (frame_state.outer_frame_state()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState) {
4491  Operator const* op;
4492  if (IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) {
4493  static constexpr int kTargetAndReceiver = 2;
4494  op = javascript()->CallForwardVarargs(argc + kTargetAndReceiver,
4495  start_index);
4496  } else {
4497  static constexpr int kTargetAndNewTarget = 2;
4498  op = javascript()->ConstructForwardVarargs(argc + kTargetAndNewTarget,
4499  start_index);
4500  }
4501  node->RemoveInput(JSCallOrConstructNode::FeedbackVectorIndexForArgc(argc));
4502  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, op);
4503  return Changed(node);
4504  }
4505  // Get to the actual frame state from which to extract the arguments;
4506  // we can only optimize this in case the {node} was already inlined into
4507  // some other function (and same for the {arg_array}).
4508  FrameState outer_state{frame_state.outer_frame_state()};
4509  FrameStateInfo outer_info = outer_state.frame_state_info();
4510  if (outer_info.type() == FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments) {
4511  // Need to take the parameters from the inlined extra arguments frame state.
4512  frame_state = outer_state;
4513  }
4514  // Add the actual parameters to the {node}, skipping the receiver.
4515  StateValuesAccess parameters_access(frame_state.parameters());
4516  for (auto it = parameters_access.begin_without_receiver_and_skip(start_index);
4517  !it.done(); ++it) {
4518  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(it.node());
4519  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(),
4520  JSCallOrConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(argc++), it.node());
4521  }
4522 
4523  if (IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) {
4524  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4525  node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(argc), frequency,
4526  feedback, ConvertReceiverMode::kAny,
4527  speculation_mode, feedback_relation));
4528  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4529  } else {
4530  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4531  node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(argc),
4532  frequency, feedback));
4533 
4534  // Check whether the given new target value is a constructor function. The
4535  // replacement {JSConstruct} operator only checks the passed target value
4536  // but relies on the new target value to be implicitly valid.
4537  CheckIfConstructor(node);
4538  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
4539  }
4540 }
4541 
4542 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
4543  Node* node, int argument_count, int arraylike_or_spread_index,
4544  CallFrequency const& frequency, FeedbackSource const& feedback_source,
4545  SpeculationMode speculation_mode, CallFeedbackRelation feedback_relation,
4546  Node* target, Effect effect, Control control) {
4547  DCHECK(IsCallOrConstructWithArrayLike(node) ||
4548  IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node));
4549  DCHECK_IMPLIES(speculation_mode == SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation,
4550  feedback_source.IsValid());
4551 
4552  // Let's not add instructions to the graph (like e.g., CheckIfConstructor
4553  // does) if the resulting call might be dead.
4554  if (feedback_source.IsValid()) {
4555  ProcessedFeedback const& call_feedback =
4556  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
4557  if (call_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
4558  return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
4559  node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCall);
4560  }
4561  }
4562 
4563  Node* arguments_list =
4564  NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, arraylike_or_spread_index);
4565 
4566  if (arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateArguments) {
4567  return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfCreateArguments(
4568  node, arguments_list, arraylike_or_spread_index, frequency,
4569  feedback_source, speculation_mode, feedback_relation);
4570  }
4571 
4572  if (!v8_flags.turbo_optimize_apply) return NoChange();
4573 
4574  // Optimization of construct nodes not supported yet.
4575  if (!IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) return NoChange();
4576 
4577  // Avoid deoptimization loops.
4578  if (speculation_mode != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) return NoChange();
4579 
4580  // Only optimize with array literals.
4581  if (arguments_list->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateLiteralArray &&
4582  arguments_list->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray) {
4583  return NoChange();
4584  }
4585 
4586  // For call/construct with spread, we need to also install a code
4587  // dependency on the array iterator lookup protector cell to ensure
4588  // that no one messed with the %ArrayIteratorPrototype%.next method.
4589  if (IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node)) {
4590  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) return NoChange();
4591  }
4592 
4593  if (arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray) {
4594  if (generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread_.count(node)) {
4595  return NoChange(); // Avoid infinite recursion.
4596  }
4597  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
4598  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceJSCallWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfEmpty(
4599  &generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread_);
4600  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
4601  }
4602 
4603  DCHECK_EQ(arguments_list->opcode(), IrOpcode::kJSCreateLiteralArray);
4604 
4605  // Find array length and elements' kind from the feedback's allocation
4606  // site's boilerplate JSArray.
4607  JSCreateLiteralOpNode args_node(arguments_list);
4608  CreateLiteralParameters const& args_params = args_node.Parameters();
4609  const FeedbackSource& array_feedback = args_params.feedback();
4610  const ProcessedFeedback& feedback =
4611  broker()->GetFeedbackForArrayOrObjectLiteral(array_feedback);
4612  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
4613 
4614  AllocationSiteRef site = feedback.AsLiteral().value();
4615  if (!site.boilerplate(broker()).has_value()) return NoChange();
4616 
4617  JSArrayRef boilerplate_array = site.boilerplate(broker())->AsJSArray();
4618  int const array_length =
4619  boilerplate_array.GetBoilerplateLength(broker()).AsSmi();
4620  SBXCHECK_GE(array_length, 0);
4621 
4622  // We'll replace the arguments_list input with {array_length} element loads.
4623  uint32_t new_argument_count =
4624  static_cast<uint32_t>(array_length) + argument_count - 1;
4625 
4626  // Do not optimize calls with a large number of arguments.
4627  // Arbitrarily sets the limit to 32 arguments.
4628  const uint32_t kMaxArityForOptimizedFunctionApply = 32;
4629  if (new_argument_count > kMaxArityForOptimizedFunctionApply) {
4630  return NoChange();
4631  }
4632 
4633  // Determine the array's map.
4634  MapRef array_map = boilerplate_array.map(broker());
4635  if (!array_map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
4636  return NoChange();
4637  }
4638 
4639  // Check and depend on NoElementsProtector.
4640  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
4641  return NoChange();
4642  }
4643 
4644  // Remove the {arguments_list} node which will be replaced by a sequence of
4645  // LoadElement nodes.
4646  node->RemoveInput(arraylike_or_spread_index);
4647 
4648  // Speculate on that array's map is still equal to the dynamic map of
4649  // arguments_list; generate a map check.
4650  effect = graph()->NewNode(
4651  simplified()->CheckMaps(CheckMapsFlag::kNone, ZoneRefSet<Map>(array_map),
4652  feedback_source),
4653  arguments_list, effect, control);
4654 
4655  // Speculate on that array's length being equal to the dynamic length of
4656  // arguments_list; generate a deopt check.
4657  ElementsKind elements_kind = array_map.elements_kind();
4658  effect = CheckArrayLength(arguments_list, elements_kind, array_length,
4659  feedback_source, effect, control);
4660 
4661  // Generate N element loads to replace the {arguments_list} node with a set
4662  // of arguments loaded from it.
4663  Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4664  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
4665  arguments_list, effect, control);
4666  for (int i = 0; i < array_length; i++) {
4667  // Load the i-th element from the array.
4668  Node* index = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(i);
4669  Node* load = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4670  simplified()->LoadElement(
4671  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(elements_kind)),
4672  elements, index, effect, control);
4673 
4674  // In "holey" arrays some arguments might be missing and we pass
4675  // 'undefined' instead.
4676  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
4677  load = ConvertHoleToUndefined(load, elements_kind);
4678  }
4679 
4680  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arraylike_or_spread_index + i, load);
4681  }
4682 
4683  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4684  node, javascript()->Call(
4685  JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(static_cast<int>(new_argument_count)),
4686  frequency, feedback_source, ConvertReceiverMode::kAny,
4687  speculation_mode, CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4688  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4689  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4690 }
4691 
4692 bool JSCallReducer::IsBuiltinOrApiFunction(JSFunctionRef function) const {
4693  // TODO(neis): Add a way to check if function template info isn't serialized
4694  // and add a warning in such cases. Currently we can't tell if function
4695  // template info doesn't exist or wasn't serialized.
4696  return function.shared(broker()).HasBuiltinId() ||
4697  function.shared(broker()).function_template_info(broker()).has_value();
4698 }
4699 
4700 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCall(Node* node) {
4701  if (broker()->StackHasOverflowed()) return NoChange();
4702 
4703  JSCallNode n(node);
4704  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4705  Node* target = n.target();
4706  Effect effect = n.effect();
4707  Control control = n.control();
4708  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
4709 
4710  auto NoChangeOrSoftDeopt = [&]() {
4711  if (p.feedback().IsValid()) {
4712  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
4713  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
4714  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
4715  return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
4716  node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCall);
4717  }
4718  }
4719  return NoChange();
4720  };
4721 
4722  // Try to specialize JSCall {node}s with constant {target}s.
4723  HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
4724  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
4725  ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
4726  if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
4727  JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
4728 
4729  // Don't inline cross native context.
4730  if (!function.native_context(broker()).equals(native_context())) {
4731  return NoChange();
4732  }
4733 
4734  Reduction res = ReduceJSCall(node, function.shared(broker()));
4735  if (!res.Changed()) return NoChangeOrSoftDeopt();
4736  return res;
4737  } else if (target_ref.IsJSBoundFunction()) {
4738  JSBoundFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSBoundFunction();
4739  ObjectRef bound_this = function.bound_this(broker());
4740  ConvertReceiverMode const convert_mode =
4741  bound_this.IsNullOrUndefined()
4742  ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined
4743  : ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
4744 
4745  // TODO(jgruber): Inline this block below once TryGet is guaranteed to
4746  // succeed.
4747  FixedArrayRef bound_arguments = function.bound_arguments(broker());
4748  const uint32_t bound_arguments_length = bound_arguments.length();
4749  if (arity + bound_arguments_length + /* receiver */ 1 >
4750  Code::kMaxArguments) {
4751  return NoChange();
4752  }
4753  static constexpr int kInlineSize = 16; // Arbitrary.
4754  base::SmallVector<Node*, kInlineSize> args;
4755  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4756  OptionalObjectRef maybe_arg = bound_arguments.TryGet(broker(), i);
4757  if (!maybe_arg.has_value()) {
4758  TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "bound argument");
4759  return NoChangeOrSoftDeopt();
4760  }
4761  args.emplace_back(
4762  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(maybe_arg.value(), broker()));
4763  }
4764 
4765  // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]] and [[BoundThis]].
4766  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(
4767  node,
4768  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function.bound_target_function(broker()),
4769  broker()),
4770  JSCallNode::TargetIndex());
4771  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(
4772  node, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(bound_this, broker()),
4773  JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex());
4774 
4775  // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4776  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4777  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), i + 2, args[i]);
4778  arity++;
4779  }
4780 
4781  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4782  node,
4783  javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
4784  p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
4785  CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4786 
4787  // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4788  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4789  }
4790 
4791  // Don't mess with other {node}s that have a constant {target}.
4792  // TODO(bmeurer): Also support proxies here.
4793  return NoChangeOrSoftDeopt();
4794  }
4795 
4796  // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateClosure operation, we can
4797  // just immediately try to inline based on the SharedFunctionInfo,
4798  // since TurboFan generally doesn't inline cross-context, and hence
4799  // the {target} must have the same native context as the call site.
4800  // Same if the {target} is the result of a CheckClosure operation.
4801  if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateClosure) {
4802  CreateClosureParameters const& params =
4803  JSCreateClosureNode{target}.Parameters();
4804  Reduction res = ReduceJSCall(node, params.shared_info());
4805  if (!res.Changed()) return NoChangeOrSoftDeopt();
4806  return res;
4807  } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCheckClosure) {
4808  FeedbackCellRef cell = MakeRef(broker(), FeedbackCellOf(target->op()));
4809  OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared = cell.shared_function_info(broker());
4810  if (!shared.has_value()) {
4811  TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "Unable to reduce JSCall. FeedbackCell "
4812  << cell << " has no FeedbackVector");
4813  return NoChangeOrSoftDeopt();
4814  }
4815  Reduction res = ReduceJSCall(node, *shared);
4816  if (!res.Changed()) return NoChangeOrSoftDeopt();
4817  return res;
4818  }
4819 
4820  // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateBoundFunction operation,
4821  // we can just fold the construction and call the bound target
4822  // function directly instead.
4823  if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateBoundFunction) {
4824  Node* bound_target_function = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 0);
4825  Node* bound_this = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 1);
4826  uint32_t const bound_arguments_length =
4827  static_cast<int>(CreateBoundFunctionParametersOf(target->op()).arity());
4828 
4829  // Patch the {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]] and [[BoundThis]].
4830  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, bound_target_function,
4831  n.TargetIndex());
4832  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, bound_this, n.ReceiverIndex());
4833 
4834  // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4835  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4836  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 2 + i);
4837  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), value);
4838  arity++;
4839  }
4840 
4841  // Update the JSCall operator on {node}.
4842  ConvertReceiverMode const convert_mode =
4843  NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), bound_this, effect)
4844  ? ConvertReceiverMode::kAny
4845  : ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
4846  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4847  node,
4848  javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
4849  p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
4850  CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4851 
4852  // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4853  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4854  }
4855 
4856  if (!ShouldUseCallICFeedback(target) ||
4857  p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated ||
4858  !p.feedback().IsValid()) {
4859  return NoChange();
4860  }
4861 
4862  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
4863  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
4864  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
4865  return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
4866  node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCall);
4867  }
4868 
4869  OptionalHeapObjectRef feedback_target;
4870  if (p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget) {
4871  feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
4872  } else {
4873  DCHECK_EQ(p.feedback_relation(), CallFeedbackRelation::kReceiver);
4874  feedback_target = native_context().function_prototype_apply(broker());
4875  }
4876 
4877  if (feedback_target.has_value() &&
4878  feedback_target->map(broker()).is_callable()) {
4879  Node* target_function =
4880  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*feedback_target, broker());
4881 
4882  // Check that the {target} is still the {target_function}.
4883  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
4884  target_function);
4885  effect = graph()->NewNode(
4886  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
4887  effect, control);
4888 
4889  // Specialize the JSCall node to the {target_function}.
4890  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_function, n.TargetIndex());
4891  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4892 
4893  // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4894  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4895  } else if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->IsFeedbackCell()) {
4896  FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell = feedback_target.value().AsFeedbackCell();
4897  // TODO(neis): This check seems unnecessary.
4898  if (feedback_cell.feedback_vector(broker()).has_value()) {
4899  // Check that {target} is a closure with given {feedback_cell},
4900  // which uniquely identifies a given function inside a native context.
4901  Node* target_closure = effect =
4902  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckClosure(feedback_cell.object()),
4903  target, effect, control);
4904 
4905  // Specialize the JSCall node to the {target_closure}.
4906  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_closure, n.TargetIndex());
4907  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4908 
4909  // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4910  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4911  }
4912  }
4913  return NoChange();
4914 }
4915 
4916 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCall(Node* node,
4917  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
4918  JSCallNode n(node);
4919  Node* target = n.target();
4920 
4921  // Do not reduce calls to functions with break points.
4922  // If this state changes during background compilation, the compilation
4923  // job will be aborted from the main thread (see
4924  // Debug::PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution()).
4925  if (shared.HasBreakInfo(broker())) return NoChange();
4926 
4927  // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
4928  // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
4929  if (IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
4930  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, target);
4931  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4932  node, javascript()->CallRuntime(
4933  Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError, 1));
4934  return Changed(node);
4935  }
4936 
4937  // Check for known builtin functions.
4938 
4939  Builtin builtin =
4940  shared.HasBuiltinId() ? shared.builtin_id() : Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
4941  switch (builtin) {
4942  case Builtin::kArrayConstructor:
4943  return ReduceArrayConstructor(node);
4944  case Builtin::kBooleanConstructor:
4945  return ReduceBooleanConstructor(node);
4946  case Builtin::kFunctionPrototypeApply:
4947  return ReduceFunctionPrototypeApply(node);
4948  case Builtin::kFastFunctionPrototypeBind:
4949  return ReduceFunctionPrototypeBind(node);
4950  case Builtin::kFunctionPrototypeCall:
4951  return ReduceFunctionPrototypeCall(node);
4952  case Builtin::kFunctionPrototypeHasInstance:
4953  return ReduceFunctionPrototypeHasInstance(node);
4954  case Builtin::kObjectConstructor:
4955  return ReduceObjectConstructor(node);
4956  case Builtin::kObjectCreate:
4957  return ReduceObjectCreate(node);
4958  case Builtin::kObjectGetPrototypeOf:
4959  return ReduceObjectGetPrototypeOf(node);
4960  case Builtin::kObjectIs:
4961  return ReduceObjectIs(node);
4962  case Builtin::kObjectPrototypeGetProto:
4963  return ReduceObjectPrototypeGetProto(node);
4964  case Builtin::kObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty:
4965  return ReduceObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty(node);
4966  case Builtin::kObjectPrototypeIsPrototypeOf:
4967  return ReduceObjectPrototypeIsPrototypeOf(node);
4968  case Builtin::kReflectApply:
4969  return ReduceReflectApply(node);
4970  case Builtin::kReflectConstruct:
4971  return ReduceReflectConstruct(node);
4972  case Builtin::kReflectGet:
4973  return ReduceReflectGet(node);
4974  case Builtin::kReflectGetPrototypeOf:
4975  return ReduceReflectGetPrototypeOf(node);
4976  case Builtin::kReflectHas:
4977  return ReduceReflectHas(node);
4978  case Builtin::kArrayForEach:
4979  return ReduceArrayForEach(node, shared);
4980  case Builtin::kArrayMap:
4981  return ReduceArrayMap(node, shared);
4982  case Builtin::kArrayFilter:
4983  return ReduceArrayFilter(node, shared);
4984  case Builtin::kArrayReduce:
4985  return ReduceArrayReduce(node, shared);
4986  case Builtin::kArrayReduceRight:
4987  return ReduceArrayReduceRight(node, shared);
4988  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeFind:
4989  return ReduceArrayFind(node, shared);
4990  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeFindIndex:
4991  return ReduceArrayFindIndex(node, shared);
4992  case Builtin::kArrayEvery:
4993  return ReduceArrayEvery(node, shared);
4994  case Builtin::kArrayIndexOf:
4995  return ReduceArrayIndexOf(node);
4996  case Builtin::kArrayIncludes:
4997  return ReduceArrayIncludes(node);
4998  case Builtin::kArraySome:
4999  return ReduceArraySome(node, shared);
5000  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeAt:
5001  return ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(node);
5002  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypePush:
5003  return ReduceArrayPrototypePush(node);
5004  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypePop:
5005  return ReduceArrayPrototypePop(node);
5006  // TODO(v8:14409): The current implementation of the inlined
5007  // ArrayPrototypeShift version doesn't seem to be beneficial and even
5008  // counter-productive at least for Object ElementsKinds. Disable it until
5009  // improvements/better heuristics have been implemented.
5010  // case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeShift:
5011  // return ReduceArrayPrototypeShift(node);
5012  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeSlice:
5013  return ReduceArrayPrototypeSlice(node);
5014  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeEntries:
5015  return ReduceArrayIterator(node, ArrayIteratorKind::kArrayLike,
5016  IterationKind::kEntries);
5017  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeKeys:
5018  return ReduceArrayIterator(node, ArrayIteratorKind::kArrayLike,
5019  IterationKind::kKeys);
5020  case Builtin::kArrayPrototypeValues:
5021  return ReduceArrayIterator(node, ArrayIteratorKind::kArrayLike,
5022  IterationKind::kValues);
5023  case Builtin::kArrayIteratorPrototypeNext:
5024  return ReduceArrayIteratorPrototypeNext(node);
5025  case Builtin::kArrayIsArray:
5026  return ReduceArrayIsArray(node);
5027  case Builtin::kArrayBufferIsView:
5028  return ReduceArrayBufferIsView(node);
5029  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetByteLength:
5030  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
5031  return ReduceArrayBufferViewByteLengthAccessor(node, JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
5032  builtin);
5033  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetByteOffset:
5034  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
5035  return ReduceArrayBufferViewByteOffsetAccessor(node, JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
5036  builtin);
5037  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetUint8:
5038  return ReduceDataViewAccess(node, DataViewAccess::kGet,
5039  ExternalArrayType::kExternalUint8Array);
5040  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetInt8:

5341 
5342 TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceJSCallWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfEmpty(
5343  std::unordered_set<Node*>* generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread) {
5344  DCHECK_EQ(generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread->count(node_ptr()), 0);
5345  JSCallWithArrayLikeOrSpreadNode n(node_ptr());
5346  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5347  TNode<Object> arguments_list = n.LastArgument();
5348  DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<Node*>(arguments_list)->opcode(),
5349  IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray);
5350 
5351  // Check that arguments_list's prototype is still an array prototype.
5352  TNode<Map> map = LoadMap(TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(arguments_list));
5353  TNode<HeapObject> proto = TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(
5354  LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapPrototype(), map));
5355  TNode<HeapObject> initial_array_prototype =
5356  HeapConstant(broker()
5357  ->target_native_context()
5358  .initial_array_prototype(broker())
5359  .object());
5360  TNode<Boolean> check = ReferenceEqual(proto, initial_array_prototype);
5361  CheckIf(check, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, p.feedback());
5362 
5363  // Turn the JSCallWithArrayLike or JSCallWithSpread roughly into:
5364  //
5365  // "arguments_list array is still empty?"
5366  // |
5367  // |
5368  // Branch
5369  // / \
5370  // / \
5371  // IfTrue IfFalse
5372  // | |
5373  // | |
5374  // JSCall JSCallWithArrayLike/JSCallWithSpread
5375  // \ /
5376  // \ /
5377  // Merge
5378 
5379  TNode<Number> length = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
5380  LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(NO_ELEMENTS), arguments_list));
5381  return SelectIf<Object>(NumberEqual(length, ZeroConstant()))
5382  .Then([&]() {
5383  TNode<Object> call = CopyNode();
5384  static_cast<Node*>(call)->RemoveInput(n.LastArgumentIndex());
5385  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5386  call, javascript()->Call(p.arity() - 1, p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
5387  p.convert_mode(), p.speculation_mode(),
5388  p.feedback_relation()));
5389  return call;
5390  })
5391  .Else([&]() {
5392  TNode<Object> call = CopyNode();
5393  generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread->insert(call);
5394  return call;
5395  })
5396  .ExpectFalse()
5397  .Value();
5398 }
5399 
5400 namespace {
5401 
5402 // Check if the target is a class constructor.
5403 // We need to check all cases where the target will be typed as Function
5404 // to prevent later optimizations from using the CallFunction trampoline,
5405 // skipping the instance type check.
5406 bool TargetIsClassConstructor(Node* node, JSHeapBroker* broker) {
5407  Node* target = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
5408  OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared;
5409  HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
5410  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
5411  ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker);
5412  if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
5413  JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
5414  shared = function.shared(broker);
5415  }
5416  } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateClosure) {
5417  CreateClosureParameters const& ccp =
5418  JSCreateClosureNode{target}.Parameters();
5419  shared = ccp.shared_info();
5420  } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCheckClosure) {
5421  FeedbackCellRef cell = MakeRef(broker, FeedbackCellOf(target->op()));
5422  shared = cell.shared_function_info(broker);
5423  }
5424 
5425  if (shared.has_value() && IsClassConstructor(shared->kind())) return true;
5426 
5427  return false;
5428 }
5429 
5430 } // namespace
5431 
5432 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(Node* node) {
5433  JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
5434  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5435  DCHECK_EQ(p.arity_without_implicit_args(), 1); // The arraylike object.
5436  // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
5437  // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
5438  if (TargetIsClassConstructor(node, broker())) {
5439  return NoChange();
5440  }
5441 
5442  std::optional<Reduction> maybe_result =
5443  TryReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(node);
5444  if (maybe_result.has_value()) {
5445  return maybe_result.value();
5446  }
5447 
5448  return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
5449  node, n.ArgumentCount(), n.LastArgumentIndex(), p.frequency(),
5450  p.feedback(), p.speculation_mode(), p.feedback_relation(), n.target(),
5451  n.effect(), n.control());
5452 }
5453 
5454 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCallWithSpread(Node* node) {
5455  JSCallWithSpreadNode n(node);
5456  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5457  DCHECK_GE(p.arity_without_implicit_args(), 1); // At least the spread.
5458  // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
5459  // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
5460  if (TargetIsClassConstructor(node, broker())) {
5461  return NoChange();
5462  }
5463  return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
5464  node, n.ArgumentCount(), n.LastArgumentIndex(), p.frequency(),
5465  p.feedback(), p.speculation_mode(), p.feedback_relation(), n.target(),
5466  n.effect(), n.control());
5467 }
5468 
5469 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstruct(Node* node) {
5470  if (broker()->StackHasOverflowed()) return NoChange();
5471 
5472  JSConstructNode n(node);
5473  ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5474  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
5475  Node* target = n.target();
5476  Node* new_target = n.new_target();
5477  Effect effect = n.effect();
5478  Control control = n.control();
5479 
5480  if (p.feedback().IsValid()) {
5481  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
5482  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
5483  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
5484  return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
5485  node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForConstruct);
5486  }
5487 
5488  OptionalHeapObjectRef feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
5489  if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->IsAllocationSite()) {
5490  // The feedback is an AllocationSite, which means we have called the
5491  // Array function and collected transition (and pretenuring) feedback
5492  // for the resulting arrays. This has to be kept in sync with the
5493  // implementation in Ignition.
5494 
5495  Node* array_function = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
5496  native_context().array_function(broker()), broker());
5497 
5498  // Check that the {target} is still the {array_function}.
5499  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
5500  array_function);
5501  effect = graph()->NewNode(
5502  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
5503  effect, control);
5504 
5505  // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
5506  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
5507  static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1);
5508  node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), array_function);
5509  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5510  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5511  node,
5512  javascript()->CreateArray(arity, feedback_target->AsAllocationSite(),
5513  FeedbackSource()));
5514  return Changed(node);
5515  } else if (feedback_target.has_value() &&
5516  !HeapObjectMatcher(new_target).HasResolvedValue() &&
5517  feedback_target->map(broker()).is_constructor()) {
5518  Node* new_target_feedback =
5519  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*feedback_target, broker());
5520 
5521  // Check that the {new_target} is still the {new_target_feedback}.
5522  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), new_target,
5523  new_target_feedback);
5524  effect = graph()->NewNode(
5525  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
5526  effect, control);
5527 
5528  // Specialize the JSConstruct node to the {new_target_feedback}.
5529  node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), new_target_feedback);
5530  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
5531  if (target == new_target) {
5532  node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), new_target_feedback);
5533  }
5534 
5535  // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
5536  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5537  }
5538  }
5539 
5540  // Try to specialize JSConstruct {node}s with constant {target}s.
5541  HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
5542  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
5543  HeapObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
5544 
5545  // Raise a TypeError if the {target} is not a constructor.
5546  if (!target_ref.map(broker()).is_constructor()) {
5547  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, target);
5548  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
5549  javascript()->CallRuntime(
5550  Runtime::kThrowConstructedNonConstructable));
5551  return Changed(node);
5552  }
5553 
5554  if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
5555  JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
5556 
5557  // Do not reduce constructors with break points.
5558  // If this state changes during background compilation, the compilation
5559  // job will be aborted from the main thread (see
5560  // Debug::PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution()).
5561  SharedFunctionInfoRef sfi = function.shared(broker());
5562  if (sfi.HasBreakInfo(broker())) return NoChange();
5563 
5564  // Don't inline cross native context.
5565  if (!function.native_context(broker()).equals(native_context())) {
5566  return NoChange();
5567  }
5568 
5569  // Check for known builtin functions.
5570  Builtin builtin =
5571  sfi.HasBuiltinId() ? sfi.builtin_id() : Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
5572  switch (builtin) {
5573  case Builtin::kArrayConstructor: {
5574  // TODO(bmeurer): Deal with Array subclasses here.
5575  // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
5576  static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1);
5577  node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), new_target);
5578  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5579  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5580  node,
5581  javascript()->CreateArray(arity, std::nullopt, FeedbackSource()));
5582  return Changed(node);
5583  }
5584  case Builtin::kObjectConstructor: {
5585  // If no value is passed, we can immediately lower to a simple
5586  // JSCreate and don't need to do any massaging of the {node}.
5587  if (arity == 0) {
5588  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5589  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Create());
5590  return Changed(node);
5591  }
5592 
5593  // If {target} is not the same as {new_target} (i.e. the Object
5594  // constructor), {value} will be ignored and therefore we can lower
5595  // to {JSCreate}. See https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-object-value.
5596  HeapObjectMatcher mnew_target(new_target);
5597  if (mnew_target.HasResolvedValue() &&
5598  !mnew_target.Ref(broker()).equals(function)) {
5599  // Drop the value inputs.
5600  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5601  for (int i = n.ArgumentCount() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
5602  node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(i));
5603  }
5604  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Create());
5605  return Changed(node);
5606  }
5607  break;
5608  }
5609  case Builtin::kPromiseConstructor:
5610  return ReducePromiseConstructor(node);
5611  case Builtin::kStringConstructor:
5612  return ReduceStringConstructor(node, function);
5613  case Builtin::kTypedArrayConstructor:
5614  return ReduceTypedArrayConstructor(node, function.shared(broker()));
5615  default:
5616  break;
5617  }
5618  } else if (target_ref.IsJSBoundFunction()) {
5619  JSBoundFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSBoundFunction();
5620  JSReceiverRef bound_target_function =
5621  function.bound_target_function(broker());
5622  FixedArrayRef bound_arguments = function.bound_arguments(broker());
5623  const uint32_t bound_arguments_length = bound_arguments.length();
5624 
5625  // TODO(jgruber): Inline this block below once TryGet is guaranteed to
5626  // succeed.
5627  static constexpr int kInlineSize = 16; // Arbitrary.
5628  base::SmallVector<Node*, kInlineSize> args;
5629  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
5630  OptionalObjectRef maybe_arg = bound_arguments.TryGet(broker(), i);
5631  if (!maybe_arg.has_value()) {
5632  TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "bound argument");
5633  return NoChange();
5634  }
5635  args.emplace_back(
5636  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(maybe_arg.value(), broker()));
5637  }
5638 
5639  // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]].
5640  node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
5641  bound_target_function, broker()));
5642 
5643  // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]]
5644  // as new.target if {new_target} equals {target}.
5645  if (target == new_target) {
5646  node->ReplaceInput(
5647  n.NewTargetIndex(),
5648  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(bound_target_function, broker()));
5649  } else {
5650  node->ReplaceInput(
5651  n.NewTargetIndex(),
5652  graph()->NewNode(
5653  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
5654  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
5655  new_target),
5656  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(bound_target_function, broker()),
5657  new_target));
5658  }
5659 
5660  // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
5661  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
5662  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), args[i]);
5663  arity++;
5664  }
5665 
5666  // Update the JSConstruct operator on {node}.
5667  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5668  node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arity),
5669  p.frequency(), FeedbackSource()));
5670 
5671  // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
5672  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5673  }
5674 
5675  // TODO(bmeurer): Also support optimizing proxies here.
5676  }
5677 
5678  // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateBoundFunction operation,
5679  // we can just fold the construction and construct the bound target
5680  // function directly instead.
5681  if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateBoundFunction) {
5682  Node* bound_target_function = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 0);
5683  uint32_t const bound_arguments_length =
5684  static_cast<int>(CreateBoundFunctionParametersOf(target->op()).arity());
5685 
5686  // Patch the {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]].
5687  node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), bound_target_function);
5688 
5689  // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]]
5690  // as new.target if {new_target} equals {target}.
5691  if (target == new_target) {
5692  node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), bound_target_function);
5693  } else {
5694  node->ReplaceInput(
5695  n.NewTargetIndex(),
5696  graph()->NewNode(common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
5697  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
5698  target, new_target),
5699  bound_target_function, new_target));
5700  }
5701 
5702  // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
5703  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
5704  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 2 + i);
5705  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), value);
5706  arity++;
5707  }
5708 
5709  // Update the JSConstruct operator on {node}.
5710  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5711  node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arity),
5712  p.frequency(), FeedbackSource()));
5713 
5714  // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
5715  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5716  }
5717 
5718  return NoChange();
5719 }
5720 
5721 // ES #sec-string.prototype.indexof
5722 // ES #sec-string.prototype.includes
5723 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeIndexOfIncludes(
5724  Node* node, StringIndexOfIncludesVariant variant) {
5725  JSCallNode n(node);
5726  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5727  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
5728  return NoChange();
5729  }
5730 
5731  Effect effect = n.effect();
5732  Control control = n.control();
5733  if (n.ArgumentCount() > 0) {
5734  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5735  Node* new_receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5736  simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), receiver, effect, control);
5737 
5738  Node* search_string = n.Argument(0);
5739  Node* new_search_string = effect =
5740  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), search_string,
5741  effect, control);
5742 
5743  Node* new_position = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
5744  if (n.ArgumentCount() > 1) {
5745  Node* position = n.Argument(1);
5746  new_position = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5747  simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), position, effect, control);
5748 
5749  Node* receiver_length =
5750  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), new_receiver);
5751  new_position = graph()->NewNode(
5752  simplified()->NumberMin(),
5753  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMax(), new_position,
5754  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5755  receiver_length);
5756  }
5757 
5758  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
5759  RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
5760  node->ReplaceInput(0, new_receiver);
5761  node->ReplaceInput(1, new_search_string);
5762  node->ReplaceInput(2, new_position);
5763  node->TrimInputCount(3);
5764  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringIndexOf());
5765 
5766  if (variant == StringIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIndexOf) {
5767  return Changed(node);
5768  } else {
5769  DCHECK(variant == StringIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIncludes);
5770  Node* result =
5771  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BooleanNot(),
5772  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), node,
5773  jsgraph()->SmiConstant(-1)));
5774  return Replace(result);
5775  }
5776  }
5777  return NoChange();
5778 }

5808 // ES #sec-string.prototype.substr
5809 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstr(Node* node) {
5810  JSCallNode n(node);
5811  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5812  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
5813  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
5814  return NoChange();
5815  }
5816 
5817  Effect effect = n.effect();
5818  Control control = n.control();
5819  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5820  Node* start = n.Argument(0);
5821  Node* end = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
5822 
5823  receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()),
5824  receiver, effect, control);
5825 
5826  start = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), start,
5827  effect, control);
5828 
5829  Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
5830 
5831  // Replace {end} argument with {length} if it is undefined.
5832  {
5833  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), end,
5834  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
5835  Node* branch =
5836  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
5837 
5838  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
5839  Node* etrue = effect;
5840  Node* vtrue = length;
5841 
5842  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
5843  Node* efalse = effect;
5844  Node* vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
5845  simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), end, efalse, if_false);
5846 
5847  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
5848  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
5849  end = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5850  vtrue, vfalse, control);
5851  }
5852 
5853  Node* initStart = graph()->NewNode(
5854  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kFalse),
5855  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), start,
5856  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5857  graph()->NewNode(
5858  simplified()->NumberMax(),
5859  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), length, start),
5860  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5861  start);
5862  // The select above guarantees that initStart is non-negative, but
5863  // our typer can't figure that out yet.
5864  initStart = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5865  common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()), initStart, effect, control);
5866 
5867  Node* resultLength = graph()->NewNode(
5868  simplified()->NumberMin(),
5869  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMax(), end,
5870  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5871  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), length, initStart));
5872 
5873  // The the select below uses {resultLength} only if {resultLength > 0},
5874  // but our typer can't figure that out yet.
5875  Node* to = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5876  common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()),
5877  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), initStart, resultLength),
5878  effect, control);
5879 
5880  Node* result_string = nullptr;
5881  // Return empty string if {from} is smaller than {to}.
5882  {
5883  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(),
5884  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), resultLength);
5885 
5886  Node* branch =
5887  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
5888 
5889  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
5890  Node* etrue = effect;
5891  Node* vtrue = etrue =
5892  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringSubstring(), receiver, initStart,
5893  to, etrue, if_true);
5894 
5895  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
5896  Node* efalse = effect;
5897  Node* vfalse = jsgraph()->EmptyStringConstant();
5898 
5899  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
5900  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
5901  result_string =
5902  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5903  vtrue, vfalse, control);
5904  }
5905 
5906  ReplaceWithValue(node, result_string, effect, control);
5907  return Replace(result_string);
5908 }

5932 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstructForwardAllArgs(Node* node) {
5933  JSConstructForwardAllArgsNode n(node);
5934  DCHECK_EQ(n.ArgumentCount(), 0);
5935 
5936  // If this frame is not being inlined, JSConstructForwardAllArgs will be
5937  // lowered later in JSGenericLowering to a builtin call.
5938  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
5939  if (frame_state.outer_frame_state()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState) {
5940  return NoChange();
5941  }
5942 
5943  // Hook up the arguments directly when forwarding arguments of inlined frames.
5944  FrameState outer_state{frame_state.outer_frame_state()};
5945  FrameStateInfo outer_info = outer_state.frame_state_info();
5946  if (outer_info.type() == FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments) {
5947  frame_state = outer_state;
5948  }
5949 
5950  int argc = 0;
5951  StateValuesAccess parameters_access(frame_state.parameters());
5952  for (auto it = parameters_access.begin_without_receiver(); !it.done(); ++it) {
5953  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(it.node());
5954  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(),
5955  JSCallOrConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(argc++), it.node());
5956  }
5957 
5958  ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5959  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5960  node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(argc),
5961  p.frequency(), p.feedback()));
5962  CheckIfConstructor(node);
5963  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5964 }

5966 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReturnReceiver(Node* node) {
5967  JSCallNode n(node);
5968  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5969  ReplaceWithValue(node, receiver);
5970  return Replace(receiver);
5971 }

5973 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
5974  Node* node, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
5975  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall ||
5976  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread ||
5977  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike ||
5978  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstruct ||
5979  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread ||
5980  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike);
5981  if (!(flags() & kBailoutOnUninitialized)) return NoChange();
5982 
5983  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
5984  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
5985  Node* frame_state =
5986  NodeProperties::FindFrameStateBefore(node, jsgraph()->Dead());
5987  Node* deoptimize =
5988  graph()->NewNode(common()->Deoptimize(reason, FeedbackSource()),
5989  frame_state, effect, control);
5990  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), deoptimize);
5991  node->TrimInputCount(0);
5992  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Dead());
5993  return Changed(node);
5994 }
5995 
5996 Node* JSCallReducer::LoadReceiverElementsKind(Node* receiver, Effect* effect,
5997  Control control) {
5998  Node* effect_node = *effect;
5999  Node* receiver_map = effect_node =
6000  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
6001  receiver, effect_node, control);
6002  Node* receiver_bit_field2 = effect_node = graph()->NewNode(
6003  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2()), receiver_map,
6004  effect_node, control);
6005  Node* receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
6006  simplified()->NumberShiftRightLogical(),
6007  graph()->NewNode(
6008  simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), receiver_bit_field2,
6009  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
6010  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
6011  *effect = effect_node;
6012  return receiver_elements_kind;
6013 }
6014 
6015 void JSCallReducer::CheckIfElementsKind(Node* receiver_elements_kind,
6016  ElementsKind kind, Node* control,
6017  Node** if_true, Node** if_false) {
6018  Node* is_packed_kind =
6019  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind,
6020  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(GetPackedElementsKind(kind)));
6021  Node* packed_branch =
6022  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), is_packed_kind, control);
6023  Node* if_packed = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), packed_branch);
6024 
6025  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
6026  Node* if_not_packed = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), packed_branch);
6027  Node* is_holey_kind =
6028  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind,
6029  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(GetHoleyElementsKind(kind)));
6030  Node* holey_branch =
6031  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), is_holey_kind, if_not_packed);
6032  Node* if_holey = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), holey_branch);
6033 
6034  Node* if_not_packed_not_holey =
6035  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), holey_branch);
6036 
6037  *if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_packed, if_holey);
6038  *if_false = if_not_packed_not_holey;
6039  } else {
6040  *if_true = if_packed;
6041  *if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), packed_branch);
6042  }
6043 }
6044 
6045 // ES6 section 23.1.3.1 Array.prototype.at ( )
6046 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(Node* node) {
6047  if (!v8_flags.turbo_inline_array_builtins) return NoChange();
6048 
6049  JSCallNode n(node);
6050  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6051  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6052  return NoChange();
6053  }
6054 
6055  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6056  Effect effect = n.effect();
6057  Control control = n.control();
6058 
6059  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6060  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6061 
6062  // Collecting maps, and checking if a fallback builtin call will be required
6063  // (it is required if at least one map doesn't support fast array iteration).
6064  ZoneVector<MapRef> maps(broker()->zone());
6065  bool needs_fallback_builtin_call = false;
6066  for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
6067  if (map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
6068  maps.push_back(map);
6069  } else {
6070  needs_fallback_builtin_call = true;
6071  }
6072  }
6073 
6074  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6075  control, p.feedback());
6076 
6077  if (maps.empty()) {
6078  // No map in the feedback supports fast iteration. Keeping the builtin call.
6079  return NoChange();
6080  }
6081 
6082  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6083  return NoChange();
6084  }
6085 
6086  IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6087  a.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
6088 
6089  TNode<Object> subgraph =
6090  a.ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(maps, needs_fallback_builtin_call);
6091  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6092 }
6093 
6094 // ES6 section 22.1.3.18 Array.prototype.push ( )
6095 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypePush(Node* node) {
6096  JSCallNode n(node);
6097  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6098  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6099  return NoChange();
6100  }
6101 
6102  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6103  Effect effect = n.effect();
6104  Control control = n.control();
6105 
6106  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6107  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6108  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6109 
6110  std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
6111  if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds, true)) {
6112  return inference.NoChange();
6113  }
6114  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6115  return inference.NoChange();
6116  }
6117 
6118  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6119  control, p.feedback());
6120 
6121  IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6122  a.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
6123 
6124  TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReduceArrayPrototypePush(&inference);
6125  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6126 }

6128 // ES6 section 22.1.3.17 Array.prototype.pop ( )
6129 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypePop(Node* node) {
6130  JSCallNode n(node);
6131  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6132  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6133  return NoChange();
6134  }
6135 
6136  Effect effect = n.effect();
6137  Control control = n.control();
6138  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6139 
6140  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6141  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6142  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6143 
6144  std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
6145  if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds)) {
6146  return inference.NoChange();
6147  }
6148  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6149  return inference.NoChange();
6150  }
6151  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6152  control, p.feedback());
6153 
6154  std::vector<Node*> controls_to_merge;
6155  std::vector<Node*> effects_to_merge;
6156  std::vector<Node*> values_to_merge;
6157  Node* value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6158 
6159  Node* receiver_elements_kind =
6160  LoadReceiverElementsKind(receiver, &effect, control);
6161  Node* next_control = control;
6162  Node* next_effect = effect;
6163  for (size_t i = 0; i < kinds.size(); i++) {
6164  ElementsKind kind = kinds[i];
6165  control = next_control;
6166  effect = next_effect;
6167  // We do not need branch for the last elements kind.
6168  if (i != kinds.size() - 1) {
6169  Node* control_node = control;
6170  CheckIfElementsKind(receiver_elements_kind, kind, control_node,
6171  &control_node, &next_control);
6172  control = control_node;
6173  }
6174 
6175  // Load the "length" property of the {receiver}.
6176  Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6177  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
6178  receiver, effect, control);
6179 
6180  // Check if the {receiver} has any elements.
6181  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
6182  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6183  Node* branch =
6184  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
6185 
6186  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
6187  Node* etrue = effect;
6188  Node* vtrue = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6189 
6190  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
6191  Node* efalse = effect;
6192  Node* vfalse;
6193  {
6194  // TODO(turbofan): We should trim the backing store if the capacity is too
6195  // big, as implemented in elements.cc:ElementsAccessorBase::SetLengthImpl.
6196 
6197  // Load the elements backing store from the {receiver}.
6198  Node* elements = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6199  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
6200  receiver, efalse, if_false);
6201 
6202  // Ensure that we aren't popping from a copy-on-write backing store.
6203  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
6204  elements = efalse =
6205  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
6206  receiver, elements, efalse, if_false);
6207  }
6208 
6209  // Compute the new {length}.
6210  Node* new_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(),
6211  length, jsgraph()->OneConstant());
6212 
6213  if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
6214  new_length = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6215  simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback(),
6216  CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
6217  new_length, length, efalse, if_false);
6218  }
6219 
6220  // Store the new {length} to the {receiver}.
6221  efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6222  simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
6223  receiver, new_length, efalse, if_false);
6224 
6225  // Load the last entry from the {elements}.
6226  vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6227  simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind)),
6228  elements, new_length, efalse, if_false);
6229 
6230  // Store a hole to the element we just removed from the {receiver}.
6231  efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6232  simplified()->StoreElement(
6233  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(GetHoleyElementsKind(kind))),
6234  elements, new_length, jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant(), efalse, if_false);
6235  }
6236 
6237  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
6238  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
6239  value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6240  vtrue, vfalse, control);
6241 
6242  // Convert the hole to undefined. Do this last, so that we can optimize
6243  // conversion operator via some smart strength reduction in many cases.
6244  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
6245  value =
6246  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
6247  }
6248 
6249  controls_to_merge.push_back(control);
6250  effects_to_merge.push_back(effect);
6251  values_to_merge.push_back(value);
6252  }
6253 
6254  if (controls_to_merge.size() > 1) {
6255  int const count = static_cast<int>(controls_to_merge.size());
6256 
6257  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count,
6258  &controls_to_merge.front());
6259  effects_to_merge.push_back(control);
6260  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
6261  &effects_to_merge.front());
6262  values_to_merge.push_back(control);
6263  value =
6264  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
6265  count + 1, &values_to_merge.front());
6266  }
6267 
6268  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6269  return Replace(value);
6270 }

6272 // ES6 section 22.1.3.22 Array.prototype.shift ( )
6273 // Currently disabled. See https://crbug.com/v8/14409
6274 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeShift(Node* node) {
6275  JSCallNode n(node);
6276  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6277  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6278  return NoChange();
6279  }
6280 
6281  Node* target = n.target();
6282  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6283  Node* context = n.context();
6284  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
6285  Effect effect = n.effect();
6286  Control control = n.control();
6287 
6288  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6289  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6290  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6291 
6292  std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
6293  if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds)) {
6294  return inference.NoChange();
6295  }
6296  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6297  return inference.NoChange();
6298  }
6299  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6300  control, p.feedback());
6301 
6302  std::vector<Node*> controls_to_merge;
6303  std::vector<Node*> effects_to_merge;
6304  std::vector<Node*> values_to_merge;
6305  Node* value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6306 
6307  Node* receiver_elements_kind =
6308  LoadReceiverElementsKind(receiver, &effect, control);
6309  Node* next_control = control;
6310  Node* next_effect = effect;
6311  for (size_t i = 0; i < kinds.size(); i++) {
6312  ElementsKind kind = kinds[i];
6313  control = next_control;
6314  effect = next_effect;
6315  // We do not need branch for the last elements kind.
6316  if (i != kinds.size() - 1) {
6317  Node* control_node = control;
6318  CheckIfElementsKind(receiver_elements_kind, kind, control_node,
6319  &control_node, &next_control);
6320  control = control_node;
6321  }
6322 
6323  // Load length of the {receiver}.
6324  Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6325  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
6326  receiver, effect, control);
6327 
6328  // Return undefined if {receiver} has no elements.
6329  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
6330  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6331  Node* branch0 =
6332  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check0, control);
6333 
6334  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
6335  Node* etrue0 = effect;
6336  Node* vtrue0 = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6337 
6338  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
6339  Node* efalse0 = effect;
6340  Node* vfalse0;
6341  {
6342  // Check if we should take the fast-path.
6343  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(
6344  simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(), length,
6345  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements));
6346  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue),
6347  check1, if_false0);
6348 
6349  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
6350  Node* etrue1 = efalse0;
6351  Node* vtrue1;
6352  {
6353  Node* elements = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6354  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
6355  receiver, etrue1, if_true1);
6356 
6357  // Load the first element here, which we return below.
6358  vtrue1 = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6359  simplified()->LoadElement(
6360  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind)),
6361  elements, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), etrue1, if_true1);
6362 
6363  // Ensure that we aren't shifting a copy-on-write backing store.
6364  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
6365  elements = etrue1 =
6366  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
6367  receiver, elements, etrue1, if_true1);
6368  }
6369 
6370  // Shift the remaining {elements} by one towards the start.
6371  Node* loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), if_true1, if_true1);
6372  Node* eloop =
6373  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, etrue1, loop);
6374  Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
6375  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
6376 
6377  Node* index = graph()->NewNode(
6378  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6379  jsgraph()->OneConstant(),
6380  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements - 1), loop);
6381 
6382  {
6383  Node* check2 =
6384  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
6385  Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check2, loop);
6386 
6387  if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
6388  etrue1 = eloop;
6389 
6390  Node* control2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
6391  Node* effect2 = etrue1;
6392 
6393  ElementAccess const access =
6394  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind);
6395 
6396  // When disable v8_flags.turbo_loop_variable, typer cannot infer index
6397  // is in [1, kMaxCopyElements-1], and will break in representing
6398  // kRepFloat64 (Range(1, inf)) to kRepWord64 when converting
6399  // input for kLoadElement. So we need to add type guard here.
6400  // And we need to use index when using NumberLessThan to check
6401  // terminate and updating index, otherwise which will break inducing
6402  // variables in LoopVariableOptimizer.
6403  static_assert(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements < kSmiMaxValue);
6404  Node* index_retyped = effect2 =
6405  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()),
6406  index, effect2, control2);
6407 
6408  Node* value2 = effect2 =
6409  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadElement(access), elements,
6410  index_retyped, effect2, control2);
6411  effect2 = graph()->NewNode(
6412  simplified()->StoreElement(access), elements,
6413  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), index_retyped,
6414  jsgraph()->OneConstant()),
6415  value2, effect2, control2);
6416 
6417  loop->ReplaceInput(1, control2);
6418  eloop->ReplaceInput(1, effect2);
6419  index->ReplaceInput(1,
6420  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
6421  jsgraph()->OneConstant()));
6422  }
6423 
6424  // Compute the new {length}.
6425  Node* new_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(),
6426  length, jsgraph()->OneConstant());
6427 
6428  if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
6429  new_length = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6430  simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback(),
6431  CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
6432  new_length, length, etrue1, if_true1);
6433  }
6434 
6435  // Store the new {length} to the {receiver}.
6436  etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6437  simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
6438  receiver, new_length, etrue1, if_true1);
6439 
6440  // Store a hole to the element we just removed from the {receiver}.
6441  etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6442  simplified()->StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(
6443  GetHoleyElementsKind(kind))),
6444  elements, new_length, jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant(), etrue1,
6445  if_true1);
6446  }
6447 
6448  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
6449  Node* efalse1 = efalse0;
6450  Node* vfalse1;
6451  {
6452  // Call the generic C++ implementation.
6453  const Builtin builtin = Builtin::kArrayShift;
6454  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetCEntryStubCallDescriptor(
6455  graph()->zone(), 1, BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver,
6456  Builtins::name(builtin), node->op()->properties(),
6457  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
6458  const bool has_builtin_exit_frame = true;
6459  Node* stub_code = jsgraph()->CEntryStubConstant(1, ArgvMode::kStack,
6460  has_builtin_exit_frame);
6461  Address builtin_entry = Builtins::CppEntryOf(builtin);
6462  Node* entry = jsgraph()->ExternalConstant(
6463  ExternalReference::Create(builtin_entry));
6464  Node* argc = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
6465  BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver);
6466  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kNewTargetIndex == 0);
6467  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kTargetIndex == 1);
6468  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kArgcIndex == 2);
6469  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kPaddingIndex == 3);
6470  if_false1 = efalse1 = vfalse1 =
6471  graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), stub_code,
6472  receiver, jsgraph()->PaddingConstant(), argc,
6473  target, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), entry,
6474  argc, context, frame_state, efalse1, if_false1);
6475  }
6476 
6477  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true1, if_false1);
6478  efalse0 =
6479  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, efalse1, if_false0);
6480  vfalse0 =
6481  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6482  vtrue1, vfalse1, if_false0);
6483  }
6484 
6485  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
6486  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, efalse0, control);
6487  value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6488  vtrue0, vfalse0, control);
6489 
6490  // Convert the hole to undefined. Do this last, so that we can optimize
6491  // conversion operator via some smart strength reduction in many cases.
6492  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
6493  value =
6494  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
6495  }
6496 
6497  controls_to_merge.push_back(control);
6498  effects_to_merge.push_back(effect);
6499  values_to_merge.push_back(value);
6500  }
6501 
6502  if (controls_to_merge.size() > 1) {
6503  int const count = static_cast<int>(controls_to_merge.size());
6504 
6505  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count,
6506  &controls_to_merge.front());
6507  effects_to_merge.push_back(control);
6508  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
6509  &effects_to_merge.front());
6510  values_to_merge.push_back(control);
6511  value =
6512  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
6513  count + 1, &values_to_merge.front());

6515

6518 }
