6520 // ES6 section 22.1.3.23 Array.prototype.slice ( )
6521 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeSlice(Node* node) {
6522  if (!v8_flags.turbo_inline_array_builtins) return NoChange();
6523  JSCallNode n(node);
6524  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6525  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6526  return NoChange();
6527  }
6528 
6529  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6530  Node* start = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6531  Node* end = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
6532  Node* context = n.context();
6533  Effect effect = n.effect();
6534  Control control = n.control();
6535 
6536  // Optimize for the case where we simply clone the {receiver}, i.e. when the
6537  // {start} is zero and the {end} is undefined (meaning it will be set to
6538  // {receiver}s "length" property).
6539 
6540  // This logic should be in sync with ArrayPrototypeSlice (to a reasonable
6541  // degree). This is because CloneFastJSArray produces arrays which are
6542  // potentially COW. If there's a discrepancy, TF generates code which produces
6543  // a COW array and then expects it to be non-COW (or the other way around) ->
6544  // immediate deopt.
6545 
6546  // LINT.IfChange(ArrayPrototypeSlice)
6547  if (!NumberMatcher(start).Is(0) ||
6548  !HeapObjectMatcher(end).Is(factory()->undefined_value())) {
6549  return NoChange();
6550  }
6551  // LINT.ThenChange(/src/builtins/array-slice.tq:ArrayPrototypeSlice)
6552 
6553  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6554  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6555  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6556 
6557  // Check that the maps are of JSArray (and more).
6558  // TODO(turbofan): Consider adding special case for the common pattern
6559  // `slice.call(arguments)`, for example jQuery makes heavy use of that.
6560  bool can_be_holey = false;
6561  for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
6562  if (!receiver_map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
6563  return inference.NoChange();
6564  }
6565  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(receiver_map.elements_kind())) {
6566  can_be_holey = true;
6567  }
6568  }
6569 
6570  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArraySpeciesProtector()) {
6571  return inference.NoChange();
6572  }
6573  if (can_be_holey && !dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6574  return inference.NoChange();
6575  }
6576  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6577  control, p.feedback());
6578 
6579  // TODO(turbofan): We can do even better here, either adding a CloneArray
6580  // simplified operator, whose output type indicates that it's an Array,
6581  // saving subsequent checks, or yet better, by introducing new operators
6582  // CopySmiOrObjectElements / CopyDoubleElements and inlining the JSArray
6583  // allocation in here. That way we'd even get escape analysis and scalar
6584  // replacement to help in some cases.
6585  Callable callable =
6586  Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kCloneFastJSArray);
6587  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6588  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
6589  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(), CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
6590  Operator::kNoThrow | Operator::kNoDeopt);
6591 
6592  // Calls to Builtin::kCloneFastJSArray produce COW arrays
6593  // if the original array is COW
6594  Node* clone = effect =
6595  graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
6596  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()), receiver,
6597  context, effect, control);
6598 
6599  ReplaceWithValue(node, clone, effect, control);
6600  return Replace(clone);
6601 }
6602 
6603 // ES6 section 22.1.2.2 Array.isArray ( arg )
6604 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIsArray(Node* node) {
6605  // We certainly know that undefined is not an array.
6606  JSCallNode n(node);
6607  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
6608  Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
6609  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
6610  return Replace(value);
6611  }
6612 
6613  Effect effect = n.effect();
6614  Control control = n.control();
6615  Node* context = n.context();
6616  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
6617  Node* object = n.Argument(0);
6618  node->ReplaceInput(0, object);
6619  node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
6620  node->ReplaceInput(2, frame_state);
6621  node->ReplaceInput(3, effect);
6622  node->ReplaceInput(4, control);
6623  node->TrimInputCount(5);
6624  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ObjectIsArray());
6625  return Changed(node);
6626 }
6627 
6628 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIterator(Node* node,
6629  ArrayIteratorKind array_kind,
6630  IterationKind iteration_kind) {
6631  JSCallNode n(node);
6632  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6633  Node* context = n.context();
6634  Effect effect = n.effect();
6635  Control control = n.control();
6636 
6637  // Check if we know that {receiver} is a valid JSReceiver.
6638  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6639  if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
6640  return NoChange();
6641  }
6642 
6643  // TypedArray iteration is stricter: it throws if the receiver is not a typed
6644  // array. So don't bother optimizing in that case.
6645  if (array_kind == ArrayIteratorKind::kTypedArray &&
6646  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(InstanceType::JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
6647  return NoChange();
6648  }
6649 
6650  if (array_kind == ArrayIteratorKind::kTypedArray) {
6651  // Make sure we deopt when the JSArrayBuffer is detached.
6652  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
6653  CallParameters const& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
6654  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6655  return NoChange();
6656  }
6657 
6658  std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
6659  for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
6660  elements_kinds.insert(map.elements_kind());
6661  }
6662 
6663  // The following detach check is built with the given {elements_kinds} in
6664  // mind, so we have to install dependency on those.
6665  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(
6666  dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect, control,
6667  CallParametersOf(node->op()).feedback());
6668 
6669  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6670  a.CheckIfTypedArrayWasDetachedOrOutOfBounds(
6671  TNode<JSTypedArray>::UncheckedCast(receiver),
6672  std::move(elements_kinds), p.feedback());
6673  std::tie(effect, control) = ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(&a);
6674  }
6675  }
6676 
6677  // JSCreateArrayIterator doesn't have control output, so we bypass the old
6678  // JSCall node on the control chain.
6679  ReplaceWithValue(node, node, node, control);
6680 
6681  // Morph the {node} into a JSCreateArrayIterator with the given {kind}.
6682  node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
6683  node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
6684  node->ReplaceInput(2, effect);
6685  node->ReplaceInput(3, control);
6686  node->TrimInputCount(4);
6687  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
6688  javascript()->CreateArrayIterator(iteration_kind));
6689  return Changed(node);
6690 }
6691 
6692 // ES #sec-%arrayiteratorprototype%.next
6693 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIteratorPrototypeNext(Node* node) {
6694  JSCallNode n(node);
6695  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6696  Node* iterator = n.receiver();
6697  Node* context = n.context();
6698  Effect effect = n.effect();
6699  Control control = n.control();
6700 
6701  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6702  return NoChange();
6703  }
6704 
6705  if (iterator->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateArrayIterator) return NoChange();
6706 
6707  IterationKind const iteration_kind =
6708  CreateArrayIteratorParametersOf(iterator->op()).kind();
6709  Node* iterated_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(iterator, 0);
6710  Effect iterator_effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(iterator)};
6711 
6712  MapInference inference(broker(), iterated_object, iterator_effect);
6713  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6714  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& iterated_object_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6715 
6716  // Check that various {iterated_object_maps} have compatible elements kinds.
6717  ElementsKind elements_kind = iterated_object_maps[0].elements_kind();
6718  if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6719  // TurboFan doesn't support loading from BigInt typed arrays yet.
6720  if (elements_kind == BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS ||
6721  elements_kind == BIGINT64_ELEMENTS) {
6722  return inference.NoChange();
6723  }
6724  for (MapRef iterated_object_map : iterated_object_maps) {
6725  if (iterated_object_map.elements_kind() != elements_kind) {
6726  return inference.NoChange();
6727  }
6728  }
6729  } else {
6730  if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), iterated_object_maps,
6731  &elements_kind)) {
6732  return inference.NoChange();
6733  }
6734  }
6735 
6736  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
6737  !dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6738  return inference.NoChange();
6739  }
6740 
6741  // Since the map inference was done relative to {iterator_effect} rather than
6742  // {effect}, we need to guard the use of the map(s) even when the inference
6743  // was reliable.
6744  inference.InsertMapChecks(jsgraph(), &effect, control, p.feedback());
6745 
6746  if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6747  // See if we can skip the detaching check.
6748  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
6749  // Bail out if the {iterated_object}s JSArrayBuffer was detached.
6750  Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6751  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
6752  iterated_object, effect, control);
6753  Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6754  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
6755  buffer, effect, control);
6756  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
6757  simplified()->NumberEqual(),
6758  graph()->NewNode(
6759  simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
6760  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
6761  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6762  effect = graph()->NewNode(
6763  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached,
6764  p.feedback()),
6765  check, effect, control);
6766  }
6767  }
6768 
6769  // Load the [[NextIndex]] from the {iterator} and leverage the fact
6770  // that we definitely know that it's in Unsigned32 range since the
6771  // {iterated_object} is either a JSArray or a JSTypedArray. For the
6772  // latter case we even know that it's a Smi in UnsignedSmall range.
6773  FieldAccess index_access = AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayIteratorNextIndex();
6774  if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6775  index_access.type = TypeCache::Get()->kJSTypedArrayLengthType;
6776  } else {
6777  index_access.type = TypeCache::Get()->kJSArrayLengthType;
6778  }
6779  Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(index_access),
6780  iterator, effect, control);
6781 
6782  // Load the elements of the {iterated_object}. While it feels
6783  // counter-intuitive to place the elements pointer load before
6784  // the condition below, as it might not be needed (if the {index}
6785  // is out of bounds for the {iterated_object}), it's better this
6786  // way as it allows the LoadElimination to eliminate redundant
6787  // reloads of the elements pointer.
6788  Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6789  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
6790  iterated_object, effect, control);
6791 
6792  // Load the length of the {iterated_object}. Due to the map checks we
6793  // already know something about the length here, which we can leverage
6794  // to generate Word32 operations below without additional checking.
6795  Node* length;
6796  if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6797  Node* byte_length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6798  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayByteLength()),
6799  iterated_object, effect, control);
6800  Node* byte_length_shifted = graph()->NewNode(
6801  jsgraph()->machine()->WordShr(), byte_length,
6802  jsgraph()->UintPtrConstant(ElementsKindToShiftSize(elements_kind)));
6803  length = graph()->NewNode(
6804  common()->ExitMachineGraph(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
6805  TypeCache::Get()->kJSTypedArrayLengthType),
6806  byte_length_shifted);
6807  } else {
6808  length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6809  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind)),
6810  iterated_object, effect, control);
6811  }
6812 
6813  // Check whether {index} is within the valid range for the {iterated_object}.
6814  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
6815  Node* branch =
6816  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone), check, control);
6817 
6818  Node* done_true;
6819  Node* value_true;
6820  Node* etrue = effect;
6821  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
6822  {
6823  // This extra check exists to refine the type of {index} but also to break
6824  // an exploitation technique that abuses typer mismatches.
6825  if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
6826  index = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6827  simplified()->CheckBounds(
6828  p.feedback(), CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds |
6829  (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)
6830  ? CheckBoundsFlag::kAllow64BitBounds
6831  : CheckBoundsFlag(0))),
6832  index, length, etrue, if_true);
6833  }
6834 
6835  done_true = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
6836  if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kKeys) {
6837  // Just return the {index}.
6838  value_true = index;
6839  } else {
6840  DCHECK(iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries ||
6841  iteration_kind == IterationKind::kValues);
6842 
6843  if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6844  Node* base_ptr = etrue =
6845  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
6846  AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayBasePointer()),
6847  iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
6848  Node* external_ptr = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6849  simplified()->LoadField(
6850  AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayExternalPointer()),
6851  iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
6852 
6853  ExternalArrayType array_type = kExternalInt8Array;
6854  switch (elements_kind) {
6855 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
6856  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: \
6857  array_type = kExternal##Type##Array; \
6858  break;
6859  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
6860  default:
6861  UNREACHABLE();
6862 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
6863  }
6864 
6865  Node* buffer = etrue =
6866  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
6867  AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
6868  iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
6869 
6870  value_true = etrue =
6871  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadTypedElement(array_type), buffer,
6872  base_ptr, external_ptr, index, etrue, if_true);
6873  } else {
6874  value_true = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6875  simplified()->LoadElement(
6876  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(elements_kind)),
6877  elements, index, etrue, if_true);
6878 
6879  // Convert hole to undefined if needed.
6880  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6881  value_true = ConvertHoleToUndefined(value_true, elements_kind);
6882  }
6883  }
6884 
6885  if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries) {
6886  // Allocate elements for key/value pair
6887  value_true = etrue =
6888  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(), index,
6889  value_true, context, etrue);
6890  } else {
6891  DCHECK_EQ(IterationKind::kValues, iteration_kind);
6892  }
6893  }
6894 
6895  // Increment the [[NextIndex]] field in the {iterator}. The TypeGuards
6896  // above guarantee that the {next_index} is in the UnsignedSmall range.
6897  Node* next_index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
6898  jsgraph()->OneConstant());
6899  etrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(index_access), iterator,
6900  next_index, etrue, if_true);
6901  }
6902 
6903  Node* done_false;
6904  Node* value_false;
6905  Node* efalse = effect;
6906  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
6907  {
6908  // iterator.[[NextIndex]] >= array.length, stop iterating.
6909  done_false = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
6910  value_false = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6911 
6912  if (!IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6913  // Mark the {iterator} as exhausted by setting the [[NextIndex]] to a
6914  // value that will never pass the length check again (aka the maximum
6915  // value possible for the specific iterated object). Note that this is
6916  // different from what the specification says, which is changing the
6917  // [[IteratedObject]] field to undefined, but that makes it difficult
6918  // to eliminate the map checks and "length" accesses in for..of loops.
6919  //
6920  // This is not necessary for JSTypedArray's, since the length of those
6921  // cannot change later and so if we were ever out of bounds for them
6922  // we will stay out-of-bounds forever.
6923  Node* end_index = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(index_access.type.Max());
6924  efalse = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(index_access),
6925  iterator, end_index, efalse, if_false);
6926  }
6927  }
6928 
6929  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
6930  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
6931  Node* value =
6932  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6933  value_true, value_false, control);
6934  Node* done =
6935  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6936  done_true, done_false, control);
6937 
6938  // Create IteratorResult object.
6939  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(),
6940  value, done, context, effect);
6941  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6942  return Replace(value);
6943 }

6945 // ES6 section 21.1.3.2 String.prototype.charCodeAt ( pos )
6946 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeStringCharCodeAt(Node* node) {
6947  JSCallNode n(node);
6948  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6949  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation &&
6950  p.speculation_mode() !=
6951  SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation) {
6952  return NoChange();
6953  }
6954 
6955  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6956  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeCharCodeAt(p.speculation_mode());
6957  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);

6960 // ES6 section 21.1.3.3 String.prototype.codePointAt ( pos )
6961 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeStringCodePointAt(Node* node) {
6962  JSCallNode n(node);
6963  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6964  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
6965  return NoChange();
6966  }
6967 
6968  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6969  Node* index = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6970  Effect effect = n.effect();
6971  Control control = n.control();
6972 
6973  // Ensure that the {receiver} is actually a String.
6974  receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()),
6975  receiver, effect, control);
6976 
6977  // Determine the {receiver} length.
6978  Node* receiver_length =
6979  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
6980 
6981  // TODO(olivf): Support SpeculationMode::kOutOfBands.
6982  // Check that the {index} is within range.
6983  index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
6984  index, receiver_length, effect, control);
6985 
6986  // Return the character from the {receiver} as single character string.
6987  Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringCodePointAt(),
6988  receiver, index, effect, control);
6989 
6990  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6991  return Replace(value);
6992 }

6994 // ES section 21.1.3.20
6995 // String.prototype.startsWith ( searchString [ , position ] )
6996 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith(Node* node) {
6997  JSCallNode n(node);
6998  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6999  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
7000  return NoChange();
7001  }
7002 
7003  TNode<Object> search_element = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7004 
7005  // Here are three conditions:
7006  // First, If search_element is definitely not a string, we make no change.
7007  // Second, If search_element is definitely a string and its length is less
7008  // or equal than max inline matching sequence threshold, we could inline
7009  // the entire matching sequence.
7010  // Third, we try to inline, and have a runtime deopt if search_element is
7011  // not a string.
7012  HeapObjectMatcher search_element_matcher(search_element);
7013  if (search_element_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
7014  ObjectRef target_ref = search_element_matcher.Ref(broker());
7015  if (!target_ref.IsString()) return NoChange();
7016  StringRef search_element_string = target_ref.AsString();
7017  if (!search_element_string.IsContentAccessible()) return NoChange();
7018  int length = search_element_string.length();
7019  // If search_element's length is less or equal than
7020  // kMaxInlineMatchSequence, we inline the entire
7021  // matching sequence.
7022  if (length <= kMaxInlineMatchSequence) {
7023  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7024  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith(search_element_string);
7025  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
7026  }
7027  }
7028 
7029  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7030  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith();
7031  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
7032 }
7033

7074 // ES section 21.1.3.1 String.prototype.charAt ( pos )
7075 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(Node* node) {
7076  JSCallNode n(node);
7077  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7078  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation &&
7079  p.speculation_mode() !=
7080  SpeculationMode::kDisallowBoundsCheckSpeculation) {
7081  return NoChange();
7082  }
7083 
7084  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7085  Node* index = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
7086 
7087  // Attempt to constant fold the operation when we know
7088  // that receiver is a string and index is a number.
7089  HeapObjectMatcher receiver_matcher(receiver);
7090  NumberMatcher index_matcher(index);
7091  if (receiver_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
7092  HeapObjectRef receiver_ref = receiver_matcher.Ref(broker());
7093  if (!receiver_ref.IsString()) return NoChange();
7094  StringRef receiver_string = receiver_ref.AsString();
7095  bool is_content_accessible = receiver_string.IsContentAccessible();
7096  bool is_integer_in_max_range =
7097  index_matcher.IsInteger() &&
7098  index_matcher.IsInRange(
7099  0.0, static_cast<double>(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex));
7100  if (is_content_accessible && is_integer_in_max_range) {
7101  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7102  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(
7103  receiver_string,
7104  static_cast<uint32_t>(index_matcher.ResolvedValue()));
7105  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
7106  }
7107  }
7108 
7109  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7110  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(p.speculation_mode());
7111  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
7112 }

7228 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeLocaleCompareIntl(Node* node) {
7229  JSCallNode n(node);
7230  // Signature: receiver.localeCompare(compareString, locales, options)
7231  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1 || n.ArgumentCount() > 3) {
7232  return NoChange();
7233  }
7234 
7235  {
7236  DirectHandle<Object> locales;
7237  {
7238  HeapObjectMatcher m(n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph()));
7239  if (!m.HasResolvedValue()) return NoChange();
7240  if (m.Is(factory()->undefined_value())) {
7241  locales = factory()->undefined_value();
7242  } else {
7243  ObjectRef ref = m.Ref(broker());
7244  if (!ref.IsString()) return NoChange();
7245  StringRef sref = ref.AsString();
7246  if (std::optional<Handle<String>> maybe_locales =
7247  sref.ObjectIfContentAccessible(broker())) {
7248  locales = *maybe_locales;
7249  } else {
7250  return NoChange();
7251  }
7252  }
7253  }
7254 
7255  TNode<Object> options = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(2, jsgraph());
7256  {
7257  HeapObjectMatcher m(options);
7258  if (!m.Is(factory()->undefined_value())) {
7259  return NoChange();
7260  }
7261  }
7262 
7263  if (Intl::CompareStringsOptionsFor(broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate(),
7264  locales, factory()->undefined_value()) !=
7265  Intl::CompareStringsOptions::kTryFastPath) {
7266  return NoChange();
7267  }
7268  }
7269 
7270  Callable callable =
7271  Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kStringFastLocaleCompare);
7272  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7273  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
7274  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
7275  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
7276  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
7277  if (n.ArgumentCount() == 3) {
7278  node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(2));
7279  } else if (n.ArgumentCount() == 1) {
7280  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.LastArgumentIndex() + 1,
7281  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7282  } else {
7283  DCHECK_EQ(2, n.ArgumentCount());
7284  }
7285  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
7286  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()));
7287  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
7288  return Changed(node);
7289 }
7290 #endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
7291 
7292 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringIteratorPrototypeNext(Node* node) {
7293  JSCallNode n(node);
7294  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7295  Effect effect = n.effect();
7296  Control control = n.control();
7297  Node* context = n.context();
7298 
7299  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7300  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7301  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_STRING_ITERATOR_TYPE)) {
7302  return NoChange();
7303  }
7304 
7305  Node* string = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7306  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorString()),
7307  receiver, effect, control);
7308  Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7309  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorIndex()),
7310  receiver, effect, control);
7311  Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), string);
7312 
7313  // branch0: if (index < length)
7314  Node* check0 =
7315  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
7316  Node* branch0 =
7317  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone), check0, control);
7318 
7319  Node* etrue0 = effect;
7320  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
7321  Node* done_true;
7322  Node* vtrue0;
7323  {
7324  done_true = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
7325  vtrue0 = etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromCodePointAt(),
7326  string, index, etrue0, if_true0);
7327 
7328  // Update iterator.[[NextIndex]]
7329  Node* char_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), vtrue0);
7330  index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index, char_length);
7331  etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(
7332  simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorIndex()),
7333  receiver, index, etrue0, if_true0);
7334  }
7335 
7336  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
7337  Node* done_false;
7338  Node* vfalse0;
7339  {
7340  vfalse0 = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
7341  done_false = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
7342  }
7343 
7344  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
7345  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, effect, control);
7346  Node* value =
7347  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), vtrue0,
7348  vfalse0, control);
7349  Node* done =
7350  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7351  done_true, done_false, control);
7352 
7353  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(),
7354  value, done, context, effect);
7355 
7356  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7357  return Replace(value);
7358 }

7360 // ES #sec-string.prototype.concat
7361 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeConcat(Node* node) {
7362  JSCallNode n(node);
7363  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7364  const int parameter_count = n.ArgumentCount();
7365  if (parameter_count > 1) return NoChange();
7366  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
7367  return NoChange();
7368  }
7369 
7370  Effect effect = n.effect();
7371  Control control = n.control();
7372  Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7373  simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
7374 
7375  if (parameter_count == 0) {
7376  ReplaceWithValue(node, receiver, effect, control);
7377  return Replace(receiver);
7378  }
7379 
7380  Node* argument = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7381  simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.Argument(0), effect, control);
7382  Node* receiver_length =
7383  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
7384  Node* argument_length =
7385  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), argument);
7386  Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), receiver_length,
7387  argument_length);
7388  length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7389  simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()), length,
7390  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(String::kMaxLength + 1), effect, control);
7391 
7392  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringConcat(), length, receiver,
7393  argument);
7394 
7395  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7396  return Replace(value);
7397 }

7401 FrameState CreateStringCreateLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
7402  JSGraph* graph, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* target, Node* context,
7403  Node* outer_frame_state) {
7404  Node* const receiver = graph->TheHoleConstant();
7405  Node* stack_parameters[]{receiver};
7406  const int stack_parameter_count = arraysize(stack_parameters);
7407  return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
7408  graph, shared, Builtin::kStringCreateLazyDeoptContinuation, target,
7409  context, stack_parameters, stack_parameter_count, outer_frame_state,
7410  ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
7411 }

7414 
7415 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringConstructor(Node* node,
7416  JSFunctionRef constructor) {
7417  JSConstructNode n(node);
7418  if (n.target() != n.new_target()) return NoChange();
7419 
7420  DCHECK_EQ(constructor, native_context().string_function(broker_));
7421  DCHECK(constructor.initial_map(broker_).IsJSPrimitiveWrapperMap());
7422 
7423  Node* context = n.context();
7424  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7425  Effect effect = n.effect();
7426  Control control = n.control();
7427 
7428  Node* primitive_value;
7429  if (n.ArgumentCount() == 0) {
7430  primitive_value = jsgraph()->EmptyStringConstant();
7431  } else {
7432  // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
7433  // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
7434  frame_state = CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(
7435  node, frame_state, constructor.shared(broker_), context, common(),
7436  graph());
7437 
7438  // This continuation takes the newly created primitive string, and wraps it
7439  // in a string wrapper, matching CreateStringWrapper.
7440  Node* continuation_frame_state =
7441  CreateStringCreateLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
7442  jsgraph(), constructor.shared(broker_), n.target(), context,
7443  frame_state);
7444 
7445  primitive_value = effect = control =
7446  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->ToString(), n.Argument(0), context,
7447  continuation_frame_state, effect, control);
7448 
7449  // Rewire potential exception edges.
7450  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
7451  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
7452  // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
7453  Node* if_exception =
7454  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect, control);
7455  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control);
7456 
7457  // Join the exception edges.
7458  Node* merge =
7459  graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception, on_exception);
7460  Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception,
7461  on_exception, merge);
7462  Node* phi =
7463  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7464  if_exception, on_exception, merge);
7465  ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
7466  merge->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
7467  ephi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
7468  phi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
7469  }
7470  }
7471 
7472  RelaxControls(node, control);
7473  node->ReplaceInput(0, primitive_value);
7474  node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
7475  node->ReplaceInput(2, effect);
7476  node->TrimInputCount(3);
7477  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->CreateStringWrapper());
7478  return Changed(node);
7479 }

7481 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromiseConstructor(Node* node) {
7482  PromiseBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7483 
7484  // We only inline when we have the executor.
7485  if (a.ConstructArity() < 1) return NoChange();
7486  // Only handle builtins Promises, not subclasses.
7487  if (a.TargetInput() != a.NewTargetInput()) return NoChange();
7488  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
7489 
7490  TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReducePromiseConstructor(native_context());
7491  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
7492 }
7493 
7494 bool JSCallReducer::DoPromiseChecks(MapInference* inference) {
7495  if (!inference->HaveMaps()) return false;
7496  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference->GetMaps();
7497 
7498  // Check whether all {receiver_maps} are JSPromise maps and
7499  // have the initial Promise.prototype as their [[Prototype]].
7500  for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
7501  if (!receiver_map.IsJSPromiseMap()) return false;
7502  HeapObjectRef prototype = receiver_map.prototype(broker());
7503  if (!prototype.equals(native_context().promise_prototype(broker()))) {
7504  return false;
7505  }
7506  }
7507 
7508  return true;
7509 }
7510 
7511 // ES section #sec-promise.prototype.catch
7512 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeCatch(Node* node) {
7513  JSCallNode n(node);
7514  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7515  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
7516  return NoChange();
7517  }
7518  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
7519  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7520  Effect effect = n.effect();
7521  Control control = n.control();
7522 
7523  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7524  if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
7525 
7526  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseThenProtector()) {
7527  return inference.NoChange();
7528  }
7529  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7530  control, p.feedback());
7531 
7532  // Massage the {node} to call "then" instead by first removing all inputs
7533  // following the onRejected parameter, and then filling up the parameters
7534  // to two inputs from the left with undefined.
7535  Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
7536  native_context().promise_then(broker()), broker());
7537  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 0);
7538  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
7539  for (; arity > 1; --arity) node->RemoveInput(3);
7540  for (; arity < 2; ++arity) {
7541  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7542  }
7543  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
7544  node, javascript()->Call(
7545  JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
7546  ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, p.speculation_mode(),
7547  CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
7548  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReducePromisePrototypeThen(node));
7549 }
7550 
7551 Node* JSCallReducer::CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
7552  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* context, Node* effect, Node* control) {
7553  DCHECK(shared.HasBuiltinId());
7554  Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell =
7555  isolate()->factory()->many_closures_cell();
7556  Callable const callable =
7557  Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), shared.builtin_id());
7558  CodeRef code = MakeRef(broker(), *callable.code());
7559  return graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateClosure(shared, code),
7560  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(feedback_cell), context,
7561  effect, control);
7562 }
7563 
7564 // ES section #sec-promise.prototype.finally
7565 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeFinally(Node* node) {
7566  JSCallNode n(node);
7567  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7568  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
7569  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7570  Node* on_finally = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7571  Effect effect = n.effect();
7572  Control control = n.control();
7573  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
7574  return NoChange();
7575  }
7576 
7577  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7578  if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
7579  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
7580 
7581  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) {
7582  return inference.NoChange();
7583  }
7584  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseThenProtector()) {
7585  return inference.NoChange();
7586  }
7587  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseSpeciesProtector()) {
7588  return inference.NoChange();
7589  }
7590  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7591  control, p.feedback());
7592 
7593  // Check if {on_finally} is callable, and if so wrap it into appropriate
7594  // closures that perform the finalization.
7595  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_finally);
7596  Node* branch =
7597  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
7598 
7599  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
7600  Node* etrue = effect;
7601  Node* catch_true;
7602  Node* then_true;
7603  {
7604  Node* context = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker());
7605  Node* constructor = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
7606  native_context().promise_function(broker()), broker());
7607 
7608  // Allocate shared context for the closures below.
7609  context = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
7610  javascript()->CreateFunctionContext(
7611  native_context().scope_info(broker()),
7612  int{PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseFinallyContextLength} -
7613  Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS,
7614  FUNCTION_SCOPE),
7615  context, etrue, if_true);
7616  etrue = graph()->NewNode(
7617  simplified()->StoreField(
7618  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(PromiseBuiltins::kOnFinallySlot)),
7619  context, on_finally, etrue, if_true);
7620  etrue = graph()->NewNode(
7621  simplified()->StoreField(
7622  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(PromiseBuiltins::kConstructorSlot)),
7623  context, constructor, etrue, if_true);
7624 
7625  // Allocate the closure for the reject case.
7626  SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_catch_finally =
7627  MakeRef(broker(), factory()->promise_catch_finally_shared_fun());
7628  catch_true = etrue = CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
7629  promise_catch_finally, context, etrue, if_true);
7630 
7631  // Allocate the closure for the fulfill case.
7632  SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_then_finally =
7633  MakeRef(broker(), factory()->promise_then_finally_shared_fun());
7634  then_true = etrue = CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
7635  promise_then_finally, context, etrue, if_true);
7636  }
7637 
7638  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
7639  Node* efalse = effect;
7640  Node* catch_false = on_finally;
7641  Node* then_false = on_finally;
7642 
7643  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
7644  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
7645  Node* catch_finally =
7646  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7647  catch_true, catch_false, control);
7648  Node* then_finally =
7649  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7650  then_true, then_false, control);
7651 
7652  // At this point we definitely know that {receiver} has one of the
7653  // {receiver_maps}, so insert a MapGuard as a hint for the lowering
7654  // of the call to "then" below.
7655  {
7656  effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(receiver_maps), receiver,
7657  effect, control);
7658  }
7659 
7660  // Massage the {node} to call "then" instead by first removing all inputs
7661  // following the onFinally parameter, and then replacing the only parameter
7662  // input with the {on_finally} value.
7663  Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
7664  native_context().promise_then(broker()), broker());
7665  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, n.TargetIndex());
7666  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
7667  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(node, control);
7668  for (; arity > 2; --arity) node->RemoveInput(2);
7669  for (; arity < 2; ++arity) {
7670  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, then_finally);
7671  }
7672  node->ReplaceInput(2, then_finally);
7673  node->ReplaceInput(3, catch_finally);
7674  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
7675  node, javascript()->Call(
7676  JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
7677  ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, p.speculation_mode(),
7678  CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
7679  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReducePromisePrototypeThen(node));
7680 }
7681 
7682 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeThen(Node* node) {
7683  JSCallNode n(node);
7684  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7685  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
7686  return NoChange();
7687  }
7688 
7689  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7690  Node* on_fulfilled = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7691  Node* on_rejected = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
7692  Node* context = n.context();
7693  Effect effect = n.effect();
7694  Control control = n.control();
7695  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7696 
7697  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7698  if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
7699 
7700  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) {
7701  return inference.NoChange();
7702  }
7703  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseSpeciesProtector()) {
7704  return inference.NoChange();
7705  }
7706  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7707  control, p.feedback());
7708 
7709  // Check that {on_fulfilled} is callable.
7710  on_fulfilled = graph()->NewNode(
7711  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kTrue),
7712  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_fulfilled),
7713  on_fulfilled, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7714 
7715  // Check that {on_rejected} is callable.
7716  on_rejected = graph()->NewNode(
7717  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kTrue),
7718  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_rejected),
7719  on_rejected, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7720 
7721  // Create the resulting JSPromise.
7722  Node* promise = effect =
7723  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreatePromise(), context, effect);
7724 
7725  // Chain {result} onto {receiver}.
7726  promise = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7727  javascript()->PerformPromiseThen(), receiver, on_fulfilled, on_rejected,
7728  promise, context, frame_state, effect, control);
7729 
7730  // At this point we know that {promise} is going to have the
7731  // initial Promise map, since even if {PerformPromiseThen}
7732  // above called into the host rejection tracker, the {promise}
7733  // doesn't escape to user JavaScript. So bake this information
7734  // into the graph such that subsequent passes can use the
7735  // information for further optimizations.
7736  MapRef promise_map =
7737  native_context().promise_function(broker()).initial_map(broker());
7738  effect =
7739  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(ZoneRefSet<Map>(promise_map)),
7740  promise, effect, control);
7741 
7742  ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
7743  return Replace(promise);
7744 }
7745 
7746 // ES section #sec-promise.resolve
7747 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromiseResolveTrampoline(Node* node) {
7748  JSCallNode n(node);
7749  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7750  Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7751  Node* context = n.context();
7752  Effect effect = n.effect();
7753  Control control = n.control();
7754  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7755 
7756  // Only reduce when the receiver is guaranteed to be a JSReceiver.
7757  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7758  if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
7759  return NoChange();
7760  }
7761 
7762  // Morph the {node} into a JSPromiseResolve operation.
7763  node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
7764  node->ReplaceInput(1, value);
7765  node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
7766  node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
7767  node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
7768  node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
7769  node->TrimInputCount(6);
7770  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->PromiseResolve());
7771  return Changed(node);
7772 }

7774 // ES #sec-typedarray-constructors
7775 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayConstructor(
7776  Node* node, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
7777  JSConstructNode n(node);
7778  Node* target = n.target();
7779  Node* arg0 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7780  Node* arg1 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
7781  Node* arg2 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(2, jsgraph());
7782  Node* new_target = n.new_target();
7783  Node* context = n.context();
7784  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7785  Effect effect = n.effect();
7786  Control control = n.control();
7787 
7788  // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
7789  // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
7790  frame_state = CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(node, frame_state, shared,
7791  context, common(), graph());
7792 
7793  // This continuation just returns the newly created JSTypedArray. We
7794  // pass the_hole as the receiver, just like the builtin construct stub
7795  // does in this case.
7796  Node* const receiver = jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant();
7797  Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
7798  jsgraph(), shared, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
7799 
7800  Node* result = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateTypedArray(), target,
7801  new_target, arg0, arg1, arg2, context,
7802  continuation_frame_state, effect, control);
7803  return Replace(result);
7804 }

7806 // ES #sec-get-%typedarray%.prototype-@@tostringtag
7807 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayPrototypeToStringTag(Node* node) {
7808  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7809  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
7810  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
7811 
7812  NodeVector values(graph()->zone());
7813  NodeVector effects(graph()->zone());
7814  NodeVector controls(graph()->zone());
7815 
7816  Node* smi_check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), receiver);
7817  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), smi_check,
7818  control);
7819 
7820  values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7821  effects.push_back(effect);
7822  controls.push_back(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control));
7823 
7824  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
7825  Node* receiver_map = effect =
7826  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
7827  receiver, effect, control);
7828  Node* receiver_bit_field2 = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7829  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2()), receiver_map,
7830  effect, control);
7831  Node* receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
7832  simplified()->NumberShiftRightLogical(),
7833  graph()->NewNode(
7834  simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), receiver_bit_field2,
7835  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
7836  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
7837 
7838  // Offset the elements kind by FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND,
7839  // so that the branch cascade below is turned into a simple table
7840  // switch by the ControlFlowOptimizer later.
7841  receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
7842  simplified()->NumberSubtract(), receiver_elements_kind,
7843  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND));
7844 
7845  // To be converted into a switch by the ControlFlowOptimizer, the below
7846  // code requires that TYPED_ARRAYS and RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS are consecutive.
7847  static_assert(LAST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1 ==
7848  FIRST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND);
7849 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
7850  do { \
7851  Node* check = graph()->NewNode( \
7852  simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind, \
7853  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(TYPE##_ELEMENTS - \
7854  FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)); \
7855  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control); \
7856  values.push_back(jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole( \
7857  broker()->GetTypedArrayStringTag(TYPE##_ELEMENTS), broker())); \
7858  effects.push_back(effect); \
7859  controls.push_back(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control)); \
7860  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control); \
7861  } while (false);
7862  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
7863  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
7864 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
7865 
7866  values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7867  effects.push_back(effect);
7868  controls.push_back(control);
7869 
7870  int const count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
7871  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count, &controls.front());
7872  effects.push_back(control);
7873  effect =
7874  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1, &effects.front());
7875  values.push_back(control);
7876  Node* value =
7877  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
7878  count + 1, &values.front());
7879  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7880  return Replace(value);
7881 }
7882 
7883 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferViewByteLengthAccessor(
7884  Node* node, InstanceType instance_type, Builtin builtin) {
7885  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
7886  DCHECK(instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE ||
7887  instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
7888  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7889  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7890  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7891 
7892  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7893  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7894  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
7895  return inference.NoChange();
7896  }
7897 
7898  std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
7899  bool maybe_rab_gsab = false;
7900  if (instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
7901  for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
7902  ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
7903  elements_kinds.insert(kind);
7904  if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) maybe_rab_gsab = true;
7905  }
7906  }
7907 
7908  if (!maybe_rab_gsab) {
7909  // We do not perform any change depending on this inference.
7910  Reduction unused_reduction = inference.NoChange();
7911  USE(unused_reduction);
7912  // Call default implementation for non-rab/gsab TAs.
7913  return ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
7914  node, instance_type, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(),
7915  builtin);
7916  }
7917 
7918  const CallParameters& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
7919  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
7920  return inference.NoChange();
7921  }
7922  DCHECK(p.feedback().IsValid());
7923 
7924  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7925  control, p.feedback());
7926 
7927  const bool depended_on_detaching_protector =
7928  dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector();
7929  if (!depended_on_detaching_protector && instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE) {
7930  // DataView prototype accessors throw on detached ArrayBuffers instead of
7931  // return 0, so skip the optimization.
7932  //
7933  // TODO(turbofan): Ideally we would bail out if the buffer is actually
7934  // detached.
7935  return inference.NoChange();
7936  }
7937 
7938  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7939  TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array =
7940  TNode<JSTypedArray>::UncheckedCast(receiver);
7941  TNode<Number> length = a.ArrayBufferViewByteLength(
7942  typed_array, instance_type, std::move(elements_kinds), a.ContextInput());
7943 
7944  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, length);
7945 }

7947 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferViewByteOffsetAccessor(
7948  Node* node, InstanceType instance_type, Builtin builtin) {
7949  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
7950  DCHECK(instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE ||
7951  instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
7952  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7953  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7954  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7955 
7956  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7957  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7958  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
7959  return inference.NoChange();
7960  }
7961 
7962  std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
7963  bool maybe_rab_gsab = false;
7964  if (instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
7965  for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
7966  ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
7967  elements_kinds.insert(kind);
7968  if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) maybe_rab_gsab = true;
7969  }
7970  }
7971 
7972  if (!maybe_rab_gsab) {
7973  // We do not perform any change depending on this inference.
7974  Reduction unused_reduction = inference.NoChange();
7975  USE(unused_reduction);
7976  // Call default implementation for non-rab/gsab TAs.
7977  return ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
7978  node, instance_type, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(),
7979  builtin);
7980  }
7981 
7982  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for RAG/GSAB TypedArray/DataView.
7983  return inference.NoChange();
7984 }
7985 
7986 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayPrototypeLength(Node* node) {
7987  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7988  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7989  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7990 
7991  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7992  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7993  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
7994  return inference.NoChange();
7995  }
7996 
7997  std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
7998  bool maybe_rab_gsab = false;
7999  for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
8000  ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
8001  elements_kinds.insert(kind);
8002  if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) maybe_rab_gsab = true;
8003  }
8004 
8005  if (!maybe_rab_gsab) {
8006  // We do not perform any change depending on this inference.
8007  Reduction unused_reduction = inference.NoChange();
8008  USE(unused_reduction);
8009  // Call default implementation for non-rab/gsab TAs.
8010  return ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
8011  node, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE, AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayByteLength(),
8012  Builtin::kTypedArrayPrototypeLength);
8013  }
8014 
8015  if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
8016  return inference.NoChange();
8017  }
8018 
8019  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
8020  TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array =
8021  TNode<JSTypedArray>::UncheckedCast(receiver);
8022  TNode<Number> length = a.TypedArrayLength(
8023  typed_array, std::move(elements_kinds), a.ContextInput());
8024 
8025  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
8026  length =
8027  a.MachineSelectIf<Number>(a.ArrayBufferViewDetachedBit(typed_array))
8028  .Then([&]() { return a.NumberConstant(0); })
8029  .Else([&]() { return length; })
8030  .ExpectFalse()
8031  .Value();
8032  }
8033 
8034  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, length);
8035 }

8093 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMapPrototypeGet(Node* node) {
8094  // We only optimize if we have target, receiver and key parameters.
8095  JSCallNode n(node);
8096  if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) return NoChange();
8097  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
8098  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8099  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
8100  Node* key = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 2);
8101 
8102  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8103  if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_MAP_TYPE)) {
8104  return NoChange();
8105  }
8106 
8107  Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8108  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
8109  effect, control);
8110 
8111  Node* entry = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8112  simplified()->FindOrderedCollectionEntry(CollectionKind::kMap), table,
8113  key, effect, control);
8114 
8115  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), entry,
8116  jsgraph()->MinusOneConstant());
8117 
8118  Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
8119 
8120  // Key not found.
8121  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
8122  Node* etrue = effect;
8123  Node* vtrue = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
8124 
8125  // Key found.
8126  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
8127  Node* efalse = effect;
8128  Node* vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
8129  simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapEntryValue()),
8130  table, entry, efalse, if_false);
8131 
8132  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
8133  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(
8134  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), vtrue, vfalse, control);
8135  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
8136 
8137  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8138  return Replace(value);
8139 }

8143 InstanceType InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(CollectionKind kind) {
8144  switch (kind) {
8145  case CollectionKind::kMap:
8146  return JS_MAP_TYPE;
8147  case CollectionKind::kSet:
8148  return JS_SET_TYPE;
8149  }
8150  UNREACHABLE();
8151 }

8155 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionPrototypeHas(
8156  Node* node, CollectionKind collection_kind) {
8157  // We only optimize if we have target, receiver and key parameters.
8158  JSCallNode n(node);
8159  if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) return NoChange();
8160  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
8161  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8162  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
8163  Node* key = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 2);
8164  InstanceType instance_type = InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(collection_kind);
8165 
8166  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8167  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
8168  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
8169  return NoChange();
8170  }
8171 
8172  Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8173  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
8174  effect, control);
8175 
8176  Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8177  simplified()->FindOrderedCollectionEntry(collection_kind), table, key,
8178  effect, control);
8179 
8180  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), index,
8181  jsgraph()->MinusOneConstant());
8182  value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BooleanNot(), value);
8183 
8184  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8185  return Replace(value);
8186 }

8196 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionIteration(
8197  Node* node, CollectionKind collection_kind, IterationKind iteration_kind) {
8198  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode());
8199  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
8200  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
8201  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8202  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
8203

8205  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8206  if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(type)) {
8207  return NoChange();

8211  javascript()->CreateCollectionIterator(collection_kind, iteration_kind),
8212  receiver, context, effect, control);
