8240 
8241 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionIteratorPrototypeNext(
8242  Node* node, int entry_size, Handle<HeapObject> empty_collection,
8243  InstanceType collection_iterator_instance_type_first,
8244  InstanceType collection_iterator_instance_type_last) {
8245  JSCallNode n(node);
8246  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8247  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
8248  return NoChange();
8249  }
8250 
8251  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
8252  Node* context = n.context();
8253  Effect effect = n.effect();
8254  Control control = n.control();
8255 
8256  // A word of warning to begin with: This whole method might look a bit
8257  // strange at times, but that's mostly because it was carefully handcrafted
8258  // to allow for full escape analysis and scalar replacement of both the
8259  // collection iterator object and the iterator results, including the
8260  // key-value arrays in case of Set/Map entry iteration.
8261  //
8262  // TODO(turbofan): Currently the escape analysis (and the store-load
8263  // forwarding) is unable to eliminate the allocations for the key-value
8264  // arrays in case of Set/Map entry iteration, and we should investigate
8265  // how to update the escape analysis / arrange the graph in a way that
8266  // this becomes possible.
8267 
8268  InstanceType receiver_instance_type;
8269  {
8270  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8271  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
8272  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
8273  receiver_instance_type = receiver_maps[0].instance_type();
8274  for (size_t i = 1; i < receiver_maps.size(); ++i) {
8275  if (receiver_maps[i].instance_type() != receiver_instance_type) {
8276  return inference.NoChange();
8277  }
8278  }
8279  if (receiver_instance_type < collection_iterator_instance_type_first ||
8280  receiver_instance_type > collection_iterator_instance_type_last) {
8281  return inference.NoChange();
8282  }
8283  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
8284  control, p.feedback());
8285  }
8286 
8287  // Transition the JSCollectionIterator {receiver} if necessary
8288  // (i.e. there were certain mutations while we're iterating).
8289  {
8290  Node* done_loop;
8291  Node* done_eloop;
8292  Node* loop = control =
8293  graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control, control);
8294  Node* eloop = effect =
8295  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect, effect, loop);
8296  Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
8297  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
8298 
8299  // Check if reached the final table of the {receiver}.
8300  Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8301  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8302  receiver, effect, control);
8303  Node* next_table = effect =
8304  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
8305  AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNextTable()),
8306  table, effect, control);
8307  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), next_table);
8308  control =
8309  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
8310 
8311  // Abort the {loop} when we reach the final table.
8312  done_loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
8313  done_eloop = effect;
8314 
8315  // Migrate to the {next_table} otherwise.
8316  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
8317 
8318  // Self-heal the {receiver}s index.
8319  Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8320  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8321  receiver, effect, control);
8322  Callable const callable =
8323  Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kOrderedHashTableHealIndex);
8324  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
8325  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
8326  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
8327  CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kEliminatable);
8328  index = effect =
8329  graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
8330  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()), table,
8331  index, jsgraph()->NoContextConstant(), effect);
8332 
8333  index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8334  common()->TypeGuard(TypeCache::Get()->kFixedArrayLengthType), index,
8335  effect, control);
8336 
8337  // Update the {index} and {table} on the {receiver}.
8338  effect = graph()->NewNode(
8339  simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8340  receiver, index, effect, control);
8341  effect = graph()->NewNode(
8342  simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8343  receiver, next_table, effect, control);
8344 
8345  // Tie the knot.
8346  loop->ReplaceInput(1, control);
8347  eloop->ReplaceInput(1, effect);
8348 
8349  control = done_loop;
8350  effect = done_eloop;
8351  }
8352 
8353  // Get current index and table from the JSCollectionIterator {receiver}.
8354  Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8355  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8356  receiver, effect, control);
8357  Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8358  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8359  receiver, effect, control);
8360 
8361  // Create the {JSIteratorResult} first to ensure that we always have
8362  // a dominating Allocate node for the allocation folding phase.
8363  Node* iterator_result = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8364  javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(),
8365  jsgraph()->TrueConstant(), context, effect);
8366 
8367  // Look for the next non-holey key, starting from {index} in the {table}.
8368  Node* controls[2];
8369  Node* effects[3];
8370  {
8371  // Compute the currently used capacity.
8372  Node* number_of_buckets = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8373  simplified()->LoadField(
8374  AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfBuckets()),
8375  table, effect, control);
8376  Node* number_of_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8377  simplified()->LoadField(
8378  AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfElements()),
8379  table, effect, control);
8380  Node* number_of_deleted_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8381  simplified()->LoadField(
8382  AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfDeletedElements()),
8383  table, effect, control);
8384  Node* used_capacity =
8385  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), number_of_elements,
8386  number_of_deleted_elements);
8387 
8388  // Skip holes and update the {index}.
8389  Node* loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control, control);
8390  Node* eloop =
8391  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect, effect, loop);
8392  Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
8393  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
8394  Node* iloop = graph()->NewNode(
8395  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), index, index, loop);
8396 
8397  index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8398  common()->TypeGuard(TypeCache::Get()->kFixedArrayLengthType), iloop,
8399  eloop, control);
8400  {
8401  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index,
8402  used_capacity);
8403  Node* branch0 =
8404  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check0, loop);
8405 
8406  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
8407  Node* efalse0 = effect;
8408  {
8409  // Mark the {receiver} as exhausted.
8410  efalse0 = graph()->NewNode(
8411  simplified()->StoreField(
8412  AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8413  receiver, jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(empty_collection), efalse0,
8414  if_false0);
8415 
8416  controls[0] = if_false0;
8417  effects[0] = efalse0;
8418  }
8419 
8420  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
8421  Node* etrue0 = effect;
8422  {
8423  // Load the key of the entry.
8424  static_assert(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex() ==
8425  OrderedHashSet::HashTableStartIndex());
8426  Node* entry_start_position = graph()->NewNode(
8427  simplified()->NumberAdd(),
8428  graph()->NewNode(
8429  simplified()->NumberAdd(),
8430  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMultiply(), index,
8431  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(entry_size)),
8432  number_of_buckets),
8433  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex()));
8434  Node* entry_key = etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(
8435  simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
8436  table, entry_start_position, etrue0, if_true0);
8437 
8438  // Advance the index.
8439  index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
8440  jsgraph()->OneConstant());
8441 
8442  Node* check1 =
8443  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), entry_key,
8444  jsgraph()->HashTableHoleConstant());
8445  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
8446  check1, if_true0);
8447 
8448  {
8449  // Abort loop with resulting value.
8450  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
8451  effect = etrue0;
8452  Node* value = effect =
8453  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::NonInternal()),
8454  entry_key, effect, control);
8455  Node* done = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
8456 
8457  // Advance the index on the {receiver}.
8458  effect = graph()->NewNode(
8459  simplified()->StoreField(
8460  AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8461  receiver, index, effect, control);
8462 
8463  // The actual {value} depends on the {receiver} iteration type.
8464  switch (receiver_instance_type) {
8465  case JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8466  case JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8467  break;
8468 
8469  case JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8470  value = effect =
8471  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(), value,
8472  value, context, effect);
8473  break;
8474 
8475  case JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8476  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8477  simplified()->LoadElement(
8478  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
8479  table,
8480  graph()->NewNode(
8481  simplified()->NumberAdd(), entry_start_position,
8482  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(OrderedHashMap::kValueOffset)),
8483  effect, control);
8484  break;
8485 
8486  case JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8487  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8488  simplified()->LoadElement(
8489  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
8490  table,
8491  graph()->NewNode(
8492  simplified()->NumberAdd(), entry_start_position,
8493  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(OrderedHashMap::kValueOffset)),
8494  effect, control);
8495  value = effect =
8496  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(),
8497  entry_key, value, context, effect);
8498  break;
8499 
8500  default:
8501  UNREACHABLE();
8502  }
8503 
8504  // Store final {value} and {done} into the {iterator_result}.
8505  effect =
8506  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(
8507  AccessBuilder::ForJSIteratorResultValue()),
8508  iterator_result, value, effect, control);
8509  effect =
8510  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(
8511  AccessBuilder::ForJSIteratorResultDone()),
8512  iterator_result, done, effect, control);
8513 
8514  controls[1] = control;
8515  effects[1] = effect;
8516  }
8517 
8518  // Continue with next loop index.
8519  loop->ReplaceInput(1, graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1));
8520  eloop->ReplaceInput(1, etrue0);
8521  iloop->ReplaceInput(1, index);
8522  }
8523  }
8524 
8525  control = effects[2] = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), 2, controls);
8526  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), 3, effects);
8527  }
8528 
8529  // Yield the final {iterator_result}.
8530  ReplaceWithValue(node, iterator_result, effect, control);
8531  return Replace(iterator_result);
8532 }
8533 
8534 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferIsView(Node* node) {
8535  JSCallNode n(node);
8536  Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
8537  RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
8538  node->ReplaceInput(0, value);
8539  node->TrimInputCount(1);
8540  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->ObjectIsArrayBufferView());
8541  return Changed(node);
8542 }
8543 
8544 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
8545  Node* node, InstanceType instance_type, FieldAccess const& access,
8546  Builtin builtin) {
8547  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
8548  TNode<JSArrayBufferView> receiver = TNode<JSArrayBufferView>::UncheckedCast(
8549  NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1));
8550  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8551 
8552  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8553  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
8554  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
8555  return inference.NoChange();
8556  }
8557 
8558  DCHECK_IMPLIES((builtin == Builtin::kTypedArrayPrototypeLength ||
8559  builtin == Builtin::kTypedArrayPrototypeByteLength),
8560  base::none_of(inference.GetMaps(), [](MapRef map) {
8561  return IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(map.elements_kind());
8562  }));
8563 
8564  if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
8565  return inference.NoChange();
8566  }
8567 
8568  const bool depended_on_detaching_protector =
8569  dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector();
8570  if (!depended_on_detaching_protector && instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE) {
8571  // DataView prototype accessors throw on detached ArrayBuffers instead of
8572  // return 0, so skip the optimization.
8573  //
8574  // TODO(turbofan): Ideally we would bail out if the buffer is actually
8575  // detached.
8576  return inference.NoChange();
8577  }
8578 
8579  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node, effect);
8580 
8581  // Load the {receiver}s field.
8582  DCHECK_EQ(access.machine_type.representation(),
8583  MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
8584  TNode<UintPtrT> value = a.EnterMachineGraph<UintPtrT>(
8585  a.LoadField<UintPtrT>(access, receiver), UseInfo::Word());
8586 
8587  // See if we can skip the detaching check.
8588  if (!depended_on_detaching_protector) {
8589  // Check whether {receiver}s JSArrayBuffer was detached.
8590  //
8591  // TODO(turbofan): Ideally we would bail out here if the {receiver}s
8592  // JSArrayBuffer was detached, but there's no way to guard against
8593  // deoptimization loops right now, since the JSCall {node} is usually
8594  // created from a LOAD_IC inlining, and so there's no CALL_IC slot
8595  // from which we could use the speculation bit.
8596  value = a.MachineSelect<UintPtrT>(a.ArrayBufferViewDetachedBit(receiver),
8597  a.UintPtrConstant(0), value,
8598  BranchHint::kFalse);
8599  }
8600 
8601  if (builtin == Builtin::kTypedArrayPrototypeLength) {
8602  TNode<UintPtrT> byte_length = value;
8603  // Divide the byte length by element size.
8604  TNode<Map> map = a.LoadMap(TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(receiver));
8605  TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind = a.LoadElementsKind(map);
8606  TNode<Uint32T> shift = a.LookupByteShiftForElementsKind(elements_kind);
8607  value = TNode<UintPtrT>::UncheckedCast(
8608  a.WordShr(byte_length, a.ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(shift)));
8609  }
8610 
8611  TNode<Number> result =
8612  a.ExitMachineGraph<Number>(value, MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
8613  TypeCache::Get()->kJSTypedArrayLengthType);
8614  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, result);
8615 }
8616 
8617 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceDataViewAccess(Node* node, DataViewAccess access,
8618  ExternalArrayType element_type) {
8619  // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
8620  JSCallNode n(node);
8621  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8622  size_t const element_size = ExternalArrayElementSize(element_type);
8623  Effect effect = n.effect();
8624  Control control = n.control();
8625  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
8626  Node* offset = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
8627  Node* value = nullptr;
8628 
8629  if (!Is64() && (element_type == kExternalBigInt64Array ||
8630  element_type == kExternalBigUint64Array)) {
8631  return NoChange();
8632  }
8633 
8634  if (access == DataViewAccess::kSet) {
8635  value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
8636  }
8637  const int endian_index = (access == DataViewAccess::kGet ? 1 : 2);
8638  Node* is_little_endian =
8639  n.ArgumentOr(endian_index, jsgraph()->FalseConstant());
8640 
8641  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
8642  return NoChange();
8643  }
8644 
8645  // Only do stuff if the {receiver} is really a DataView.
8646  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8647  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
8648  !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE)) {
8649  return NoChange();
8650  }
8651 
8652  // Check that the {offset} is within range for the {receiver}.
8653  HeapObjectMatcher m(receiver);
8654  if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsJSDataView()) {
8655  // We only deal with DataViews here whose [[ByteLength]] is at least
8656  // {element_size}, as for all other DataViews it'll be out-of-bounds.
8657  JSDataViewRef dataview = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSDataView();
8658 
8659  size_t length = dataview.byte_length();
8660  if (length < element_size) return NoChange();
8661 
8662  // Check that the {offset} is within range of the {length}.
8663  Node* byte_length = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(length - (element_size - 1));
8664  offset = effect =
8665  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(
8666  p.feedback(), CheckBoundsFlag::kAllow64BitBounds),
8667  offset, byte_length, effect, control);
8668  } else {
8669  // We only deal with DataViews here that have Smi [[ByteLength]]s.
8670  Node* byte_length = effect =
8671  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
8672  AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength()),
8673  receiver, effect, control);
8674  if (element_size > 1) {
8675  // For non-byte accesses we also need to check that the {offset}
8676  // plus the {element_size}-1 fits within the given {byte_length}.
8677  // So to keep this as a single check on the {offset}, we subtract
8678  // the {element_size}-1 from the {byte_length} here (clamped to
8679  // positive safe integer range), and perform a check against that
8680  // with the {offset} below.
8681  byte_length = graph()->NewNode(
8682  simplified()->NumberMax(), jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(),
8683  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), byte_length,
8684  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(element_size - 1)));
8685  }
8686 
8687  // Check that the {offset} is within range of the {byte_length}.
8688  offset = effect =
8689  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(
8690  p.feedback(), CheckBoundsFlag::kAllow64BitBounds),
8691  offset, byte_length, effect, control);
8692  }
8693 
8694  // Coerce {is_little_endian} to boolean.
8695  is_little_endian =
8696  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), is_little_endian);
8697 
8698  // Coerce {value} to Number.
8699  if (access == DataViewAccess::kSet) {
8700  if (element_type == kExternalBigInt64Array ||
8701  element_type == kExternalBigUint64Array) {
8702  value = effect =
8703  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToBigInt(
8704  BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt, p.feedback()),
8705  value, effect, control);
8706  } else {
8707  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8708  simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
8709  NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
8710  value, effect, control);
8711  }
8712  }
8713 
8714  // We need to retain either the {receiver} itself or its backing
8715  // JSArrayBuffer to make sure that the GC doesn't collect the raw
8716  // memory. We default to {receiver} here, and only use the buffer
8717  // if we anyways have to load it (to reduce register pressure).
8718  Node* buffer_or_receiver = receiver;
8719 
8720  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
8721  // Get the underlying buffer and check that it has not been detached.
8722  Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8723  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
8724  receiver, effect, control);
8725 
8726  // Bail out if the {buffer} was detached.
8727  Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8728  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
8729  buffer, effect, control);
8730  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
8731  simplified()->NumberEqual(),
8732  graph()->NewNode(
8733  simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
8734  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
8735  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
8736  effect = graph()->NewNode(
8737  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached,
8738  p.feedback()),
8739  check, effect, control);
8740 
8741  // We can reduce register pressure by holding on to the {buffer}
8742  // now to retain the backing store memory.
8743  buffer_or_receiver = buffer;
8744  }
8745 
8746  // Load the {receiver}s data pointer.
8747  Node* data_pointer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8748  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewDataPointer()),
8749  receiver, effect, control);
8750 
8751  switch (access) {
8752  case DataViewAccess::kGet:
8753  // Perform the load.
8754  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8755  simplified()->LoadDataViewElement(element_type), buffer_or_receiver,
8756  data_pointer, offset, is_little_endian, effect, control);
8757  break;
8758  case DataViewAccess::kSet:
8759  // Perform the store.
8760  effect = graph()->NewNode(
8761  simplified()->StoreDataViewElement(element_type), buffer_or_receiver,
8762  data_pointer, offset, value, is_little_endian, effect, control);
8763  value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
8764  break;
8765  }
8766 
8767  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8768  return Changed(value);
8769 }
8770 
8771 // ES6 section 18.2.2 isFinite ( number )
8772 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceGlobalIsFinite(Node* node) {
8773  JSCallNode n(node);
8774  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8775  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
8776  return NoChange();
8777  }
8778  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
8779  Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
8780  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
8781  return Replace(value);
8782  }
8783 
8784  Effect effect = n.effect();
8785  Control control = n.control();
8786  Node* input = n.Argument(0);
8787 
8788  input = effect =
8789  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
8790  NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
8791  input, effect, control);
8792  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberIsFinite(), input);
8793  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
8794  return Replace(value);
8795 }

8815  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(

8817  input, effect, control);

8831  return NoChange();

8841 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-date.prototype.getdate
8842 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-date.prototype.getday
8843 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-date.prototype.getfullyear
8844 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-date.prototype.gethours
8845 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-date.prototype.getminutes
8846 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-date.prototype.getmonth
8847 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-date.prototype.getseconds
8848 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceDatePrototypeGetField(Node* node,
8849  JSDate::FieldIndex field) {
8850  DCHECK_LT(field, JSDate::kFirstUncachedField);
8851  if (!v8_flags.turbofan_inline_date_accessors) return NoChange();
8852 
8853  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
8854  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8855  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
8856 
8857  MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8858  if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_DATE_TYPE)) {
8859  return NoChange();
8860  }
8861 
8862  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoDateTimeConfigurationChangeProtector()) {
8863  return NoChange();
8864  }
8865 
8866 #define __ gasm.
8867  JSGraphAssembler gasm(broker(), jsgraph(), jsgraph()->zone(),
8868  BranchSemantics::kJS);
8869  gasm.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
8870 
8871  Node* value =
8872  __ LoadField<Object>(AccessBuilder::ForJSDateField(field),
8873  TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(receiver));
8874 
8875  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, gasm.effect(), gasm.control());
8876  return Replace(value);
8877 #undef __
8878 }

8890 // ES6 section 20.1.2.13 Number.parseInt ( string, radix )
8891 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceNumberParseInt(Node* node) {
8892  JSCallNode n(node);
8893  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
8894  Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
8895  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
8896  return Replace(value);
8897  }
8898 
8899  Effect effect = n.effect();
8900  Control control = n.control();
8901  Node* context = n.context();
8902  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
8903  Node* object = n.Argument(0);
8904  Node* radix = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
8905 
8906  // Try constant-folding when input is a string constant.
8907  HeapObjectMatcher object_matcher(object);
8908  HeapObjectMatcher radix_object_matcher(radix);
8909  NumberMatcher radix_number_matcher(radix);
8910  if (object_matcher.HasResolvedValue() &&
8911  object_matcher.Ref(broker()).IsString() &&
8912  (radix_object_matcher.Is(factory()->undefined_value()) ||
8913  radix_number_matcher.HasResolvedValue())) {
8914  StringRef input_value = object_matcher.Ref(broker()).AsString();
8915  // {undefined} is treated same as 0.
8916  int radix_value = radix_object_matcher.Is(factory()->undefined_value())
8917  ? 0
8918  : DoubleToInt32(radix_number_matcher.ResolvedValue());
8919  if (radix_value != 0 && (radix_value < 2 || radix_value > 36)) {
8920  Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
8921  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
8922  return Replace(value);
8923  }
8924 
8925  std::optional<double> number = input_value.ToInt(broker(), radix_value);
8926  if (number.has_value()) {
8927  Node* result = graph()->NewNode(common()->NumberConstant(number.value()));
8928  ReplaceWithValue(node, result);
8929  return Replace(result);
8930  }
8931  }
8932 
8933  node->ReplaceInput(0, object);
8934  node->ReplaceInput(1, radix);
8935  node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
8936  node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
8937  node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
8938  node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
8939  node->TrimInputCount(6);
8940  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ParseInt());
8941  return Changed(node);
8942 }
8943 
8944 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceRegExpPrototypeTest(Node* node) {
8945  JSCallNode n(node);
8946  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8947  if (v8_flags.force_slow_path) return NoChange();
8948  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
8949 
8950  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
8951  return NoChange();
8952  }
8953 
8954  Effect effect = n.effect();
8955  Control control = n.control();
8956  Node* regexp = n.receiver();
8957 
8958  // Only the initial JSRegExp map is valid here, since the following lastIndex
8959  // check as well as the lowered builtin call rely on a known location of the
8960  // lastIndex field.
8961  MapRef regexp_initial_map =
8962  native_context().regexp_function(broker()).initial_map(broker());
8963 
8964  MapInference inference(broker(), regexp, effect);
8965  if (!inference.Is(regexp_initial_map)) return inference.NoChange();
8966  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& regexp_maps = inference.GetMaps();
8967 
8968  ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(graph()->zone());
8969  AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
8970 
8971  for (MapRef map : regexp_maps) {
8972  access_infos.push_back(broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(
8973  map, broker()->exec_string(), AccessMode::kLoad));
8974  }
8975 
8976  PropertyAccessInfo ai_exec =
8977  access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfosAsOne(access_infos,
8978  AccessMode::kLoad);
8979  if (ai_exec.IsInvalid()) return inference.NoChange();
8980  if (!ai_exec.IsFastDataConstant()) return inference.NoChange();
8981 
8982  // Do not reduce if the exec method is not on the prototype chain.
8983  OptionalJSObjectRef holder = ai_exec.holder();
8984  if (!holder.has_value()) return inference.NoChange();
8985 
8986  // Bail out if the exec method is not the original one.
8987  if (ai_exec.field_representation().IsDouble()) return inference.NoChange();
8988  OptionalObjectRef constant = holder->GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
8989  broker(), ai_exec.field_representation(), ai_exec.field_index(),
8990  dependencies());
8991  if (!constant.has_value() ||
8992  !constant->equals(native_context().regexp_exec_function(broker()))) {
8993  return inference.NoChange();
8994  }
8995 
8996  // Add proper dependencies on the {regexp}s [[Prototype]]s.
8997  dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
8998  ai_exec.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype, holder.value());
8999 
9000  inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
9001  control, p.feedback());
9002 
9003  Node* context = n.context();
9004  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
9005  Node* search = n.Argument(0);
9006  Node* search_string = effect = graph()->NewNode(
9007  simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), search, effect, control);
9008 
9009  Node* lastIndex = effect = graph()->NewNode(
9010  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSRegExpLastIndex()), regexp,
9011  effect, control);
9012 
9013  Node* lastIndexSmi = effect = graph()->NewNode(
9014  simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), lastIndex, effect, control);
9015 
9016  Node* is_positive = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(),
9017  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), lastIndexSmi);
9018 
9019  effect = graph()->NewNode(
9020  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi, p.feedback()),
9021  is_positive, effect, control);
9022 
9023  node->ReplaceInput(0, regexp);
9024  node->ReplaceInput(1, search_string);
9025  node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
9026  node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
9027  node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
9028  node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
9029  node->TrimInputCount(6);
9030  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->RegExpTest());
9031  return Changed(node);
9032 }
9033 
9034 // ES section #sec-number-constructor
9035 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceNumberConstructor(Node* node) {
9036  JSCallNode n(node);
9037  Node* target = n.target();
9038  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
9039  Node* value = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
9040  Node* context = n.context();
9041  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
9042 
9043  // Create the artificial frame state in the middle of the Number constructor.
9044  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info =
9045  native_context().number_function(broker()).shared(broker());
9046  Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
9047  jsgraph(), shared_info, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
9048 
9049  // Convert the {value} to a Number.
9050  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
9051  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToNumberConvertBigInt());
9052  NodeProperties::ReplaceFrameStateInput(node, continuation_frame_state);
9053  return Changed(node);
9054 }
9055 
9056 // ES section #sec-bigint-constructor
9057 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBigIntConstructor(Node* node) {
9058  if (!jsgraph()->machine()->Is64()) return NoChange();
9059 
9060  JSCallNode n(node);
9061  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
9062  return NoChange();
9063  }
9064 
9065  Node* target = n.target();
9066  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
9067  Node* value = n.Argument(0);
9068  Node* context = n.context();
9069  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
9070 
9071  // Create the artificial frame state in the middle of the BigInt constructor.
9072  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info =
9073  native_context().bigint_function(broker()).shared(broker());
9074  Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
9075  jsgraph(), shared_info, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
9076 
9077  // Convert the {value} to a BigInt.
9078  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
9079  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToBigIntConvertNumber());
9080  NodeProperties::ReplaceFrameStateInput(node, continuation_frame_state);
9081  return Changed(node);
9082 }
9083 
9084 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBigIntAsN(Node* node, Builtin builtin) {
9085  DCHECK(builtin == Builtin::kBigIntAsIntN ||
9086  builtin == Builtin::kBigIntAsUintN);
9087 
9088  if (!jsgraph()->machine()->Is64()) return NoChange();
9089 
9090  JSCallNode n(node);
9091  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
9092  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
9093  return NoChange();
9094  }
9095  if (n.ArgumentCount() < 2) {
9096  return NoChange();
9097  }
9098 
9099  Effect effect = n.effect();
9100  Control control = n.control();
9101  Node* bits = n.Argument(0);
9102  Node* value = n.Argument(1);
9103 
9104  NumberMatcher matcher(bits);
9105  if (matcher.IsInteger() && matcher.IsInRange(0, 64)) {
9106  const int bits_value = static_cast<int>(matcher.ResolvedValue());
9107  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
9108  (builtin == Builtin::kBigIntAsIntN
9109  ? simplified()->SpeculativeBigIntAsIntN(bits_value, p.feedback())
9110  : simplified()->SpeculativeBigIntAsUintN(bits_value,
9111  p.feedback())),
9112  value, effect, control);
9113  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
9114  return Replace(value);
9115  }
9116 
9117  return NoChange();
9118 }
9119 
9120 std::optional<Reduction> JSCallReducer::TryReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(
9121  Node* node) {
9122  if (!v8_flags.turbo_optimize_math_minmax) return std::nullopt;
9123 
9124  JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
9125  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
9126  Node* target = n.target();
9127  Effect effect = n.effect();
9128  Control control = n.control();
9129 
9130  if (p.speculation_mode() != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) {
9131  return std::nullopt;
9132  }
9133 
9134  if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) {
9135  return std::nullopt;
9136  }
9137 
9138  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
9139  return std::nullopt;
9140  }
9141 
9142  // These ops are handled by ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread.
9143  // IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray is not included, since arguments_list
9144  // for Math.min/min is not likely to keep empty.
9145  Node* arguments_list = n.Argument(0);
9146  if (arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateLiteralArray ||
9147  arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateArguments) {
9148  return std::nullopt;
9149  }
9150 
9151  HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
9152  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
9153  ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
9154  if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
9155  JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
9156 
9157  // Don't inline cross native context.
9158  if (!function.native_context(broker()).equals(native_context())) {
9159  return std::nullopt;
9160  }
9161 
9162  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = function.shared(broker());
9163  Builtin builtin =
9164  shared.HasBuiltinId() ? shared.builtin_id() : Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
9165  if (builtin == Builtin::kMathMax || builtin == Builtin::kMathMin) {
9166  return ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(node, builtin);
9167  } else {
9168  return std::nullopt;
9169  }
9170  }
9171  }
9172 
9173  // Try specialize the JSCallWithArrayLike node with feedback target.
9174  if (ShouldUseCallICFeedback(target) &&
9175  p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget &&
9176  p.feedback().IsValid()) {
9177  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
9178  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
9179  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
9180  return std::nullopt;
9181  }
9182  OptionalHeapObjectRef feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
9183  if (feedback_target.has_value() &&
9184  feedback_target->map(broker()).is_callable()) {
9185  Node* target_function =
9186  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*feedback_target, broker());
9187  ObjectRef target_ref = feedback_target.value();
9188  if (!target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
9189  return std::nullopt;
9190  }
9191  JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
9192  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = function.shared(broker());
9193  Builtin builtin =
9194  shared.HasBuiltinId() ? shared.builtin_id() : Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
9195  if (builtin == Builtin::kMathMax || builtin == Builtin::kMathMin) {
9196  // Check that the {target} is still the {target_function}.
9197  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
9198  target_function);
9199  effect = graph()->NewNode(
9200  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
9201  effect, control);
9202 
9203  // Specialize the JSCallWithArrayLike node to the {target_function}.
9204  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_function,
9205  n.TargetIndex());
9206  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
9207  // Try to further reduce the Call MathMin/Max with double array.
9208  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(
9209  ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(node, builtin));
9210  }
9211  }
9212  }
9213 
9214  return std::nullopt;
9215 }
9216 
9217 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(Node* node,
9218  Builtin builtin) {
9219  JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
9220  DCHECK_NE(n.Parameters().speculation_mode(),
9221  SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation);
9222  DCHECK_EQ(n.ArgumentCount(), 1);
9223 
9224  JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
9225  Node* subgraph = a.ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(builtin);
9226  return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
9227 }

9230 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceGetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(

9243 Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceSetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(
9244  Node* node) {
9245  JSCallNode n(node);
9246  Effect effect = n.effect();
9247  Control control = n.control();
9248 
9249  if (n.ArgumentCount() == 0) return NoChange();

9252  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(),
9253  n.Argument(0), effect);
9254

9256 
9257  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
9258  return Replace(node);
9259 }
